biff.definition_0: A sudden, sharp blow or punch.

hoyas.definition_0: Any plant of the genus Hoya

odeum.definition_0: An ancient Greek or Roman building used for performances of music and poetry.

fief.definition_0: An estate held by a person on condition of providing military service to a superior.
fief.definition_1: Something over which one has rights or exercises control.
fief.definition_2: An area of dominion, especially in a corporate or governmental bureaucracy.

gizmo.definition_0: Something, generally a device, for which one does not know the proper term.

pelt.definition_0: A blow or stroke from something thrown.

bract.definition_0: A leaf or leaf-like structure from the axil out of which a stalk of a flower or an inflorescence arises.

gawk.definition_1: A fool; a simpleton; a stupid or clumsy person.

lysin.definition_0: Any substance or antibody that can cause the destruction (by lysis) of blood cells, bacteria etc

tesla.definition_0: In the International System of Units, the derived unit of magnetic flux density or magnetic inductivity. Symbol: T

borax.definition_0: A white or gray/grey crystalline salt, with a slight alkaline taste, used as a flux, in soldering metals, making enamels, fixing colors/colours on porcelain, and as a soap, etc.
borax.definition_1: The sodium salt of boric acid, Na2B4O7, either anhydrous or with 5 or 10 molecules of water of crystallisation; sodium tetraborate.
borax.definition_2: (sometimes attributive) Cheap or tawdry furniture or other works of industrial design.

beaky.definition_2: Having a nose which resembles a beak.

quad.definition_1: A kind of round-robin tournament between four players, where each participant plays every other participant once.
quad.definition_2: The Bible, Book of Mormon, Doctrine and Covenants, and Pearl of Great Price bound in a single volume.

gird.definition_0: To bind with a flexible rope or cord.
gird.definition_1: To encircle with, or as if with a belt.
gird.definition_2: To prepare oneself for an action.

pore.definition_0: A tiny opening in the skin.
pore.definition_1: By extension any small opening or interstice, especially one of many, or one allowing the passage of a fluid.

splash.definition_0: The sound made by an object hitting a liquid.

anise.definition_0: An umbelliferous plant (Pimpinella anisum) growing naturally in Egypt, and cultivated in Spain, Malta, etc., for its carminative and aromatic seeds, which are used as a spice. It has a licorice scent.
anise.definition_1: (often qualified as "sweet anise" or "wild anise") Fennel, Foeniculum vulgare.

jilt.definition_0: A woman who jilts a lover.

rile.definition_1: To stir or move from a state of calm or order

hooch.definition_0: Alcoholic liquor, especially inferior or illicit whisky.

huff.definition_0: A heavy breath; a grunt or sigh.
huff.definition_1: An expression of anger, annoyance, disgust, etc.
huff.definition_2: One swelled with a false sense of importance or value; a boaster.

jibe.definition_0: A facetious or insulting remark; a jeer, a taunt.

dean.definition_0: A senior official in a college or university, who may be in charge of a division or faculty (for example, the dean of science) or have some other advisory or disciplinary function (for example, the dean of students).
dean.definition_1: A dignitary or presiding officer in certain church bodies, especially an ecclesiastical dignitary, subordinate to a bishop, in charge of a chapter of canons.
dean.definition_2: The senior member of some group of people.

gout.definition_0: An extremely painful inflammation of joints, especially of the big toe, caused by a metabolic defect resulting in the accumulation of uric acid in the blood and the deposition of urates around the joints.
gout.definition_1: (usually followed by of) A spurt or splotch.
gout.definition_2: A disease of wheat and cornstalks, caused by insect larvae.

lour.definition_0: A frown, a scowl; an angry or sullen look.
lour.definition_1: Of the sky, the weather, etc.: a dark, gloomy, and threatening appearance.

foggy.definition_0: Obscured by mist or fog; unclear; hazy

lath.definition_0: A thin, narrow strip, fastened to the rafters, studs, or floor beams of a building, for the purpose of supporting a covering of tiles, plastering, etc.

flax.definition_0: A plant of the genus Linum, especially Linum usitatissimum, which has a single, slender stalk, about a foot and a half high, with blue flowers. Also known as linseed, especially when referring to the seeds.
flax.definition_1: The fibers of Linum usitatissimum, grown to make linen and related textiles.
flax.definition_2: The flax bush, a plant of the genus Phormium, native to New Zealand, with strap-like leaves up to 3 metres long that grow in clumps.

prong.definition_0: A thin, pointed, projecting part, as of an antler or a fork or similar tool. A tine.

rill.definition_0: A very small brook; a streamlet.

leek.definition_0: The vegetable Allium ampeloprasum var. porrum, having edible leaves and an onion-like bulb but with a milder flavour than the onion.
leek.definition_1: Any of several species of Allium, broadly resembling the domesticated plant in appearance in the wild.

hurl.definition_0: A throw, especially a violent throw; a fling.
hurl.definition_2: The act of hitting the sliotar with the hurley.

chive.definition_0: A perennial plant, Allium schoenoprasum, related to the onion.
chive.definition_1: (in the plural) The leaves of this plant used as a herb.
chive.definition_2: The style and stigma of a flower, especially saffron.

swale.definition_0: A low tract of moist or marshy land.
swale.definition_1: A long narrow and shallow trough between ridges on a beach, running parallel to the coastline.
swale.definition_2: A shallow troughlike depression that's created to carry water during rainstorms or snow melts; a drainage ditch.

souse.definition_0: Something kept or steeped in brine
souse.definition_1: The act of sousing; a plunging into water.

shive.definition_2: A beam or plank of split wood.

lard.definition_0: Fat from the abdomen of a pig, especially as prepared for use in cooking or pharmacy.
lard.definition_1: Fatty meat from a pig; bacon, pork.

flux.definition_0: The act of flowing; a continuous moving on or passing by, as of a flowing stream.
flux.definition_2: A chemical agent for cleaning metal prior to soldering or welding.

felt.definition_0: A cloth or stuff made of matted fibres of wool, or wool and fur, fulled or wrought into a compact substance by rolling and pressure, with lees or size, without spinning or weaving.
felt.definition_2: A skin or hide; a fell; a pelt.

hanse.definition_0: A merchant guild, particularly the Fellowship of London Merchants (the "Old Hanse") given a monopoly on London's foreign trade by the Normans or its successor, the Company of Merchant Adventurers (the "New Hanse"), incorporated in 1497 and chartered under Henry VII and Elizabeth I.
hanse.definition_1: The rights and privileges of such guilds, particularly their trade monopolies.
hanse.definition_2: A commercial association of Scottish free burghs in the Middle Ages.

wort.definition_1: Any of various plants or herbs, used in combination to refer to specific plants such as St. John's wort, or on its own as a generic term.

weak.definition_0: Lacking in force (usually strength) or ability.
weak.definition_1: Unable to sustain a great weight, pressure, or strain.
weak.definition_2: Unable to withstand temptation, urgency, persuasion, etc.; easily impressed, moved, or overcome; accessible; vulnerable.

cart.definition_0: A small, open, wheeled vehicle, drawn or pushed by a person or animal, more often used for transporting goods than passengers.
cart.definition_1: A small motor vehicle resembling a car; a go-cart.

raze.definition_0: To demolish; to level to the ground.
raze.definition_1: To scrape as if with a razor.

jinn.definition_0: (Muslim demonology) A genie and descendant of the jann, normally invisible to the human eye, but who may also appear in animal or human form, equivalent to demons in Jewish demonology.

magma.definition_0: The molten matter within the earth, the source of the material of lava flows, dikes of eruptive rocks, etc.
magma.definition_1: A basic algebraic structure consisting of a set equipped with a single binary operation.

lava.definition_0: The molten rock ejected by a volcano from its crater or fissured sides.
lava.definition_2: A shade of red, named after the volcanic lava.

marsh.definition_0: An area of low, wet land, often with tall grass.

bursa.definition_0: Any of the many small fluid-filled sacs located at the point where a muscle or tendon slides across bone. These sacs serve to reduce friction between the two moving surfaces.

aegis.definition_0: A mythological shield associated with the Greek deities Zeus and Athena (and their Roman counterparts Jupiter and Minerva) shown as a short cloak made of goatskin worn on the shoulders, more as an emblem of power and protection than a military shield. The aegis of Athena or Minerva is usually shown with a border of snakes and with the head of Medusa in the center.
aegis.definition_1: Usually as under the aegis: guidance, protection; endorsement, sponsorship.

haze.definition_0: Very fine solid particles (smoke, dust) or liquid droplets (moisture) suspended in the air, slightly limiting visibility.
haze.definition_1: A reduction of transparency of a clear gas or liquid.
haze.definition_2: An analogous dullness on a surface that is ideally highly reflective or transparent.

slice.definition_0: That which is thin and broad.
slice.definition_1: A thin, broad piece cut off.

mite.definition_0: Any of many minute arachnids which, along with the ticks, comprise subclass Acarina (aka Acari).
mite.definition_1: A small coin formerly circulated in England, rated at about a third of a farthing.
mite.definition_2: A lepton, a small coin used in Palestine in the time of Christ.

strong.definition_0: Capable of producing great physical force.
strong.definition_1: Capable of withstanding great physical force.
strong.definition_2: (of water, wind, etc.) Having a lot of power.

burst.definition_0: An act or instance of bursting.
burst.definition_1: A sudden, often intense, expression, manifestation or display.
burst.definition_2: A series of shots fired from an automatic firearm.

scale.definition_0: A ladder; a series of steps; a means of ascending.
scale.definition_1: An ordered, usually numerical sequence used for measurement, means of assigning a magnitude.

ruff.definition_0: A circular frill or ruffle on a garment, especially a starched, fluted frill at the neck in Elizabethan and Jacobean England (1560s–1620s).
ruff.definition_1: Anything formed with plaits or flutings like a frill.

plant.definition_0: An organism that is not an animal, especially an organism capable of photosynthesis. Typically a small or herbaceous organism of this kind, rather than a tree.
plant.definition_1: An organism of the kingdom Plantae; now specifically, a living organism of the Embryophyta (land plants) or of the Chlorophyta (green algae), a eukaryote that includes double-membraned chloroplasts in its cells containing chlorophyll a and b, or any organism closely related to such an organism.
plant.definition_2: Now specifically, a multicellular eukaryote that includes chloroplasts in its cells, which have a cell wall.

stalk.definition_0: The stem or main axis of a plant, which supports the seed-carrying parts.
stalk.definition_1: The petiole, pedicel, or peduncle of a plant.
stalk.definition_2: Something resembling the stalk of a plant, such as the stem of a quill.

quick.definition_0: Raw or sensitive flesh, especially that underneath finger and toe nails.
quick.definition_1: Plants used in making a quickset hedge
quick.definition_2: The life; the mortal point; a vital part; a part susceptible to serious injury or keen feeling.

fruit.definition_0: (often in the plural) In general, a product of plant growth useful to man or animals.
fruit.definition_1: Specifically, a sweet, edible part of a plant that resembles seed-bearing fruit (see next sense), even if it does not develop from a floral ovary; also used in a technically imprecise sense for some sweet or sweetish vegetables, such as the petioles of rhubarb, that resemble a true fruit or are used in cookery as if they were a fruit.
fruit.definition_2: A product of fertilization in a plant, specifically:

fiber.definition_0: A single elongated piece of a given material, roughly round in cross-section, often twisted with other fibers to form thread.
fiber.definition_1: A material in the form of fibers.
fiber.definition_2: A material whose length is at least 1000 times its width.

blue.definition_0: The colour of the clear sky or the deep sea, between green and violet in the visible spectrum, and one of the primary additive colours for transmitted light; the colour obtained by subtracting red and green from white light using magenta and cyan filters; or any colour resembling this.
blue.definition_2: Any of several processes to protect metal against rust.

strip.definition_0: A long, thin piece of land; any long, thin area.
strip.definition_1: (usually countable, sometimes uncountable) A long, thin piece of any material; any such material collectively.

nerd.definition_0: (sometimes derogatory) A person who is intellectual but generally introverted
nerd.definition_1: (sometimes derogatory) One who has an intense, obsessive interest in something.
nerd.definition_2: An unattractive, socially awkward, annoying, undesirable, and/or boring, person; a dork.

book.definition_0: A collection of sheets of paper bound together to hinge at one edge, containing printed or written material, pictures, etc.
book.definition_1: A long work fit for publication, typically prose, such as a novel or textbook, and typically published as such a bound collection of sheets, but now sometimes electronically as an e-book.
book.definition_2: A major division of a long work.

quay.definition_0: A stone or concrete structure on navigable water used for loading and unloading vessels; a wharf.

flesh.definition_0: The soft tissue of the body, especially muscle and fat.
flesh.definition_1: The skin of a human or animal.
flesh.definition_2: (by extension) Bare arms, bare legs, bare torso.

grill.definition_0: A grating; a grid of wire or a sheet of material with a pattern of holes or slots, usually used to protect something while allowing the passage of air and liquids. Typical uses: to allow air through a fan while preventing fingers or objects from passing; to allow people to talk to somebody, while preventing attack.
grill.definition_1: On a vehicle, a slotted cover as above, to protect and hide the radiator, while admitting air to cool it.
grill.definition_2: A cooking device comprising a source of radiative heat and a means of holding food under it; a broiler in US English

salvo.definition_0: An exception; a reservation; an excuse.

stone.definition_0: A hard earthen substance that can form large rocks.
stone.definition_1: A small piece of stone, a pebble.
stone.definition_2: A gemstone, a jewel, especially a diamond.

flash.definition_0: A device that produces a short flash of light to help illuminate a scene, mostly for night-time or indoors photography.

twig.definition_0: A small thin branch of a tree or bush.

hone.definition_0: A sharpening stone composed of extra-fine grit used for removing the burr or curl from the blade of a razor or some other edge tool.
hone.definition_1: A machine tool used in the manufacture of precision bores.

claw.definition_0: A curved, pointed horny nail on each digit of the foot of a mammal, reptile, or bird.
claw.definition_2: The pincer (chela) of a crustacean or other arthropod.

quail.definition_0: To waste away; to fade, to wither
quail.definition_2: To lose heart or courage; to be daunted or fearful.

knob.definition_0: A rounded protuberance, especially one arising from a flat surface; a fleshy lump or caruncle.
knob.definition_1: A rounded control switch that can be turned on its axis, designed to be operated by the fingers.
knob.definition_2: A ball-shaped part of a handle, lever, etc., designed to be grabbed by the hand.

clue.definition_0: A strand of yarn etc. as used to guide one through a labyrinth; something which points the way, a guide.
clue.definition_1: Information which may lead one to a certain point or conclusion.
clue.definition_2: An object or a kind of indication which may be used as evidence.

clew.definition_0: A roughly spherical mass or body.
clew.definition_1: A ball of thread or yarn.
clew.definition_2: Yarn or thread as used to guide one's way through a maze or labyrinth; a guide, a clue.

laugh.definition_0: An expression of mirth particular to the human species; the sound heard in laughing; laughter.
laugh.definition_1: Something that provokes mirth or scorn.

ball.definition_0: A solid or hollow sphere, or roughly spherical mass.
ball.definition_2: (mildly, usually in the plural) A testicle.

whale.definition_0: Any of several species of large sea mammals of the infraorder Cetacea.
whale.definition_1: Something, or someone, that is very large.
whale.definition_2: Something, or someone, that is excellent.

onion.definition_0: A monocotyledonous plant (Allium cepa), allied to garlic, used as vegetable and spice.
onion.definition_1: The bulb of such a plant.

filet.definition_0: A headband; a ribbon or other band used to tie the hair up, or keep a headdress in place, or for decoration.
filet.definition_1: A fine strip of any material, in various technical uses.
filet.definition_2: A heavy bead of waterproofing compound or sealant material generally installed at the point where vertical and horizontal surfaces meet.

blend.definition_0: A mixture of two or more things.
blend.definition_1: A word formed by combining two other words; a grammatical contamination, portmanteau word.

water.definition_0: A substance (of molecular formula H₂O) found at room temperature and pressure as a clear liquid; it is present naturally as rain, and found in rivers, lakes and seas; its solid form is ice and its gaseous form is steam.
water.definition_1: The aforementioned liquid, considered one of the Classical elements or basic elements of alchemy.
water.definition_2: Water in a body; an area of open water.

large.definition_0: An old musical note, equal to two longas, four breves, or eight semibreves.

prey.definition_0: Anything, as goods, etc., taken or got by violence; anything taken by force from an enemy in war
prey.definition_1: That which is or may be seized by animals or birds to be devoured; hence, a person given up as a victim.
prey.definition_2: A living thing that is eaten by another living thing.

wand.definition_0: A hand-held narrow rod, usually used for pointing or instructing, or as a traditional emblem of authority.
wand.definition_1: (by extension) An instrument shaped like a wand, such as a curling wand.

flay.definition_1: Fear; a source of fear; a formidable matter; a fearsome or repellent-looking individual.

crust.definition_0: A more solid, dense or hard layer on a surface or boundary.
crust.definition_1: The external, hardened layer of certain foodstuffs, including most types of bread, fried meat, etc.
crust.definition_2: An outer layer composed of pastry

gloss.definition_1: A superficially or deceptively attractive appearance

whig.definition_0: Acidulated whey, sometimes mixed with buttermilk and sweet herbs, used as a cooling beverage.

maze.definition_0: A labyrinth; a puzzle consisting of a complicated network of paths or passages, the aim of which is to find one's way.
maze.definition_1: Something made up of many confused or conflicting elements; a tangle.
maze.definition_2: Confusion of thought; state of bewilderment.

shore.definition_0: Land adjoining a non-flowing body of water, such as an ocean, lake or pond.
shore.definition_1: (from the perspective of one on a body of water) Land, usually near a port.

great.definition_0: A person of major significance, accomplishment or acclaim.
great.definition_1: The main division in a pipe organ, usually the loudest division.
great.definition_2: (in combinations such as "two-greats", "three-greats" etc.) An instance of the word "great" signifying an additional generation in phrases expressing family relationships.

piece.definition_0: A part of a larger whole, usually in such a form that it is able to be separated from other parts.
piece.definition_1: A single item belonging to a class of similar items
piece.definition_2: One of the figures used in playing chess, specifically a higher-value figure as distinguished from a pawn; by extension, a similar counter etc. in other games.

fluid.definition_0: Any substance which can flow with relative ease, tends to assume the shape of its container, and obeys Bernoulli's principle; a liquid, gas or plasma.
fluid.definition_1: A liquid (as opposed to a solid or gas).
fluid.definition_2: (specifically, typically in the plural) Intravenous fluids.

glue.definition_0: A hard gelatin made by boiling bones and hides, used in solution as an adhesive; or any sticky adhesive substance.
glue.definition_1: Anything that binds two things or people together.

joke.definition_1: Something said or done for amusement, not in seriousness.
joke.definition_2: The root cause or main issue, especially an unexpected one

knot.definition_0: A looping of a piece of string or of any other long, flexible material that cannot be untangled without passing one or both ends of the material through its loops.

rock.definition_1: A large hill or island having no vegetation.
rock.definition_2: Something that is strong, stable, and dependable; a person who provides security or support to another.

stock.definition_1: The capital raised by a company through the issue of shares. The total of shares held by an individual shareholder.
stock.definition_2: The raw material from which things are made; feedstock.

yelp.definition_0: An abrupt, high-pitched noise or utterance.
yelp.definition_1: A type of emergency vehicle siren sounding quicker and more intense than the wail.

acre.definition_0: An English unit of land area (symbol: a. or ac.) originally denoting a day's plowing for a yoke of oxen, now standardized as 4,840 square yards or 4,046.86 square meters.
acre.definition_1: Any of various similar units of area in other systems.
acre.definition_2: (usually in the plural) A wide expanse.

meter.definition_0: (always meter) A device that measures things.
meter.definition_1: (always meter) A parking meter or similar device for collecting payment.
meter.definition_2: (always meter) One who metes or measures.

pier.definition_0: A raised platform built from the shore out over water, supported on piles; used to secure, or provide access to shipping; a jetty.
pier.definition_1: A similar structure, especially at a seaside resort, used to provide entertainment.
pier.definition_2: A structure that projects tangentially from the shoreline to accommodate ships; often double-sided.

alarm.definition_0: A summons to arms, as on the approach of an enemy.
alarm.definition_1: Any sound or information intended to give notice of approaching danger; a warning sound to arouse attention; a warning of danger.

whip.definition_0: A lash; a pliant, flexible instrument, such as a rod (commonly of cane or rattan) or a plaited or braided rope or thong (commonly of leather) used to create a sharp "crack" sound for directing or herding animals.
whip.definition_1: A blow administered with a whip.

yard.definition_0: A small, usually uncultivated area adjoining or (now especially) within the precincts of a house or other building.
yard.definition_1: The property surrounding one's house, typically dominated by one's lawn.
yard.definition_2: An enclosed area designated for a specific purpose, e.g. on farms, railways etc.

stick.definition_0: An elongated piece of wood or similar material, typically put to some use, for example as a wand or baton.
stick.definition_1: Any roughly cylindrical (or rectangular) unit of a substance.
stick.definition_2: Material or objects attached to a stick or the like.

Stage.definition_1: A platform; a surface, generally elevated, upon which show performances or other public events are given.
Stage.definition_2: A floor or storey of a house.

hail.definition_0: Balls or pieces of ice falling as precipitation, often in connection with a thunderstorm.

reed.definition_0: Any of various types of tall stiff perennial grass-like plants growing together in groups near water.
reed.definition_1: The hollow stem of these plants.
reed.definition_2: Part of the mouthpiece of certain woodwind instruments, comprising a thin piece of wood or metal which shakes very quickly to produce sound when a musician blows over it.

arrow.definition_0: A projectile consisting of a shaft, a point and a tail with stabilizing fins that is shot from a bow.
arrow.definition_1: A sign or symbol used to indicate a direction (e.g. →).

felon.definition_0: A person who has committed a felony.
felon.definition_1: A person who has been tried and convicted of a felony.

form.definition_1: (social) To do with structure or procedure.
form.definition_2: A blank document or template to be filled in by the user.

node.definition_0: A knot, knob, protuberance or swelling.
node.definition_1: The point where the orbit of a planet, as viewed from the Sun, intersects the ecliptic. The ascending and descending nodes refer respectively to the points where the planet moves from South to North and N to S; their respective symbols are ☊ and ☋.

earth.definition_0: The third planet of the Solar System; the world upon which humans live.
earth.definition_1: The personification of the Earth or earth, as a fertile woman or goddess.

grass.definition_0: Any plant of the family Poaceae, characterized by leaves that arise from nodes in the stem and leaf bases that wrap around the stem, especially those grown as ground cover rather than for grain.
grass.definition_1: Various plants not in family Poaceae that resemble grasses.

hater.definition_1: One who expresses unfounded or inappropriate hatred or dislike, particularly if motivated by envy.

donor.definition_1: A group or molecule that donates either a radical, electrons or a moiety in a chemical reaction. Compare acceptor.

conga.definition_0: A tall, narrow, single-headed Cuban hand drum of African origin
conga.definition_1: A march of Cuban origin in four-four time in which people form a chain, each holding the hips of the person in front of them; in each bar, dancers take three shuffle steps and then kick alternate legs outwards at the beat; the chain weaves around the place and allows new participants to join the back of the chain

pox.definition_0: A disease characterized by purulent skin eruptions that may leave pockmarks.

thing.definition_0: That which is considered to exist as a separate entity, object, quality or concept.
thing.definition_1: A word, symbol, sign, or other referent that can be used to refer to any entity.
thing.definition_2: An individual object or distinct entity.

money.definition_0: A legally or socially binding conceptual contract of entitlement to wealth, void of intrinsic value, payable for all debts and taxes, and regulated in supply.
money.definition_1: A generally accepted means of exchange and measure of value.
money.definition_2: A currency maintained by a state or other entity which can guarantee its value (such as a monetary union).

fund.definition_0: A sum or source of money.
fund.definition_2: A money-management operation, such as a mutual fund.

glade.definition_0: An open passage through a wood; a grassy open or cleared space in a forest.
glade.definition_2: An open space in the ice on a river or lake.

tepid.definition_1: Uninterested; exhibiting little passion or eagerness.

gloat.definition_0: An act or instance of gloating.

grump.definition_0: A habitually grumpy or complaining person.

avoid.definition_0: To try not to meet or communicate with (a person); to shun
avoid.definition_1: To keep away from; to keep clear of; to stay away from
avoid.definition_2: To try not to do something or to have something happen

jest.definition_0: An act performed for amusement; a joke.
jest.definition_1: Someone or something that is ridiculed; the target of a joke.
jest.definition_2: A deed; an action; a gest.

young.definition_0: People who are young; young people, collectively; youth.
young.definition_1: Young or immature offspring (especially of an animal).
young.definition_2: (possibly nonstandard) An individual offspring; a single recently born or hatched organism.

cheep.definition_0: A short, high-pitched sound made by a small bird.

oxide.definition_0: A binary chemical compound of oxygen with another chemical element.

tumor.definition_0: An abnormal growth; differential diagnosis includes abscess, metaplasia, and neoplasia.

doze.definition_0: A light, short sleep or nap.

primp.definition_0: To spend time improving one's appearance, often in front of a mirror.
primp.definition_1: To dress in an affected manner.

oval.definition_0: An elongated round shape resembling an egg or ellipse.
oval.definition_1: A thing having such a shape, such as an arena.
oval.definition_2: In a projective plane, a set of points such that no three are collinear and there is a unique tangent line at each point.

prink.definition_0: To give a wink; to wink.

befog.definition_0: To envelop in fog or smoke.
befog.definition_1: To confuse, mystify (a person); to make less acute or perceptive, to cloud (a person’s faculties).
befog.definition_2: To obscure, make less clear (a subject, issue, etc.).

refer.definition_1: To submit to (another person or group) for consideration; to send or direct elsewhere.
refer.definition_2: To place in or under by a mental or rational process; to assign to, as a class, a cause, source, a motive, reason, or ground of explanation.

pasty.definition_0: (chiefly in the plural) A small item of clothing that conceals little more than the nipple of a woman's breast, primarily worn by female exotic dancers.

jaunt.definition_1: A short excursion for pleasure or refreshment; a ramble; a short journey.

order.definition_1: A position in an arrangement, disposition, or sequence.
order.definition_2: The state of being well arranged.

evade.definition_0: To get away from by cunning; to avoid by dexterity, subterfuge, address, or ingenuity; to elude; to cleverly escape from
evade.definition_1: To escape; to slip away; — sometimes with from.
evade.definition_2: To attempt to escape; to practice artifice or sophistry, for the purpose of eluding.

dwell.definition_0: A period of time in which a system or component remains in a given state.
dwell.definition_1: A brief pause in the motion of part of a mechanism to allow an operation to be completed.
dwell.definition_2: A planned delay in a timed control program.

file.definition_0: A collection of papers collated and archived together.
file.definition_2: Course of thought; thread of narration.

cloy.definition_0: To fill up or choke up; to stop up.
cloy.definition_1: To clog, to glut, or satisfy, as the appetite; to satiate.
cloy.definition_2: To fill to loathing; to surfeit.

greed.definition_0: A selfish or excessive desire for more than is needed or deserved, especially of money, wealth, food, or other possessions.

vigor.definition_0: Active strength or force of body or mind; capacity for exertion, physically, intellectually, or morally; energy.
vigor.definition_1: Strength or force in animal or vegetable nature or action.

ocher.definition_0: An earth pigment containing silica, aluminum and ferric oxide
ocher.definition_1: A somewhat dark yellowish orange colour

liger.definition_0: An animal born to a male lion and a tigress.

loose.definition_1: A state of laxity or indulgence; unrestrained freedom, abandonment.
loose.definition_2: All play other than set pieces (scrums and line-outs).

ink.definition_0: A pigment (or dye)-based fluid used for writing, printing etc.
ink.definition_1: A particular type, color or container of this fluid.
ink.definition_2: The black or dark-colored fluid ejected by squid, octopus etc, as a protective strategy.

cable.definition_0: (material) A long object used to make a physical connection.
cable.definition_1: (communications) A system for transmitting television or Internet services over a network of coaxial or fibreoptic cables.
cable.definition_2: A telegram, notably when sent by (submarine) telegraph cable.

trick.definition_0: Something designed to fool or swindle.
trick.definition_1: A single element of a magician's (or any variety entertainer's) act; a magic trick.

tube.definition_0: Anything that is hollow and cylindrical in shape.
tube.definition_1: An approximately cylindrical container, usually with a crimped end and a screw top, used to contain and dispense semiliquid substances.
tube.definition_2: (often capitalized as Tube) The London Underground railway system, originally referred to the lower level lines that ran in tubular tunnels as opposed to the higher ones which ran in rectangular section tunnels. (Often the tube.)

gummy.definition_0: A sheep that is losing or has lost its teeth.

month.definition_0: A period into which a year is divided, historically based on the phases of the moon.
month.definition_1: A period of 30 days, 31 days, or some alternation thereof.
month.definition_2: (in the plural) A woman's period; menstrual discharge.

canal.definition_0: An artificial waterway or artificially improved river used for travel, shipping, or irrigation.
canal.definition_1: A tubular channel within the body.
canal.definition_2: One of the faint, hazy markings resembling straight lines on early telescopic images of the surface of Mars.

sticky.definition_0: A sticky note, such as a post-it note.
sticky.definition_1: A discussion thread fixed at the top of the list of topics or threads so as to keep it in view.
sticky.definition_2: A small adhesive particle found in wastepaper.

shrew.definition_0: Any of numerous small, mouselike, chiefly nocturnal, mammals of the family Soricidae (order Soricomorpha).
shrew.definition_1: Certain other small mammals that resemble true shrews (order Soricomorpha).
shrew.definition_2: An ill-tempered, nagging woman: a scold.

lyric.definition_1: (also in plural) The words of a song or other vocal music. The singular form often refers to a part of the words, whereas the plural form can refer to all of the words.

alert.definition_1: A notification of higher importance than an advisory.
alert.definition_2: A state of readiness for potential combat.

cause.definition_0: (often with of, typically of adverse results) The source of, or reason for, an event or action; that which produces or effects a result.
cause.definition_1: (especially with for and a bare noun) Sufficient reason for a state, as of emotion.
cause.definition_2: A goal, aim or principle, especially one which transcends purely selfish ends.

firm.definition_0: A business partnership; the name under which it trades.
firm.definition_2: A criminal gang, especially based around football hooliganism.

state.definition_0: A condition; a set of circumstances applying at any given time.

grasp.definition_2: That which is accessible; that which is within one's reach or ability.

gore.definition_0: Blood, especially that from a wound when thickened due to exposure to the air.

tusk.definition_0: One of a pair of elongated pointed teeth that extend outside the mouth of an animal such as walrus, elephant or wild boar.
tusk.definition_1: A small projection on a (tusk) tenon.

wake.definition_0: The act of waking, or state of being awake.
wake.definition_1: The state of forbearing sleep, especially for solemn or festive purposes; a vigil.

sleep.definition_0: To rest in a state of reduced consciousness.
sleep.definition_1: (of a spinning top or yo-yo) To spin on its axis with no other perceptible motion.
sleep.definition_2: To cause (a spinning top or yo-yo) to spin on its axis with no other perceptible motion.

duct.definition_0: A pipe, tube or canal which carries gas or liquid from one place to another.
duct.definition_1: An enclosure or channel for electrical cable runs.

event.definition_2: One of several contests that combine to make up a competition.

date.definition_0: The fruit of the date palm, Phoenix dactylifera, somewhat in the shape of an olive, containing a soft, sweet pulp and enclosing a hard kernel.

grip.definition_0: To take hold of, particularly with the hand.
grip.definition_1: To help or assist, particularly in an emotional sense.
grip.definition_2: To do something with another that makes you happy/gives you relief.

numb.definition_0: To cause to become numb (physically or emotionally).
numb.definition_1: To cause (a feeling) to be less intense.
numb.definition_2: To cause (the mind, faculties, etc.) to be less acute.

mouse.definition_0: Any small rodent of the genus Mus.
mouse.definition_1: A member of the many small rodent and marsupial species resembling such a rodent.

snout.definition_0: The long, projecting nose, mouth, and jaw of a beast, as of pigs.
snout.definition_1: The front of the prow of a ship or boat.

vigil.definition_0: An instance of keeping awake during normal sleeping hours, especially to keep watch or pray.
vigil.definition_1: A period of observation or surveillance at any hour.
vigil.definition_2: The eve of a religious festival in which staying awake is part of the ritual devotions.

lemon.definition_1: A semitropical evergreen tree, Citrus limon, that bears such fruits.
lemon.definition_2: A taste or flavour/flavor of lemons.

aware.definition_0: Vigilant or on one's guard against danger or difficulty.
aware.definition_1: Conscious or having knowledge of something.

dead.definition_0: (with "the", a demonstrative, or a possessive) Those who have died.

orbit.definition_0: A circular or elliptical path of one object around another object, particularly in astronomy and space travel.
orbit.definition_1: A sphere of influence; an area of control.
orbit.definition_2: The course of one's usual progression, or the extent of one's typical range.

yoke.definition_0: Frame around the neck, and related senses.
yoke.definition_1: Pair of harnessed draught animals, and related senses.

foul.definition_0: Covered with, or containing unclean matter; dirty.
foul.definition_1: (of words or a way of speaking) obscene, vulgar or abusive.

knee.definition_0: In humans, the joint or the region of the joint in the middle part of the leg between the thigh and the shank.
knee.definition_1: In the horse and allied animals, the carpal joint, corresponding to the wrist in humans.
knee.definition_2: The part of a garment that covers the knee.

limb.definition_0: A major appendage of human or animal, used for locomotion (such as an arm, leg or wing).
limb.definition_2: The part of the bow, from the handle to the tip.

sew.definition_0: To use a needle to pass thread repeatedly through (pieces of fabric) in order to join them together.
sew.definition_1: To use a needle to pass thread repeatedly through pieces of fabric in order to join them together.
sew.definition_2: Followed by into: to enclose by sewing.

cure.definition_0: A method, device or medication that restores good health.
cure.definition_1: Act of healing or state of being healed; restoration to health after a disease, or to soundness after injury.

yarn.definition_0: A twisted strand of fiber used for knitting or weaving.
yarn.definition_1: Bundles of fibers twisted together, and which in turn are twisted in bundles to form strands, which in their turn are twisted or plaited to form rope.
yarn.definition_2: A story, a tale, especially one that is incredible.

sing.definition_0: A gathering at which people sing songs.

flip.definition_0: A maneuver which rotates an object end over end.
flip.definition_1: A complete change of direction, decision, movement etc.

squab.definition_0: (sometimes attributive) A baby pigeon, dove, or chicken.
squab.definition_1: The meat of such a baby bird used as food.

yearn.definition_0: To long, have a strong desire (for something).
yearn.definition_1: To long for something in the past with melancholy, nostalgically.
yearn.definition_2: To have strong feelings of love, sympathy, affection, etc. (toward someone).

abash.definition_0: To make ashamed; to embarrass; to destroy the self-possession of, as by exciting suddenly a consciousness of guilt, mistake, or inferiority; to disconcert; to discomfit.
abash.definition_1: To lose self-possession; to become ashamed.

simp.definition_0: A simple person lacking common sense; a fool or simpleton.

lusty.definition_0: Exhibiting lust (in the obsolete sense meaning "vigor"); strong, healthy, robust; vigorous; full of sap or vitality.
lusty.definition_1: Hearty, merry, gleesome, enthusiastic, lively, stirring.
lusty.definition_2: Given to experiencing lust; enjoying physical sensations; lustful.

queer.definition_0: (sometimes derogatory) A person who is or appears homosexual, or who has homosexual qualities.
queer.definition_1: (sometimes derogatory) A person of any non-heterosexual sexuality or sexual identity.
queer.definition_2: (sometimes derogatory) A person of any genderqueer identity.

heave.definition_0: An effort to raise something, such as a weight or one's own body, or to move something heavy.
heave.definition_1: An upward motion; a rising; a swell or distention, as of the breast in difficult breathing, of the waves, of the earth in an earthquake, etc.
heave.definition_2: A horizontal dislocation in a metallic lode, taking place at an intersection with another lode.

tango.definition_0: A Standard ballroom dance in 4/4 time; or a social dance, the Argentine tango.
tango.definition_1: A piece of music suited to such a dance.
tango.definition_2: The letter T in the ICAO spelling alphabet.

flair.definition_0: A natural or innate talent or aptitude.

sail.definition_0: A piece of fabric attached to a boat and arranged such that it causes the wind to drive the boat along. The sail may be attached to the boat via a combination of mast, spars and ropes.
sail.definition_1: (nautical,uncountable) The concept of a sail or sails, as if a substance.
sail.definition_2: The power harnessed by a sail or sails, or the use of this power for travel or transport.

boat.definition_0: A craft used for transportation of goods, fishing, racing, recreational cruising, or military use on or in the water, propelled by oars or outboard motor or inboard motor or by wind.
boat.definition_2: A vehicle, utensil, or dish somewhat resembling a boat in shape.

groom.definition_0: A man who is about to marry.

lime.definition_0: Any inorganic material containing calcium, usually calcium oxide (quicklime) or calcium hydroxide (slaked lime).
lime.definition_1: Any gluey or adhesive substance; something which traps or captures someone; sometimes a synonym for birdlime.

perk.definition_1: A bonus ability that a player character can acquire; a permanent power-up.

gripe.definition_0: A complaint, often a petty or trivial one.
gripe.definition_1: A wire rope, often used on davits and other life raft launching systems.

idol.definition_0: A graven image or representation of anything that is revered, or believed to convey spiritual power.
idol.definition_1: A cultural icon, or especially popular person.
idol.definition_2: (originally Japan) Popular entertainer; usually young, captivating, attractive; and often female, with an image of being close to fans.

sty.definition_0: A pen or enclosure for swine.
sty.definition_1: A messy, dirty or debauched place.

swarm.definition_0: A large number of insects, especially when in motion or (for bees) migrating to a new colony.
swarm.definition_1: A mass of people, animals or things in motion or turmoil.
swarm.definition_2: A group of nodes sharing the same torrent in a BitTorrent network.

doyen.definition_0: A commander in charge of ten men.
doyen.definition_1: The senior, or eldest male member of a group.
doyen.definition_2: A leading light, or exemplar of a particular practice or movement.

decoy.definition_0: A person or object meant to lure somebody into danger.
decoy.definition_1: A real or fake animal used by hunters to lure game.

fusty.definition_2: (by extension) Old-fashioned, refusing to change or update.

dregs.definition_0: (collectively) The sediment settled at the bottom of a liquid; the lees in a container of unfiltered wine.
dregs.definition_1: (the dregs) The worst and lowest part of something.

town.definition_0: A settlement; an area with residential districts, shops and amenities, and its own local government; especially one larger than a village and smaller than a city.
town.definition_1: Any more urbanized center than the place of reference.
town.definition_2: A rural settlement in which a market was held at least once a week.

small.definition_0: Any part of something that is smaller or slimmer than the rest, now usually with anatomical reference to the back.

folly.definition_1: Thoughtless action resulting in tragic consequence.
folly.definition_2: A fanciful building built for purely ornamental reasons.

sine.definition_0: In a right triangle, the ratio of the length of the side opposite an angle to the length of the hypotenuse.

dowry.definition_0: Payment, such as property or money, paid by the bride's family to the groom or his family at the time of marriage.
dowry.definition_1: Payment by the groom or his family to the bride's family: bride price.

flume.definition_0: A ravine or gorge, usually one with water running through.
flume.definition_1: An open channel or trough used to direct or divert liquids.

hawk.definition_0: A diurnal predatory bird of the family Accipitridae, smaller than an eagle.
hawk.definition_1: Any diurnal predatory terrestrial bird of similar size and appearance to the accipitrid hawks, such as a falcon
hawk.definition_2: An advocate of aggressive political positions and actions.

gait.definition_0: Manner of walking or stepping; bearing or carriage while moving.
gait.definition_1: One of the different ways in which a horse can move, either naturally or as a result of training.

usurp.definition_0: To seize power from another, usually by illegitimate means.
usurp.definition_1: To use and assume the coat of arms of another person.
usurp.definition_2: To take the place rightfully belonging to someone or something else.

revet.definition_0: To face (an embankment, etc.) with masonry, wood, or other material.

soggy.definition_0: Soaked with moisture or other liquid.

bide.definition_0: To bear; to endure; to tolerate.
bide.definition_1: To dwell or reside in a location; to abide.
bide.definition_2: To wait; to be in expectation; to stay; to remain.

hemp.definition_0: A tall annual herb, Cannabis sativa, native to Asia.
hemp.definition_1: Various products of this plant, including fibres and the drug cannabis.

skirl.definition_0: A shrill sound, as of bagpipes.

smell.definition_0: A sensation, pleasant or unpleasant, detected by inhaling air (or, the case of water-breathing animals, water) carrying airborne molecules of a substance.
smell.definition_2: A conclusion or intuition that a situation is wrong, more complex than it seems, or otherwise inappropriate.

eagle.definition_0: Any of several large carnivorous and carrion-eating birds in the family Accipitridae, having a powerful hooked bill and keen vision.
eagle.definition_1: A gold coin with a face value of ten dollars, formerly used in the United States.
eagle.definition_2: A 13th-century coin minted in Europe and circulated in England as a debased sterling silver penny, outlawed under Edward I.

stale.definition_0: Something stale; a loaf of bread or the like that is no longer fresh.

flaky.definition_0: Consisting of flakes or of small, loose masses; lying, or cleaving off, in flakes or layers; flakelike.
flaky.definition_1: (of a person) Unreliable; likely to make plans with others but then abandon those plans.
flaky.definition_2: (of a thing) Unreliable; working only on an intermittent basis; likely to malfunction.

noel.definition_1: A kind of hymn, or canticle, of mediaeval origin, sung in honor of the birth of Christ; a Christmas carol.

leery.definition_0: Cautious, suspicious, wary, hesitant, or nervous about something; having reservations or concerns.

ditty.definition_1: A saying or utterance, especially one that is short and frequently repeated.

shove.definition_2: A forward movement of packed river-ice.

llama.definition_0: A South American mammal of the camel family, Lama glama, used as a domestic beast of burden and a source of wool and meat.

bulky.definition_0: Being large in size, mass, or volume.
bulky.definition_2: Having excess body mass, especially muscle.

vixen.definition_1: A malicious, quarrelsome or temperamental woman.

racy.definition_1: Having a strong flavor indicating origin; of distinct characteristic taste; tasting of the soil.
racy.definition_2: (by extension) Exciting to the mind by a strong or distinctive character of thought or language; peculiar and piquant; fresh and lively.

hook.definition_0: A rod bent into a curved shape, typically with one end free and the other end secured to a rope or other attachment.
hook.definition_1: A barbed metal hook used for fishing; a fishhook.
hook.definition_2: Any of various hook-shaped agricultural implements such as a billhook.

teeth.definition_0: The ability to be enforced, or to be enforced to any useful effect.

bite.definition_1: The wound left behind after having been bitten.
bite.definition_2: The swelling of one's skin caused by an insect's mouthparts or sting.

rapid.definition_0: (often in the plural) a rough section of a river or stream which is difficult to navigate due to the swift and turbulent motion of the water.

curve.definition_0: A gentle bend, such as in a road.
curve.definition_1: A simple figure containing no straight portions and no angles; a curved line.
curve.definition_2: A grading system based on the scale of performance of a group used to normalize a right-skewed grade distribution (with more lower scores) into a bell curve, so that more can receive higher grades, regardless of their actual knowledge of the subject.

gaff.definition_0: A tool consisting of a large metal hook with a handle or pole, especially the one used to pull large fish aboard a boat.
gaff.definition_1: A minor error or faux pas, a gaffe.

team.definition_0: A set of draught animals, such as two horses in front of a carriage.
team.definition_1: Any group of people involved in the same activity, especially sports or work.
team.definition_2: A group of animals moving together, especially young ducks.

roan.definition_0: An animal such as a horse that has a coat of a dark base color with individual white hairs mixed in.
roan.definition_1: The color of such an animal.
roan.definition_2: A kind of leather used for slippers, bookbinding, etc., made from sheepskin, tanned with sumac and colored to imitate ungrained morocco.

wink.definition_0: An act of winking (a blinking of only one eye), or a message sent by winking.
wink.definition_1: A brief period of sleep; especially forty winks.

heir.definition_0: Someone who inherits, or is designated to inherit, the property of another.
heir.definition_1: One who inherits, or has been designated to inherit, a hereditary title or office.
heir.definition_2: A successor in a role, representing continuity with the predecessor.

pour.definition_2: A downpour, or flood of precipitation.

swish.definition_0: A short rustling, hissing or whistling sound, often made by friction.
swish.definition_1: A hissing, sweeping movement through the air, as of an animal's tail.
swish.definition_2: A sound of liquid flowing inside a container.

axiom.definition_0: A seemingly self-evident or necessary truth which is based on assumption; a principle or proposition which cannot actually be proved or disproved.
axiom.definition_1: (proof theory) A fundamental assumption that serves as a basis for deduction of theorems; a postulate (sometimes distinguished from postulates as being universally applicable, whereas postulates are particular to a certain science or context).
axiom.definition_2: An established principle in some artistic practice or science that is universally received.

rune.definition_0: A letter, or character, belonging to the written language of various ancient Germanic peoples, especially the Scandinavians and the Anglo-Saxons.
rune.definition_1: A Finnish or Scandinavian epic poem, or a division of one, especially a division of the Kalevala.
rune.definition_2: A letter or mark used as mystical or magic symbol.

may.definition_0: To be strong; to have power (over).

leave.definition_0: To have a consequence or remnant.

chief.definition_0: A leader or head of a group of people, organisation, etc.
chief.definition_1: The top part of a shield or escutcheon; more specifically, an ordinary consisting of the upper part of the field cut off by a horizontal line, generally occupying the top third.
chief.definition_2: The principal part or top of anything.

other.definition_0: An other, another (person, etc), more often rendered as another.
other.definition_1: The other one; the second of two.

lave.definition_0: To pour or throw out, as water; lade out; bail; bail out.
lave.definition_1: To draw, as water; drink in.

roost.definition_0: The place where a bird sleeps (usually its nest or a branch).
roost.definition_1: A group of birds roosting together.

shill.definition_0: A person paid to endorse a product favourably, while pretending to be impartial.
shill.definition_1: An accomplice at a confidence trick during an auction or gambling game.
shill.definition_2: A house player in a casino.

smite.definition_1: To strike down or kill with godly force.

equal.definition_0: A person or thing of equal status to others.

wreak.definition_0: To cause something harmful; to afflict; to inflict; to harm or injury; to let out something harmful; .
wreak.definition_1: To chasten, or chastise/chastize, or castigate, or punish, or smite.
wreak.definition_2: To inflict or take vengeance on.

size.definition_1: A regulation determining the amount of money paid in fees, taxes etc.
size.definition_2: A fixed standard for the magnitude, quality, quantity etc. of goods, especially food and drink.

monk.definition_0: A male member of a monastic order who has devoted his life for religious service.
monk.definition_1: In earlier usage, an eremite or hermit devoted to solitude, as opposed to a cenobite, who lived communally.
monk.definition_2: A male who leads an isolated life; a loner, a hermit.

horse.definition_0: Any of several animals related to Equus ferus caballus.

owlet.definition_0: Any of various birds of prey of the order Strigiformes that are primarily nocturnal and have forward-looking, binocular vision, limited eye movement, and good hearing.
owlet.definition_1: (by extension) A person seen as having owl-like characteristics, especially appearing wise or serious, or being nocturnally active.

rank.definition_0: Strong of its kind or in character; unmitigated; virulent; thorough; utter (used of negative things).
rank.definition_1: Strong in growth; growing with vigour or rapidity, hence, coarse or gross.
rank.definition_2: Suffering from overgrowth or hypertrophy; plethoric.

sign.definition_0: (sometimes also used uncountably) A visible indication.
sign.definition_1: Physical evidence left by an animal.
sign.definition_2: A clearly visible object, generally flat, bearing a short message in words or pictures.

bride.definition_0: A woman in the context of her own wedding; one who is going to marry or has just been married.

fell.definition_1: The stitching down of a fold of cloth; specifically, the portion of a kilt, from the waist to the seat, where the pleats are stitched down.
fell.definition_2: The end of a web, formed by the last thread of the weft.

yaw.definition_0: The rotation of an aircraft, ship, or missile about its vertical axis so as to cause the longitudinal axis of the aircraft, ship, or missile to deviate from the flight line or heading in its horizontal plane.
yaw.definition_1: The angle between the longitudinal axis of a projectile at any moment and the tangent to the trajectory in the corresponding point of flight of the projectile.
yaw.definition_2: A vessel's motion rotating about the vertical axis, so the bow yaws from side to side; a characteristic of unsteadiness.

fawn.definition_1: A pale brown colour tinted with yellow, like that of a fawn.
fawn.definition_2: The young of an animal; a whelp.

flue.definition_0: A pipe or duct that carries gaseous combustion products away from the point of combustion (such as a furnace).
flue.definition_1: An enclosed passageway in which to direct air or other gaseous current along.
flue.definition_2: A woolly or downy substance; down, nap; a piece of this.

scum.definition_0: A layer of impurities that accumulates at the surface of a liquid (especially molten metal or water).
scum.definition_1: A greenish water vegetation (such as algae), usually found floating on the surface of ponds
scum.definition_2: The topmost liquid layer of a cesspool or septic tank.

sword.definition_0: A long-bladed weapon with a hilt, and usually a pommel and cross-guard, which is designed to stab, slash, and/or hack.
sword.definition_1: A suit in the minor arcana in tarot.

blade.definition_0: The sharp cutting edge of a knife, chisel, or other tool, a razor blade/sword.
blade.definition_1: The flat functional end of a propeller, oar, hockey stick, screwdriver, skate, etc.
blade.definition_2: The narrow leaf of a grass or cereal.

bleep.definition_0: A brief high-pitched sound, as from some electronic device.
bleep.definition_1: Something named by an explicit noun in the original, unedited version of the containing sentence.
bleep.definition_2: A broad genre of electronic music with goth and industrial influences, as opposed to traditional gothic rock.

sweep.definition_1: The person who steers a dragon boat.
sweep.definition_2: A person who stands at the stern of a surf boat, steering with a steering oar and commanding the crew.

swipe.definition_0: A quick grab, bat, or other motion with the hand or paw; a sweep.
swipe.definition_1: A strong blow given with a sweeping motion, as with a bat or club.
swipe.definition_2: An act of interacting with a touch screen by drawing the finger rapidly across it.

prawn.definition_0: A crustacean of the suborder Dendrobranchiata.
prawn.definition_1: A crustacean sometimes confused with shrimp.
prawn.definition_2: A woman with a very toned body, but an unattractive face.

quoin.definition_0: Any of the corner building blocks of a building, usually larger or more ornate than the surrounding blocks.
quoin.definition_2: A metal wedge which fits into the space between the type and the edge of a chase, and is tightened to fix the metal type in place.

hump.definition_1: A deformity in humans caused by abnormal curvature of the upper spine.
hump.definition_2: (animals) A rounded fleshy mass, such as on a camel or zebu.

wince.definition_0: A sudden movement or gesture of shrinking away.
wince.definition_1: A reel used in dyeing, steeping, or washing cloth; a winch. It is placed over the division wall between two wince pits so as to allow the cloth to descend into either compartment at will.

roast.definition_0: A cut of meat suited to roasting
roast.definition_1: A meal consisting of roast foods.
roast.definition_2: The degree to which something, especially coffee, is roasted.

slew.definition_0: The act, or process of slewing.

lease.definition_1: (chiefly dialectal) To pick, select, pick out; to pick up.

clump.definition_0: A cluster or lump; an unshaped piece or mass.
clump.definition_1: A thick group or bunch, especially of bushes or hair.

fuzzy.definition_0: (often in the plural) A very small piece of plush material.
fuzzy.definition_1: Something covered with fuzz or hair, as an animal or plush toy.
fuzzy.definition_2: A person, especially a college student, interested in humanities or social sciences, as opposed to one interested in mathematics, science, or engineering.

spike.definition_0: In a violin-family instrument, the carved wooden plug which sits in the bottom block of the instrument.

hill.definition_0: An elevated location smaller than a mountain.
hill.definition_2: A heap of earth surrounding a plant.

snake.definition_0: A legless reptile of the sub-order Serpentes with a long, thin body and a fork-shaped tongue.
snake.definition_2: Somebody who acts deceitfully for social gain.

fetch.definition_0: An act of fetching, of bringing something from a distance.
fetch.definition_1: The object of fetching; the source of an attraction; a force, propensity, or quality which attracts.
fetch.definition_2: A stratagem or trick; an artifice.

beef.definition_0: The meat from a cow, bull or other bovine.
beef.definition_1: (plural: beefs) A grudge; dislike (of something or someone); lack of faith or trust (in something or someone); a reason for a dislike or grudge. (often + with)

knell.definition_0: The sound of a bell knelling; a toll (particularly one signalling a death).
knell.definition_1: A sign of the end or demise of something or someone.

truck.definition_0: A small wheel or roller, specifically the wheel of a gun carriage.
truck.definition_1: The ball on top of a flagpole.
truck.definition_2: On a wooden mast, a circular disc (or sometimes a rectangle) of wood near or at the top of the mast, usually with holes or sheaves to reeve signal halyards; also a temporary or emergency place for a lookout. "Main" refers to the mainmast, whereas a truck on another mast may be called (on the mizzenmast, for example) "mizzen-truck".

quack.definition_0: The sound made by a duck.

thump.definition_0: A blow that produces a muffled sound.
thump.definition_1: The sound of such a blow; a thud.
thump.definition_2: Used to replace the vulgar or blasphemous element in "what the hell" and similar phrases.

jolly.definition_1: A marine in the English navy.

penny.definition_0: In the United Kingdom and Ireland, a copper coin worth 1/240 of a pound sterling or Irish pound before decimalisation. Abbreviation: d.
penny.definition_1: In the United Kingdom, a copper coin worth 1/100 of a pound sterling. Abbreviation: p.
penny.definition_2: In Ireland, a coin worth 1/100 of an Irish pound before the introduction of the euro. Abbreviation: p.

shunt.definition_0: An act of moving (suddenly), as due to a push or shove.
shunt.definition_1: A connection used as an alternative path between parts of an electrical circuit.
shunt.definition_2: The shifting of the studs on a projectile from the deep to the shallow sides of the grooves in its discharge from a shunt gun.

track.definition_0: A mark left by something that has passed along.
track.definition_1: A mark or impression left by the foot, either of man or animal.
track.definition_2: The entire lower surface of the foot; said of birds, etc.

cower.definition_0: To crouch or cringe, or to avoid or shy away from something, in fear.
cower.definition_2: To cause to cower; to frighten into submission.

sleet.definition_0: Pellets of ice made of mostly frozen raindrops or refrozen melted snowflakes.
sleet.definition_1: A mixture of rain and snow.
sleet.definition_2: A smooth coating of ice formed on ground or other objects by freezing rain.

pitch.definition_0: A sticky, gummy substance secreted by trees; sap.
pitch.definition_1: A dark, extremely viscous material remaining in still after distilling crude oil and tar.

furry.definition_0: An animal character with human-like characteristics; most commonly refers to such characters created by members of the furry subculture.
furry.definition_1: A member of the furry fandom.
furry.definition_2: Someone who roleplays or identifies with a furry character. (Compare therianthrope.)

chair.definition_0: An item of furniture used to sit on or in, comprising a seat, legs, back, and sometimes arm rests, for use by one person. Compare stool, couch, sofa, settee, loveseat and bench.
chair.definition_1: The seating position of a particular musician in an orchestra.
chair.definition_2: An iron block used on railways to support the rails and secure them to the sleepers, and similar devices.

twang.definition_0: The sharp, quick sound of a vibrating tight string, for example, of a bow or a musical instrument.
twang.definition_1: A particular sharp vibrating sound characteristic of electric guitars.
twang.definition_2: A trace of a regional or foreign accent in someone's voice.

fate.definition_0: The presumed cause, force, principle, or divine will that predetermines events.
fate.definition_1: The effect, consequence, outcome, or inevitable events predetermined by this cause.
fate.definition_2: An event or a situation which is inevitable in the fullness of time.

splay.definition_0: A slope or bevel, especially of the sides of a door or window, by which the opening is made larger at one face of the wall than at the other, or larger at each of the faces than it is between them.

craft.definition_2: (obsolete in the general sense) A work or product of art .

snuff.definition_0: Finely ground or pulverized tobacco intended for use by being sniffed or snorted into the nose.
snuff.definition_1: Fine-ground or minced tobacco, dry or moistened, intended for use by placing a pinch behind the lip or beneath the tongue; see also snus.
snuff.definition_2: A snort or sniff of fine-ground, powdered, or pulverized tobacco.

hefty.definition_2: (of a person) Possessing physical strength and weight; rugged and powerful; powerfully or heavily built.

stoop.definition_0: The staircase and landing or porch leading to the entrance of a residence.
stoop.definition_1: The threshold of a doorway, a doorstep.

tardy.definition_0: A piece of paper given to students who are late to class.
tardy.definition_1: An instance of a student being marked as tardy by a teacher in his or her attendance sheet.

droop.definition_0: Something which is limp or sagging
droop.definition_1: A condition or posture of drooping

witch.definition_0: A person who practices witchcraft; a woman or man who practices witchcraft.
witch.definition_2: One who exercises more-than-common power of attraction; a charming or bewitching person.

gleam.definition_0: A small or indistinct shaft or stream of light.
gleam.definition_1: A glimpse or hint; an indistinct sign of something.

slink.definition_1: The young of an animal when born prematurely, especially a calf.
slink.definition_2: The meat of such a prematurely born animal.

bully.definition_0: A person who is intentionally, physically, or emotionally cruel to others; especially to those who are weaker or have less power or privilege.
bully.definition_1: A noisy, blustering fellow, more insolent than courageous; one who is threatening and quarrelsome; an insolent, tyrannical fellow.

zest.definition_0: The outer skin of a citrus fruit, used as a flavouring or garnish.
zest.definition_2: (by extension) Enthusiasm; keen enjoyment; relish; gusto.

harsh.definition_1: To put a damper on (a mood).

shine.definition_0: Brightness from a source of light.
shine.definition_2: Excellence in quality or appearance; splendour.

cover.definition_1: Area or situation which screens a person or thing from view.
cover.definition_2: The front and back of a book, magazine, CD package, etc.

spume.definition_0: Foam or froth of liquid, particularly that of seawater.

swirl.definition_1: A twist or coil of something.
swirl.definition_2: The upward rushing of a fish through the water to take the bait.

glaze.definition_0: The vitreous coating of pottery or porcelain; anything used as a coating or color in glazing. See glaze (transitive verb).
glaze.definition_1: A transparent or semi-transparent layer of paint.
glaze.definition_2: A smooth edible coating applied to food.

tinge.definition_0: A small added amount of colour; (by extension) a small added amount of some other thing.
tinge.definition_1: The degree of vividness of a colour; hue, shade, tint.

light.definition_0: Visible electromagnetic radiation. The human eye can typically detect radiation (light) in the wavelength range of about 400 to 750 nanometers. Nearby shorter and longer wavelength ranges, although not visible, are commonly called ultraviolet and infrared light.
light.definition_2: Spiritual or mental illumination; enlightenment, useful information.

metal.definition_0: (heading) Chemical elements or alloys, and the mines where their ores come from.
metal.definition_1: A light tincture used in a coat of arms, specifically argent and or.
metal.definition_2: Molten glass that is to be blown or moulded to form objects.

forge.definition_0: Furnace or hearth where metals are heated prior to hammering them into shape.
forge.definition_1: Workshop in which metals are shaped by heating and hammering them.
forge.definition_2: The act of beating or working iron or steel.

nudge.definition_1: A feature of instant messaging software used to get the attention of another user, as by shaking the conversation window or playing a sound.
nudge.definition_2: The rotation by one step of a fruit machine reel of the player's choice.

habit.definition_0: An action performed on a regular basis.
habit.definition_1: An action performed repeatedly and automatically, usually without awareness.
habit.definition_2: A long piece of clothing worn by monks and nuns.

dross.definition_1: Residue that forms on the surface of a metal from oxidation.

twill.definition_0: A pattern, characterised by diagonal ridges, created by the regular interlacing of threads of the warp and weft during weaving.
twill.definition_1: A cloth or portion of cloth woven in such a pattern.

tress.definition_0: A braid, knot, or curl, of hair; a ringlet.
tress.definition_2: (by extension) A knot or festoon, as of flowers.

gorse.definition_0: Evergreen shrub, of the genus Ulex, having spiny leaves and yellow flowers.

knurl.definition_1: A crossgrained protuberance; a nodule; a boss or projection.
knurl.definition_2: A lined or crossgrained pattern of ridges or indentations rolled or pressed into a part for grip.

sloop.definition_0: A single-masted sailboat with only one headsail.
sloop.definition_1: A sailing warship, smaller than a frigate, with its guns all on one deck.
sloop.definition_2: A sloop-of-war, smaller than a frigate, larger than a corvette.

krill.definition_0: Any of several small marine crustacean species of plankton in the order Euphausiacea in the class Malacostraca.

burl.definition_0: A tree growth in which the grain has grown in a deformed manner.
burl.definition_1: Wood of a mottled veneer, usually cut from such a growth.
burl.definition_2: A knot or lump in thread or cloth.

ficus.definition_0: A plant belonging to the genus Ficus, including the rubber plant.

bogle.definition_0: A goblin; a frightful spectre or phantom; a bogy or bugbear.

sprit.definition_0: A spar between mast and upper outer corner of a spritsail on sailing boats.

druse.definition_0: An inner surface with a crust of tiny crystals.
druse.definition_1: An aggregation of calcium oxalate crystals found in certain plants.
druse.definition_2: A tiny yellow or white accumulation of extracellular material that builds up in Bruch's membrane of the eye.

serac.definition_0: Often sérac: a hard, cone-shaped, pale green, strongly flavoured cheese from Switzerland made from skimmed cowmilk and blue fenugreek (Trigonella caerulea); Schabziger, Sapsago. It is usually eaten grated, mixed with butter, or in a fondue.
serac.definition_1: (glaciology) A sharp tower of ice formed by intersecting crevasses of a glacier.

tint.definition_1: A pale or faint tinge of any color; especially, a variation of a color obtained by adding white (contrast shade)
tint.definition_2: A color considered with reference to other very similar colors.

value.definition_0: The quality (positive or negative) that renders something desirable or valuable.
value.definition_1: The degree of importance given to something.
value.definition_2: That which is valued or highly esteemed, such as one's morals, morality, or belief system.

shape.definition_0: The status or condition of something
shape.definition_1: Condition of personal health, especially muscular health.
shape.definition_2: The appearance of something in terms of its arrangement in space, especially its outline; often a basic geometric two-dimensional figure.

slump.definition_0: A heavy or helpless collapse; a slouching or drooping posture; a period of poor activity or performance, especially an extended period.
slump.definition_1: A measure of the fluidity of freshly mixed concrete, based on how much the concrete formed in a standard slump cone sags when the cone is removed.

pride.definition_0: The quality or state of being proud; an unreasonable overestimation of one's own superiority in terms of talents, looks, wealth, importance etc., which manifests itself in lofty airs, distance, reserve and often contempt of others.
pride.definition_1: (often with of or in) A sense of one's own worth, and abhorrence of what is beneath or unworthy of one; lofty self-respect; noble self-esteem; elevation of character; dignified bearing; proud delight; -- in a good sense.
pride.definition_2: Proud or disdainful behavior or treatment; insolence or arrogance of demeanor; haughty bearing and conduct; insolent exultation; disdain; hubris.

pique.definition_0: A feeling of enmity; ill-feeling, animosity; a transient feeling of wounded pride.
pique.definition_1: A feeling of irritation or resentment, awakened by a social slight or injury; offence, especially taken in an emotional sense with little thought or consideration.

quirk.definition_0: An idiosyncrasy; a slight glitch, mannerism; something unusual about the manner or style of something or someone
quirk.definition_1: An acute angle dividing a molding; a groove that runs lengthwise between the upper part of a moulding and a soffit

sward.definition_0: A layer of earth into which grass has grown; turf; sod.
sward.definition_1: An expanse of land covered in grass; a lawn or meadow.

blaze.definition_0: A fire, especially a fast-burning fire producing a lot of flames and light.
blaze.definition_1: Intense, direct light accompanied with heat.
blaze.definition_2: The white or lighter-coloured markings on a horse's face.

price.definition_0: The cost required to gain possession of something.
price.definition_1: The cost of an action or deed.

fire.definition_0: A (usually self-sustaining) chemical reaction involving the bonding of oxygen with carbon or other fuel, with the production of heat and the presence of flame or smouldering.
fire.definition_1: An instance of this chemical reaction, especially when intentionally created and maintained in a specific location to a useful end (such as a campfire or a hearth fire).
fire.definition_2: The occurrence, often accidental, of fire in a certain place, causing damage and danger.

cloth.definition_0: A woven fabric such as used in dressing, decorating, cleaning or other practical use.
cloth.definition_1: Specifically, a tablecloth, especially as spread before a meal or removed afterwards.
cloth.definition_2: A piece of cloth used for a particular purpose.

giant.definition_0: A mythical human of very great size.
giant.definition_1: Specifically, any of the gigantes, the race of giants in the Greek mythology.
giant.definition_2: A very tall and large person.

power.definition_0: Ability to do or undergo something.
power.definition_1: (social) Ability to coerce, influence or control.

smirk.definition_0: An uneven, often crooked smile that is insolent, self-satisfied or scornful
smirk.definition_1: A forced or affected smile; a simper

cube.definition_0: A regular polyhedron having six identical square faces.
cube.definition_1: Any object more or less in the form of a cube.
cube.definition_2: The third power of a number, value, term or expression.

surf.definition_0: Waves that break on an ocean shoreline.
surf.definition_1: An instance or session of riding a surfboard in the surf.

fuzz.definition_0: A frizzy mass of hair or fibre.
fuzz.definition_1: Quality of an image that is unclear; a blurred image.
fuzz.definition_2: The random data used in fuzz testing.

fizz.definition_0: An emission of a rapid stream of bubbles.
fizz.definition_1: The sound of such an emission.

patch.definition_0: A piece of cloth, or other suitable material, sewed or otherwise fixed upon a garment to repair or strengthen it, especially upon an old garment to cover a hole.
patch.definition_1: A small piece of anything used to repair damage or a breach; as, a patch on a kettle, a roof, etc.
patch.definition_2: A piece of any size, used to repair something for a temporary period only, or that it is temporary because it is not meant to last long or will be removed as soon as a proper repair can be made, which will happen in the near future.

heavy.definition_0: A villain or bad guy; the one responsible for evil or aggressive acts.
heavy.definition_2: A large multi-engined aircraft. (The term heavy normally follows the call-sign when used by air traffic controllers.)

cream.definition_0: The butterfat/milkfat part of milk which rises to the top; this part when separated from the remainder.
cream.definition_1: A yellowish white colour; the colour of cream.
cream.definition_2: Frosting, custard, creamer or another substance similar to the oily part of milk or to whipped cream.

depth.definition_0: The vertical distance below a surface; the degree to which something is deep
depth.definition_1: The distance between the front and the back, as the depth of a drawer or closet
depth.definition_2: The intensity, complexity, strength, seriousness or importance of an emotion, situation, etc.

sniff.definition_1: A quantity of something that is inhaled through the nose
sniff.definition_2: A brief perception, or tiny amount.

plumb.definition_0: A little mass of lead, or the like, attached to a line, and used by builders, etc., to indicate a vertical direction.
plumb.definition_1: A weight on the end of a long line, used by sailors to determine the depth of water.

slake.definition_1: To cool (something) with water or another liquid.
slake.definition_2: To become mixed with water, so that a true chemical combination takes place.

snare.definition_0: A trap (especially one made from a loop of wire, string, or leather).
snare.definition_2: A loop of cord used in obstetric cases, to hold or to pull a fetus from the mother animal.

spray.definition_0: A fine, gentle, dispersed mist of liquid.
spray.definition_2: Any of numerous commercial products, including paints, cosmetics, and insecticides, that are dispensed from containers in this manner.

leech.definition_0: An aquatic blood-sucking annelid of class Hirudinea, especially Hirudo medicinalis.
leech.definition_1: A person who derives profit from others in a parasitic fashion.
leech.definition_2: A glass tube designed for drawing blood from damaged tissue by means of a vacuum.

wispy.definition_0: Consisting of or resembling a wisp; like a slender, flexible strand or bundle.

lanky.definition_0: Tall, slim, and rather ungraceful or awkward.

quaff.definition_0: The act of quaffing; a deep draught.

stoup.definition_2: A receptacle for holy water, especially a basin set at the entrance of a church.

smalt.definition_0: A deep blue pigment made from powdered glass mixed with cobalt oxide
