mauve.definition_1: The colour of this dye; a pale purple or violet colour.

spoor.definition_0: The track, trail, droppings or scent of an animal

dint.definition_0: A blow, stroke, especially dealt in a fight.
dint.definition_1: Force, power; especially in by dint of.
dint.definition_2: The mark left by a blow; an indentation or impression made by violence; a dent.

kugel.definition_0: A traditional Jewish dish consisting of baked pudding of rice, pasta, or potatoes with vegetables or raisins and spices
kugel.definition_1: Traditional house ornament made of glass
kugel.definition_2: Overly materialistic and selfish young Jewish woman

fluky.definition_1: Unstable, prone to rapid and unpredictable changes

droll.definition_0: A funny person; a buffoon, a wag.

smile.definition_0: A facial expression comprised by flexing the muscles of both ends of one's mouth, often showing the front teeth, without vocalisation, and in humans is a common involuntary or voluntary expression of happiness, pleasure, amusement or anxiety.
smile.definition_2: A drink bought by one person for another.

swift.definition_0: A small plain-colored bird of the family Apodidae that resembles a swallow and is noted for its rapid flight.
swift.definition_1: Any of certain lizards of the genus Sceloporus.
swift.definition_2: A moth of the family Hepialidae, swift moth, ghost moth.

raid.definition_0: A quick hostile or predatory incursion or invasion in a battle.
raid.definition_1: An attack or invasion for the purpose of making arrests, seizing property, or plundering

creep.definition_0: To move slowly with the abdomen close to the ground.
creep.definition_1: Of plants, to grow across a surface rather than upwards.
creep.definition_2: To move slowly and quietly in a particular direction.

spurt.definition_0: A brief gush, as of liquid spurting from an orifice or a cut/wound.

raven.definition_0: Any of several, generally large and lustrous black species of birds in the genus Corvus, especially the common raven, Corvus corax.

slush.definition_2: Flavored shaved ice served as a drink.

tower.definition_0: A very tall iron-framed structure, usually painted red and white, on which microwave, radio, satellite, or other communication antennas are installed; mast.
tower.definition_1: A similarly framed structure with a platform or enclosed area on top, used as a lookout for spotting fires, plane crashes, fugitives, etc.

cloak.definition_0: A long outer garment worn over the shoulders covering the back; a cape, often with a hood.
cloak.definition_2: That which conceals; a disguise or pretext.

spire.definition_0: The stalk or stem of a plant.
spire.definition_1: A young shoot of a plant; a spear.
spire.definition_2: Any of various tall grasses, rushes, or sedges, such as the marram, the reed canary-grass, etc.

spank.definition_0: An instance of spanking, separately or part of a multiple blows-beating; a smack, swat, or slap.
spank.definition_1: A slapping sound, as produced by spanking.

clink.definition_0: The sound of metal on metal, or glass on glass.

steep.definition_0: The steep side of a mountain etc.; a slope or acclivity.

lager.definition_0: A type of beer, brewed using a bottom-fermenting yeast.

quire.definition_0: One-twentieth of a ream of paper; a collection of twenty-four or twenty-five sheets of paper of the same size and quality, unfolded or having a single fold.
quire.definition_1: A set of leaves which are stitched together, originally a set of four pieces of paper (eight leaves, sixteen pages). This is most often a single signature (i.e. group of four), but may be several nested signatures.

quark.definition_0: In the Standard Model, an elementary subatomic particle that forms matter. They combine to form hadrons, such as protons and neutrons.
quark.definition_1: (X Window System) An integer that uniquely identifies a text string.

lock.definition_0: Something used for fastening, which can only be opened with a key or combination.
lock.definition_1: (by extension) A mutex or other token restricting access to a resource.
lock.definition_2: A segment of a canal or other waterway enclosed by gates, used for raising and lowering boats between levels.

scud.definition_1: Clouds or rain driven by the wind.
scud.definition_2: A loose formation of small ragged cloud fragments (or fog) not attached to a larger higher cloud layer.

rift.definition_1: A break in the clouds, fog, mist etc., which allows light through.
rift.definition_2: A shallow place in a stream; a ford.

pith.definition_0: The soft, spongy substance in the center of the stems of many plants and trees.
pith.definition_1: The spongy interior substance of a feather or horn.

snipe.definition_0: Any of various limicoline game birds of the genera Gallinago, Lymnocryptes and Coenocorypha in the family Scolopacidae, having a long, slender, nearly straight beak.
snipe.definition_2: A shot fired from a concealed place.

skimp.definition_0: To mock, deride, scorn, scold, make fun of.

waste.definition_0: Excess of material, useless by-products or damaged, unsaleable products; garbage; rubbish.
waste.definition_2: A waste land; an uninhabited desolate region; a wilderness or desert.

skulk.definition_1: A group of people seen as being fox-like (e.g. cunning, dishonest, or having nefarious plans).

code.definition_0: A short symbol, often with little relation to the item it represents.
code.definition_1: A body of law, sanctioned by legislation, in which the rules of law to be specifically applied by the courts are set forth in systematic form; a compilation of laws by public authority; a digest.
code.definition_2: Any system of principles, rules or regulations relating to one subject.

knack.definition_0: A readiness in performance; aptness at doing something.
knack.definition_2: Something performed, or to be done, requiring aptness and dexterity.

scrub.definition_0: One who labors hard and lives meanly; a mean fellow.
scrub.definition_1: One who is incompetent or unable to complete easy tasks.
scrub.definition_2: A thicket or jungle, often specified by the name of the prevailing plant

genus.definition_0: A rank in the classification of organisms, below family and above species; a taxon at that rank.
genus.definition_2: A natural number representing any of several related measures of the complexity of a given manifold or graph.

strop.definition_0: A strap; more specifically a piece of leather or a substitute (notably canvas), or strip of wood covered with a suitable material, for honing a razor, in this sense also called razor strop.
strop.definition_1: A bad mood or temper (see stroppy.)
strop.definition_2: A piece of rope spliced into a circular wreath, and put round a block for hanging it.

urge.definition_0: A strong desire; an itch to do something.

mince.definition_1: Finely chopped mixed fruit used in Christmas pies; mincemeat.
mince.definition_2: An affected (often dainty or short and precise) gait.

decay.definition_0: The process or result of being gradually decomposed.
decay.definition_1: A deterioration of condition; loss of status or fortune.

feint.definition_0: A movement made to confuse the opponent; a dummy.
feint.definition_1: That which is feigned; an assumed or false appearance; a pretense or stratagem.
feint.definition_2: (war) An offensive movement resembling an attack in all but its continuance

sloth.definition_0: Laziness; slowness in the mindset; disinclination to action or labour.
sloth.definition_1: A herbivorous, arboreal South American mammal of the families Megalonychidae and Bradypodidae, noted for its slowness and inactivity.
sloth.definition_2: A collective term for a group of bears.

mint.definition_0: A building or institution where money (originally, only coins) is produced under government licence.
mint.definition_1: A large amount of money. A vast sum or amount, etc.
mint.definition_2: Any place regarded as a source of unlimited supply; the supply itself.

flail.definition_0: A tool used for threshing, consisting of a long handle with a shorter stick attached with a short piece of chain, thong or similar material.
flail.definition_1: A weapon which has the (usually spherical) striking part attached to the handle with a flexible joint such as a chain.

house.definition_0: A structure built or serving as an abode of human beings.
house.definition_1: The people who live in a house; a household.
house.definition_2: A building used for something other than a residence (typically with qualifying word).

staff.definition_0: (plural staffs or staves) A long, straight, thick wooden rod or stick, especially one used to assist in walking.
staff.definition_1: (plural staves) A series of horizontal lines on which musical notes are written; a stave.
staff.definition_2: (plural staff or staffs) The employees of a business.

mast.definition_0: A tall, slim post or tower, usually tapering upward, used to support, for example, the sails on a ship, flags, floodlights, meteorological instruments ,or communications equipment such as an aerial, usually supported by guy-wires.
mast.definition_1: A non-judicial punishment ("NJP") disciplinary hearing under which a commanding officer studies and disposes of cases involving those under his command.

abode.definition_0: To endure without yielding; to withstand; await defiantly; to encounter; to persevere.
abode.definition_1: To bear patiently; to tolerate; to put up with; stand.
abode.definition_2: To pay for; to stand the consequences of; to answer for; to suffer for; to atone for.

truth.definition_0: True facts, genuine depiction or statements of reality.
truth.definition_1: Conformity to fact or reality; correctness, accuracy.
truth.definition_2: The state or quality of being true to someone or something.

round.definition_0: So as to form a circle or trace a circular path, or approximation thereof.
round.definition_1: So as to surround or be near.

nomad.definition_0: A member of a society or class who herd animals from pasture to pasture with no fixed home.
nomad.definition_1: A person who changes residence frequently.
nomad.definition_2: A player who changes teams frequently.

swell.definition_0: To become bigger, especially due to being engorged.
swell.definition_2: To grow gradually in force or loudness.

juice.definition_0: A liquid from a plant, especially fruit.

sight.definition_0: (in the singular) The ability to see.
sight.definition_1: The act of seeing; perception of objects by the eye; view.

yield.definition_0: To pay, give in payment; repay, recompense; reward; requite.
yield.definition_1: To furnish; to afford; to render; to give forth.
yield.definition_2: To give way; to allow another to pass first.

sling.definition_0: An instrument for throwing stones or other missiles, consisting of a short strap with two strings fastened to its ends, or with a string fastened to one end and a light stick to the other.
sling.definition_1: A kind of hanging bandage put around the neck, in which a wounded arm or hand is supported.
sling.definition_2: A loop of cloth, worn around the neck, for supporting a baby or other such load.

fight.definition_0: To contend in physical conflict, either singly or in war, battle etc.
fight.definition_1: To contend in physical conflict with each other, either singly or in war, battle etc.
fight.definition_2: To strive for something; to campaign or contend for success.

plush.definition_0: A textile fabric with a nap or shag on one side, longer and softer than the nap of velvet.

clean.definition_1: The first part of the event clean and jerk in which the weight is brought from the ground to the shoulders.

voice.definition_0: Sound uttered by the mouth, especially by human beings in speech or song; sound thus uttered considered as possessing some special quality or character
voice.definition_1: Sound made through vibration of the vocal cords; sonant, or intonated, utterance; tone; — distinguished from mere breath sound as heard in whispering and voiceless consonants.
voice.definition_2: The tone or sound emitted by an object

bread.definition_0: A foodstuff made by baking dough made from cereals.

milk.definition_0: A white liquid produced by the mammary glands of female mammals to nourish their young. From certain animals, especially cows, it is also called dairy milk and is a common food for humans as a beverage or used to produce various dairy products such as butter, cheese, and yogurt.
milk.definition_1: A white (or whitish) liquid obtained from a vegetable source such as almonds, coconuts, oats, rice, and/or soy beans. Also called non-dairy milk.

flute.definition_0: A woodwind instrument consisting of a tube with a row of holes that produce sound through vibrations caused by air blown across the edge of the holes, often tuned by plugging one or more holes with a finger; the Western concert flute, a transverse side-blown flute of European origin.
flute.definition_1: A recorder, also a woodwind instrument.
flute.definition_2: A glass with a long, narrow bowl and a long stem, used for drinking wine, especially champagne.

fox.definition_0: A red fox, small carnivore (Vulpes vulpes), related to dogs and wolves, with red or silver fur and a bushy tail.
fox.definition_1: Any of numerous species of small wild canids resembling the red fox. In the taxonomy they form the tribe Vulpini within the family Canidae, consisting of nine genera (see the Wikipedia article on the fox).

grits.definition_0: (usually in the plural) Husked but unground oats.
grits.definition_1: (usually in the plural) Coarsely ground corn or hominy used as porridge.

angry.definition_1: (said about a wound or a rash) Inflamed and painful.
angry.definition_2: (said about the elements, like the sky or the sea) Dark and stormy, menacing.

dump.definition_0: A place where waste or garbage is left; a ground or place for dumping ashes, refuse, etc.; a disposal site.
dump.definition_1: A car or boat for dumping refuse, etc.
dump.definition_2: That which is dumped, especially in a chaotic way; a mess.

sly.definition_1: (having a positive sense) Dexterous in performing an action, so as to escape notice
sly.definition_2: Done with, and marked by, artful and dexterous secrecy; subtle

boom.definition_0: A low-pitched, resonant sound, such as of an explosion.
boom.definition_2: One of the calls of certain monkeys or birds.

smoke.definition_0: The visible vapor/vapour, gases, and fine particles given off by burning or smoldering material.
smoke.definition_2: Anything to smoke (e.g. cigarettes, marijuana, etc.)

soil.definition_0: A mixture of mineral particles and organic material, used to support plant growth.
soil.definition_1: The unconsolidated mineral or organic material on the immediate surface of the earth that serves as a natural medium for the growth of land plants.
soil.definition_2: The unconsolidated mineral or organic matter on the surface of the earth that has been subjected to and shows effects of genetic and environmental factors of: climate (including water and temperature effects), and macro- and microorganisms, conditioned by relief, acting on parent material over a period of time. A product-soil differs from the material from which it is derived in many physical, chemical, biological, and morphological properties and characteristics.

glove.definition_0: An item of clothing other than a mitten, covering all or part of the hand and fingers, but usually allowing independent movement of the fingers.
glove.definition_2: The ability to catch a hit ball.

snook.definition_0: A freshwater and marine fish of the family Centropomidae in the order Perciformes.
snook.definition_1: Any of various other ray-finned fishes in several families.

slate.definition_0: A fine-grained homogeneous sedimentary rock composed of clay or volcanic ash which has been metamorphosed so that it cleaves easily into thin layers.
slate.definition_1: The bluish-grey colour of most slate.
slate.definition_2: A chalkboard, sheet of slate for writing on with chalk or with a thin rod of slate (a slate pencil) formerly commonly used by both students and teachers in schools

zoom.definition_0: To communicate with someone using the Zoom videoconferencing software.

crazy.definition_0: An insane or eccentric person; a crackpot.

solid.definition_0: A substance in the fundamental state of matter that retains its size and shape without need of a container (as opposed to a liquid or gas).
solid.definition_1: A three-dimensional figure (as opposed to a surface, an area, or a curve).

scour.definition_0: The removal of sediment caused by swiftly moving water.
scour.definition_1: A place scoured out by running water, as in the bed of a stream below a waterfall.
scour.definition_2: A place where wool is washed to remove grease and impurities prior to processing.

basin.definition_0: A wide bowl for washing, sometimes affixed to a wall
basin.definition_1: A shallow bowl used for a single serving of a drink or liquidy food
basin.definition_2: A depression, natural or artificial, containing water

brace.definition_1: A measurement of length, originally representing a person's outstretched arms.
brace.definition_2: A curved instrument or handle of iron or wood, for holding and turning bits, etc.; a bitstock.

smear.definition_1: Any of various forms of distortion that make a signal harder to see or hear.

cloud.definition_1: A visible mass of water droplets suspended in the air.
cloud.definition_2: Any mass of dust, steam or smoke resembling such a mass.

slime.definition_0: Soft, moist earth or clay, having an adhesive quality; viscous mud; any substance of a dirty nature, that is moist, soft, and adhesive; bitumen; mud containing metallic ore, obtained in the preparatory dressing.
slime.definition_1: Any mucilaginous substance; or a mucus-like substance which exudes from the bodies of certain animals, such as snails or slugs.
slime.definition_2: A sneaky, unethical person; a slimeball.

scent.definition_1: An odour left by an animal that may be used for tracing.

blast.definition_1: A forcible stream of gas or liquid from an orifice, for example from a bellows, the mouth, etc.

style.definition_0: Senses relating to a thin, pointed object.
style.definition_1: (by extension from sense 1.1) A particular manner of expression in writing or speech, especially one regarded as good.
style.definition_2: A particular manner of creating, doing, or presenting something, especially a work of architecture or art.

shaft.definition_0: The entire body of a long weapon, such as an arrow.
shaft.definition_1: The long, narrow, central body of a spear, arrow, or javelin.
shaft.definition_2: (by extension) Anything cast or thrown as a spear or javelin.

stuff.definition_0: Miscellaneous items or objects; (with possessive) personal effects.
stuff.definition_2: The tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object.

curry.definition_0: One of a family of dishes originating from South Asian cuisine, flavoured by a spiced sauce.
curry.definition_1: A spiced sauce or relish, especially one flavoured with curry powder.

quill.definition_0: The lower shaft of a feather, specifically the region lacking barbs.
quill.definition_1: A pen made from a feather.

spile.definition_1: A spigot or plug used to stop the hole in a barrel or cask.
spile.definition_2: A spout inserted in a maple (or other tree) to draw off sap.

bogus.definition_0: A liquor made of rum and molasses.

drum.definition_0: A percussive musical instrument spanned with a thin covering on at least one end for striking, forming an acoustic chamber, affecting what materials are used to make it; a membranophone.
drum.definition_2: A barrel or large cylindrical container for liquid transport and storage.

frill.definition_0: A strip of pleated fabric or paper used as decoration or trim.
frill.definition_1: A substance or material on the edge of something, resembling such a strip of fabric.
frill.definition_2: A wrinkled edge to a film.

swill.definition_0: (collective) A mixture of solid and liquid food scraps fed to pigs etc; especially kitchen waste for this purpose.
swill.definition_1: (by extension) Any disgusting or distasteful liquid.

twist.definition_1: Anything twisted, or the act of twisting.

filth.definition_0: Dirt; foul matter; that which soils or defiles.
filth.definition_1: Smut; that which sullies or defiles the moral character; corruption; pollution.

donut.definition_0: A deep-fried piece of dough or batter, commonly made in a toroidal or ellipsoidal shape, and mixed with various sweeteners and flavors, sometimes filled with jelly, custard or cream.
donut.definition_1: Anything in the shape of a torus.
donut.definition_2: (automobile) A peel-out or skid-mark in the shape of donut; a 360-degree skid.

hives.definition_0: Itchy, swollen, red areas of the skin which can appear quickly in response to an allergen or due to other conditions.

rinse.definition_1: A liquid used to rinse, now particularly a hair dye.

eggs.definition_0: An approximately spherical or ellipsoidal body produced by birds, reptiles, insects and other animals, housing the embryo during its development.
eggs.definition_1: The egg of a domestic fowl (especially a hen) or its contents, used as food.
eggs.definition_2: The female primary cell, the ovum.

hold.definition_1: An act or instance of holding.
hold.definition_2: A place where animals are held for safety

pluck.definition_1: The lungs, heart with trachea and often oesophagus removed from slaughtered animals.

honey.definition_0: A viscous, sweet fluid produced from plant nectar by bees. Often used to sweeten tea or to spread on baked goods.

grape.definition_0: A small, round, smooth-skinned edible fruit, usually purple, red, or green, that grows in bunches on vines of genus Vitis.
grape.definition_1: A woody vine that bears clusters of grapes; a grapevine; of genus Vitis.
grape.definition_2: A dark purplish-red colour, the colour of many grapes.

woe.definition_0: Great sadness or distress; a misfortune causing such sadness.

fussy.definition_0: Anxious or particular about petty details.
fussy.definition_1: Having a tendency to fuss, cry, or be bad-tempered/ill-tempered (especially of babies).

clung.definition_0: To hold very tightly, as to not fall off.
clung.definition_1: To adhere to an object, without being affixed, in such a way as to follow its contours. Used especially of fabrics and films.
clung.definition_2: To cause to adhere to, especially by twining round or embracing.

pear.definition_0: An edible fruit produced by the pear tree, similar to an apple but elongated towards the stem.
pear.definition_1: A type of fruit tree (Pyrus communis).
pear.definition_2: The wood of the pear tree (pearwood, pear wood).

jaded.definition_1: To treat like a jade; to spurn.

candy.definition_0: Edible, sweet-tasting confectionery containing sugar, or sometimes artificial sweeteners, and often flavored with fruit, chocolate, nuts, herbs and spices, or artificial flavors.
candy.definition_1: A piece of confectionery of this kind.

comic.definition_1: A story composed of cartoon images arranged in sequence, usually with textual captions; a graphic novel.

boil.definition_0: A localized accumulation of pus in the skin, resulting from infection.

salt.definition_0: A common substance, chemically consisting mainly of sodium chloride (NaCl), used extensively as a condiment and preservative.
salt.definition_1: One of the compounds formed from the reaction of an acid with a base, where a positive ion replaces a hydrogen of the acid.
salt.definition_2: A salt marsh, a saline marsh at the shore of a sea.

apple.definition_0: A common, round fruit produced by the tree Malus domestica, cultivated in temperate climates.
apple.definition_1: Any of various tree-borne fruits or vegetables especially considered as resembling an apple; also (with qualifying words) used to form the names of other specific fruits such as custard apple, rose apple, thorn apple etc.
apple.definition_2: The fruit of the Tree of Knowledge, eaten by Adam and Eve according to post-Biblical Christian tradition; the forbidden fruit.

gulag.definition_1: The system of all Soviet prison and/or labor camps in use during the Stalinist period.

green.definition_2: Unripe, said of certain fruits that change color when they ripen.

wool.definition_0: The hair of the sheep, llama and some other ruminants.
wool.definition_1: A cloth or yarn made from the wool of sheep.
wool.definition_2: Anything with a texture like that of wool.

fluff.definition_0: Anything light, soft or fuzzy, especially fur, hair, feathers.
fluff.definition_2: A lapse or mistake, especially a mistake in an actor's lines.

adore.definition_1: To love with one's entire heart and soul; regard with deep respect and affection.

bask.definition_0: To bathe in warmth; to be exposed to pleasant heat.
bask.definition_1: To take great pleasure or satisfaction; to feel warmth or happiness. (This verb is usually followed by "in").

trial.definition_0: An opportunity to test something out; a test.
trial.definition_1: Appearance at judicial court in order to be examined.

soft.definition_0: A soft or foolish person; an idiot.
soft.definition_1: Ellipsis of soft tyre (A tyre whose compound is softer than mediums, and harder than supersofts.)
soft.definition_2: A soft sound or part of a sound.

ore.definition_0: Rock or other material that contains valuable or utilitarian materials; primarily a rock containing metals or gems for which it is typically mined and processed.

boar.definition_0: A wild boar (Sus scrofa), the wild ancestor of the domesticated pig.

fleck.definition_2: A small spot or streak; a speckle.

vent.definition_0: An opening through which gases, especially air, can pass.
vent.definition_2: The opening of a volcano from which lava flows.

age.definition_0: The whole duration of a being, whether animal, plant, or other kind, being alive.
age.definition_1: The number of full years, months, days, hours, etc., that someone, or something, has been alive.
age.definition_2: One of the stages of life.

bake.definition_0: The act of cooking food by baking.
bake.definition_1: Any of various baked dishes resembling casserole.
bake.definition_2: A social event at which food (such as seafood) is baked, or at which baked food is served.

aunt.definition_0: The sister or sister-in-law of one’s parent.
aunt.definition_1: The female cousin of one’s parent.
aunt.definition_2: A woman of an older generation than oneself, especially a friend of one's parents, by means of fictive kin.

bluff.definition_0: An act of bluffing; a false expression of the strength of one's position in order to intimidate; braggadocio.
bluff.definition_1: An attempt to represent oneself as holding a stronger hand than one actually does.

bark.definition_0: The short, loud, explosive sound uttered by a dog, a fox, and some other animals.

aim.definition_0: The pointing of a weapon, as a gun, a dart, or an arrow, or object, in the line of direction with the object intended to be struck; the line of fire; the direction of anything, such as a spear, a blow, a discourse, a remark, towards a particular point or object, with a view to strike or affect it.
aim.definition_1: The point intended to be hit, or object intended to be attained or affected.

bald.definition_0: A mountain summit or crest that lacks forest growth despite a warm climate conducive to such, as is found in many places in the Southern Appalachian Mountains.

bead.definition_0: Prayer, later especially with a rosary.
bead.definition_1: Each in a string of small balls making up the rosary or paternoster.

ask.definition_0: An act or instance of asking.

airy.definition_1: Relating or belonging to air; high in air; aerial.
airy.definition_2: Open to a free current of air; exposed to the air; breezy.

love.definition_1: A person who is the object of romantic feelings; a darling, a sweetheart, a beloved.
love.definition_2: A term of friendly address, regardless of feelings.

bass.definition_0: A low spectrum of sound tones.
bass.definition_1: A section of musical group that produces low-pitched sound, lower than the baritone and tenor.
bass.definition_2: One who sings in the bass range.

barn.definition_0: A building, often found on a farm, used for storage or keeping animals such as cattle.
barn.definition_1: A unit of surface area equal to 10−28 square metres.

base.definition_0: Something from which other things extend; a foundation.
base.definition_1: The starting point of a logical deduction or thought; basis.
base.definition_2: A permanent structure for housing military personnel and material.

both.definition_0: Each of the two, or of the two kinds.

beam.definition_0: Any large piece of timber or iron long in proportion to its thickness, and prepared for use.
beam.definition_1: One of the principal horizontal timbers of a building; one of the transverse members of a ship's frame on which the decks are laid — supported at the sides by knees in wooden ships and by stringers in steel ones.
beam.definition_2: The maximum width of a vessel (note that a vessel with a beam of 15 foot can also be said to be 15 foot abeam)

bean.definition_0: A reusable software component written in Java.

bear.definition_0: A large omnivorous mammal, related to the dog and raccoon, having shaggy hair, a very small tail, and flat feet; a member of family Ursidae.
bear.definition_2: An investor who sells commodities, securities or futures in anticipation of a fall in prices.

bet.definition_0: A wager, an agreement between two parties that a stake (usually money) will be paid by the loser to the winner (the winner being the one who correctly forecast the outcome of an event).

bell.definition_0: A percussive instrument made of metal or other hard material, typically but not always in the shape of an inverted cup with a flared rim, which resonates when struck.
bell.definition_1: The sounding of a bell as a signal.

revel.definition_0: An instance of merrymaking; a celebration.

bind.definition_1: A troublesome situation; a problem; a predicament or quandary.
bind.definition_2: Any twining or climbing plant or stem, especially a hop vine; a bine.

best.definition_0: The supreme effort one can make, or has made.
best.definition_2: The person (or persons; or thing or things) that is (are) most excellent.

bee.definition_0: A flying insect, of the clade Anthophila within the hymenopteran superfamily Apoidea, known for its organised societies (though only a minority have them), for collecting pollen and (in some species) producing wax and honey.

beat.definition_2: A pulse on the beat level, the metric level at which pulses are heard as the basic unit. Thus a beat is the basic time unit of a piece.

trend.definition_0: An inclination in a particular direction.

bill.definition_0: Any of various bladed or pointed hand weapons, originally designating an Anglo-Saxon sword, and later a weapon of infantry, especially in the 14th and 15th centuries, commonly consisting of a broad, heavy, double-edged, hook-shaped blade, with a short pike at the back and another at the top, attached to the end of a long staff.
bill.definition_1: A cutting instrument, with hook-shaped point, and fitted with a handle, used in pruning, etc.; a billhook.
bill.definition_2: Somebody armed with a bill; a billman.

bird.definition_0: A member of the class of animals Aves in the phylum Chordata, characterized by being warm-blooded, having feathers and wings usually capable of flight, and laying eggs.
bird.definition_2: A girl or woman, especially one considered sexually attractive.

belt.definition_0: A band worn around the waist to hold clothing to one's body (usually pants), hold weapons (such as a gun or sword), or serve as a decorative piece of clothing.
belt.definition_1: A band used as a restraint for safety purposes, such as a seat belt.
belt.definition_2: A band that is used in a machine to help transfer motion or power.

thick.definition_0: The thickest, or most active or intense, part of something.

paint.definition_0: A substance that is applied as a liquid or paste, and dries into a solid coating that protects or adds color/colour to an object or surface to which it has been applied.
paint.definition_1: (in the plural) A set of containers or blocks of paint of different colors/colours, used for painting pictures.
paint.definition_2: The free-throw lane, construed with the.

smelt.definition_0: Any small anadromous fish of the family Osmeridae, found in the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans and in lakes in North America and northern part of Europe.

beta.definition_0: The second letter of the Greek alphabet (Β,  β), preceded by alpha (Α,  α) and followed by gamma, (Γ,  γ). In modern Greek it represents the voiced labiodental fricative sound of v found in the English words have and vase.
beta.definition_1: Used in marking scheme: α, β, γ or α+, α, α-, β etc.
beta.definition_2: Average sensitivity of a security's price to overall securities market prices.

bend.definition_1: Any of the various knots which join the ends of two lines.
bend.definition_2: (in the plural, underwater diving, with the) A severe condition caused by excessively quick decompression, causing bubbles of nitrogen to form in the blood; decompression sickness.

blow.definition_1: A chance to catch one’s breath.

bit.definition_0: A piece of metal placed in a horse's mouth and connected to the reins to direct the animal.
bit.definition_1: A rotary cutting tool fitted to a drill, used to bore holes.
bit.definition_2: A coin of a specified value.

daub.definition_0: Excrement or clay used as a bonding material in construction.
daub.definition_1: A soft coating of mud, plaster etc.

short.definition_2: A short version of a garment in a particular size.

rough.definition_0: The unmowed part of a golf course.
rough.definition_1: A rude fellow; a coarse bully; a rowdy.
rough.definition_2: A scuffed and roughened area of the pitch, where the bowler's feet fall, used as a target by spin bowlers because of its unpredictable bounce.

blip.definition_0: To emit one or more bleeps.
blip.definition_1: To edit out inappropriate spoken language in a broadcast by replacing offending words with bleeps.

stain.definition_1: A blemish on one's character or reputation.
stain.definition_2: A substance used to soak into a surface and colour it.

blur.definition_1: Something that appears hazy or indistinct

shield.definition_0: Anything that protects or defends; defense; shelter; protection.
shield.definition_1: A shape like that of a shield; usually, an inverted triangle with sides that curve inward to form a pointed bottom, commonly used for police identifications and company logos.
shield.definition_2: A large expanse of exposed stable Precambrian rock.

blob.definition_0: A shapeless or amorphous mass; a vague shape or amount, especially of a liquid or semisolid substance; a clump, group or collection that lacks definite shape.
blob.definition_1: In astronomy, a large cloud of gas. In particular, an extended Lyman-Alpha blob is a huge body of gas that may be the precursor to a galaxy.

taint.definition_0: A contamination, decay or putrefaction, especially in food
taint.definition_1: A mark of disgrace, especially on one's character; blemish

bolt.definition_0: A (usually) metal fastener consisting of a cylindrical body that is threaded, with a larger head on one end. It can be inserted into an unthreaded hole up to the head, with a nut then threaded on the other end; a heavy machine screw.
bolt.definition_1: A sliding pin or bar in a lock or latch mechanism.
bolt.definition_2: A bar of wood or metal dropped in horizontal hooks on a door and adjoining wall or between the two sides of a double door, to prevent the door(s) from being forced open.

bog.definition_0: An area of decayed vegetation (particularly sphagnum moss) which forms a wet spongy ground too soft for walking; a marsh or swamp.
bog.definition_1: Confusion, difficulty, or any other thing or place that impedes progress in the manner of such areas.
bog.definition_2: The acidic soil of such areas, principally composed of peat; marshland, swampland.

boot.definition_0: A heavy shoe that covers part of the leg.
boot.definition_1: A blow with the foot; a kick.
boot.definition_2: A flexible cover of rubber or plastic, which may be preformed to a particular shape and used to protect a shaft, lever, switch, or opening from dust, dirt, moisture, etc.

bowl.definition_0: A roughly hemispherical container used to hold, mix or present food, such as salad, fruit or soup, or other items.
bowl.definition_1: As much as is held by a bowl.
bowl.definition_2: A dish comprising a mix of different foods, not all of which need be cooked, served in a bowl.

bone.definition_0: A composite material consisting largely of calcium phosphate and collagen and making up the skeleton of most vertebrates.
bone.definition_1: Any of the components of an endoskeleton, made of bone.
bone.definition_2: A bone of a fish; a fishbone.

speck.definition_0: A tiny spot, especially of dirt etc.
speck.definition_1: A very small thing; a particle; a whit.
speck.definition_2: A small etheostomoid fish, Etheostoma stigmaeum, common in the eastern United States.

boss.definition_0: A person who oversees and directs the work of others; a supervisor.
boss.definition_1: A person in charge of a business or company.
boss.definition_2: A leader, the head of an organized group or team.

blot.definition_0: A blemish, spot or stain made by a coloured substance.
blot.definition_1: (by extension) A stain on someone's reputation or character; a disgrace.
blot.definition_2: A method of transferring proteins, DNA or RNA, onto a carrier.

bore.definition_0: A hole drilled or milled through something, or (by extension) its diameter.
bore.definition_1: The tunnel inside of a gun's barrel through which the bullet travels when fired, or (by extension) its diameter.
bore.definition_2: A tool, such as an auger, for making a hole by boring.

bull.definition_0: An adult male of domesticated cattle or oxen.
bull.definition_1: A male of domesticated cattle or oxen of any age.

born.definition_0: To carry or convey, literally or figuratively.
born.definition_2: To support, keep up, or maintain.

bump.definition_0: A light blow or jolting collision.
bump.definition_1: The sound of such a collision.
bump.definition_2: A protuberance on a level surface.

wharf.definition_0: A man-made landing place for ships on a shore or river bank.
wharf.definition_1: The bank of a river, or the shore of the sea.

shawl.definition_0: A square or rectangular piece of cloth worn as a covering for the head, neck, and shoulders, typically by women.
shawl.definition_1: A fold of wrinkled flesh under the lips and neck of a bloodhound, used in scenting.

aroma.definition_0: A smell; especially a pleasant spicy or fragrant one.

singe.definition_0: A burning of the surface; a slight burn.

crash.definition_0: A sudden, intense, loud sound, as made for example by cymbals.
crash.definition_1: An automobile, airplane, or other vehicle accident.
crash.definition_2: A malfunction of computer software or hardware which causes it to shut down or become partially or totally inoperable.

wreck.definition_0: Something or someone that has been ruined.
wreck.definition_1: The remains of something that has been severely damaged or worn down.
wreck.definition_2: An event in which something is damaged through collision.

calm.definition_0: (in a person) The state of being calm; peacefulness; absence of worry, anger, fear or other strong negative emotion.
calm.definition_1: (in a place or situation) The state of being calm; absence of noise and disturbance.
calm.definition_2: A period of time without wind.

bunk.definition_0: One of a series of berths or beds placed in tiers.
bunk.definition_1: A built-in bed on board ship, often erected in tiers one above the other.

berth.definition_0: A fixed bunk for sleeping (in caravans, trains, etc).
berth.definition_1: Room for maneuvering or safety. (Often used in the phrase a wide berth.)
berth.definition_2: A space for a ship to moor or a vehicle to park.

cake.definition_0: A rich, sweet dessert food, typically made of flour, sugar and eggs and baked in an oven, and often covered in icing.
cake.definition_1: A small mass of baked dough, especially a thin loaf from unleavened dough.
cake.definition_2: A thin wafer-shaped mass of fried batter; a griddlecake or pancake.

cane.definition_0: A plant with simple stems, like bamboo or sugar cane, or the stem thereof
cane.definition_1: The stem of such a plant adapted for use as a tool
cane.definition_2: A rod-shaped tool or device, somewhat like a cane

buy.definition_0: Something which is bought; a purchase.

under.definition_1: Under anesthesia, especially general anesthesia; sedated.

birth.definition_0: The process of childbearing; the beginning of life.
birth.definition_2: A beginning or start; a point of origin.

coco.definition_1: Coconut, the fruit of the coconut palm.

clot.definition_0: A thrombus, solidified mass of blood.
clot.definition_1: A solidified mass of any liquid.

taro.definition_0: Colocasia esculenta, raised as a food primarily for its corm, which distantly resembles potato.
taro.definition_1: Any of several other species with similar corms and growth habit in Colocasia, Alocasia etc.

coupe.definition_0: An ice cream dessert; the glass it is served in.
coupe.definition_1: A car with two doors (variant of coupé).

pail.definition_0: A vessel of wood, tin, plastic, etc., usually cylindrical and having a handle -- used especially for carrying liquids, for example water or milk; a bucket (sometimes with a cover).
pail.definition_1: (In technical use) A closed (covered) cylindrical shipping container.

vapid.definition_0: Offering nothing that is stimulating or challenging.

toga.definition_0: A loose outer garment worn by the citizens of Ancient Rome.

quip.definition_0: A smart, sarcastic turn or jest; a taunt; a severe retort or comeback; a gibe.

weir.definition_0: An adjustable dam placed across a river to regulate the flow of water downstream.
weir.definition_1: A fence placed across a river to catch fish.

dolt.definition_0: A stupid person; a blockhead or dullard.

allot.definition_0: To distribute or apportion by (or as if by) lot.
allot.definition_1: To assign or designate as a task or for a purpose.

cede.definition_0: To give up; yield to another.

veld.definition_0: The open pasture land or grassland of South Africa and neighboring countries.

hasp.definition_0: A clasp, especially a metal strap fastened by a padlock or a pin; also, a hook for fastening a door.
hasp.definition_1: A spindle to wind yarn, thread, or silk on.
hasp.definition_2: An instrument for cutting the surface of grassland; a scarifier.

ewer.definition_0: A kind of widemouthed pitcher or jug with a shape like a vase and a handle.

lien.definition_1: A right to take possession of a debtor’s property as security until a debt or duty is discharged.

aloof.definition_0: Reserved and remote; either physically or emotionally distant; standoffish.

obey.definition_0: To do as ordered by (a person, institution etc), to act according to the bidding of.
obey.definition_1: To do as one is told.
obey.definition_2: To be obedient, compliant (to a given law, restriction etc.).

foal.definition_0: A young horse or related animal, especially just after birth or less than a year old.
foal.definition_1: A young boy who assisted the headsman by pushing or pulling the tub.

watt.definition_0: In the International System of Units, the derived unit of power; the power of a system in which one joule of energy is transferred per second. Symbol: W

acorn.definition_0: The fruit of the oak, being an oval nut growing in a woody cup or cupule.
acorn.definition_1: A cone-shaped piece of wood on the point of the spindle above the vane, on the mast-head.

admix.definition_1: The mixture that results from admixing, especially an alloy.

dox.definition_0: Documents, especially information sought by hackers about an individual (address, credit card numbers, etc.).

finch.definition_0: Any bird of the family Fringillidae, seed-eating passerine birds, native chiefly to the Northern Hemisphere and usually having a conical beak.

ensue.definition_1: To follow (in time), to be subsequent to.
ensue.definition_2: To occur afterwards, as a result or effect.

aerie.definition_0: A local chapter of the Fraternal Order of Eagles.

nacho.definition_0: A single tortilla chip from a dish of nachos.

igloo.definition_0: A dome-shaped Inuit shelter, constructed of blocks cut from snow.
igloo.definition_1: A cavity, or excavation, made in the snow by a seal, over its breathing hole in the sea ice.
igloo.definition_2: A reinforced bunker for the storage of nuclear weapons.

agile.definition_0: Having the faculty of quick motion in the limbs; apt or ready to move
agile.definition_2: Of or relating to agile software development, a technique for iterative and incremental development of software involving collaboration between teams.

sieve.definition_0: A device with a mesh bottom to separate, in a granular material, larger particles from smaller ones, or to separate solid objects from a liquid.
sieve.definition_1: A process, physical or abstract, that arrives at a final result by filtering out unwanted pieces of input from a larger starting set of input.

dole.definition_0: Money or other goods given as charity.
dole.definition_2: Payment by the state to the unemployed.

halt.definition_0: To limp; move with a limping gait.
halt.definition_1: To stand in doubt whether to proceed, or what to do; hesitate; be uncertain; linger; delay; mammer.
halt.definition_2: To be lame, faulty, or defective, as in connection with ideas, or in measure, or in versification.

opine.definition_0: To have or express an opinion; to state as an opinion; to suppose, consider (that).
opine.definition_1: To give one's formal opinion (on or upon something).

sock.definition_0: A knitted or woven covering for the foot.
sock.definition_1: A shoe worn by Greco-Roman comedy actors.
sock.definition_2: A color pattern (usually white) on a cat's or dog's lower leg that is different from the color pattern on the rest of the animal.

lend.definition_1: (of a person or animal) The loins; flank; buttocks.

black.definition_0: The colour/color perceived in the absence of light, but also when no light is reflected, but rather absorbed.
black.definition_2: A pen, pencil, crayon, etc., made of black pigment.

poor.definition_0: (with "the") Those who have little or no possessions or money, taken as a group.

muted.definition_1: To turn off the sound of.

white.definition_0: The color/colour of snow or milk; the colour of light containing equal amounts of all visible wavelengths.
white.definition_1: A person of European descent with light-coloured skin.
white.definition_2: Any butterfly of the family Pieridae.

howl.definition_0: The protracted, mournful cry of a dog or a wolf, or other like sound.
howl.definition_1: A prolonged cry of distress or anguish; a wail.

sole.definition_0: A wooden band or yoke put around the neck of an ox or cow in the stall.

spawn.definition_0: To produce or deposit (eggs) in water.
spawn.definition_1: To generate, bring into being, especially non-mammalian beings in very large numbers.

kilt.definition_0: A traditional Scottish garment, usually worn by men, having roughly the same morphology as a wrap-around skirt, with overlapping front aprons and pleated around the sides and back, and usually made of twill-woven worsted wool with a tartan pattern.
kilt.definition_1: Any Scottish garment from which the above lies in a direct line of descent, such as the philibeg, or the great kilt or belted plaid
kilt.definition_2: A plaid, pleated school uniform skirt sometimes structured as a wrap around, sometimes pleated throughout the entire circumference; also used as boys' wear in 19th century USA.

dove.definition_0: A pigeon, especially one smaller in size; a bird (often arbitrarily called either a pigeon or a dove or both) of more than 300 species of the family Columbidae.
dove.definition_1: A person favouring conciliation and negotiation rather than conflict.
dove.definition_2: Term of endearment for one regarded as pure and gentle.

brood.definition_0: The young of certain animals, especially a group of young birds or fowl hatched at one time by the same mother.
brood.definition_1: The young of any egg-laying creature, especially if produced at the same time.
brood.definition_2: The eggs and larvae of social insects such as bees, ants and some wasps, especially when gathered together in special brood chambers or combs within the colony.

augur.definition_0: A diviner who foretells events by the behaviour of birds or other animals, or by signs derived from celestial phenomena, or unusual occurrences.
augur.definition_1: An official who interpreted omens before the start of public events.

pout.definition_1: A fit of sulking or sullenness.

award.definition_0: A judgment, sentence, or final decision. Specifically: The decision of arbitrators in a case submitted.
award.definition_1: The paper containing the decision of arbitrators; that which is warded.
award.definition_2: A trophy or medal; something that denotes an accomplishment, especially in a competition. A prize or honor based on merit.

flex.definition_1: The or an act of flexing.

shred.definition_0: A long, narrow piece cut or torn off; a strip.
shred.definition_1: In general, a fragment; a piece; a particle; a very small amount.

maul.definition_0: A heavy long-handled hammer, used for splitting logs by driving a wedge into them, or in combat.
maul.definition_1: A situation where the player carrying the ball, who must be on his feet, is held by one or more opponents, and one or more of the ball carrier's team mates bind onto the ball carrier.

wisp.definition_0: A small bundle, as of straw or other like substance; any slender, flexible structure or group.
wisp.definition_2: A will o' the wisp, or ignis fatuus.

twit.definition_2: A euphemism for "twat", a contemptible or stupid person.

taut.definition_0: To make taut; to tauten, to tighten.

hatch.definition_0: A horizontal door in a floor or ceiling.
hatch.definition_2: An opening in a wall at window height for the purpose of serving food or other items. A pass through.

plea.definition_0: An appeal, petition, urgent prayer or entreaty.
plea.definition_2: That which is alleged or pleaded, in defense or in justification.

claim.definition_0: A demand of ownership made for something.
claim.definition_2: The right or ground of demanding.

sharp.definition_0: The symbol ♯, placed after the name of a note in the key signature or before a note on the staff to indicate that the note is to be played a semitone higher.
sharp.definition_1: A note that is played a semitone higher than usual; denoted by the name of the note that is followed by the symbol ♯.
sharp.definition_2: A note that is sharp in a particular key.

scrap.definition_0: A (small) piece; a fragment; a detached, incomplete portion.
scrap.definition_2: The crisp substance that remains after drying out animal fat.

veto.definition_0: A political right to disapprove of (and thereby stop) the process of a decision, a law etc.
veto.definition_2: An authoritative prohibition or negative; a forbidding; an interdiction.

rigid.definition_0: A bicycle with no suspension system.

dock.definition_0: Any of the genus Rumex of coarse weedy plants with small green flowers related to buckwheat, especially common dock, and used as potherbs and in folk medicine, especially in curing nettle rash.
dock.definition_1: A burdock plant, or the leaves of that plant.

trim.definition_0: Decoration; especially, decoration placed along edges or borders.
trim.definition_1: A haircut, especially a moderate one to touch up an existing style.

crisp.definition_0: A thin slice of fried potato eaten as a snack.
crisp.definition_1: A baked dessert made with fruit and crumb topping
crisp.definition_2: Anything baked or fried and eaten as a snack

bleak.definition_1: Desolate and exposed; swept by cold winds.

gilt.definition_0: To cover with a thin layer of gold; to cover with gold leaf.
gilt.definition_2: To decorate with a golden surface appearance.

cruel.definition_0: To spoil or ruin (one's chance of success)
cruel.definition_1: To violently provoke (a child) in the belief that this will make them more assertive.

grant.definition_0: The act of granting; a bestowing or conferring; concession; allowance; permission.
grant.definition_1: The yielding or admission of something in dispute.
grant.definition_2: The thing or property granted; a gift; a boon.

mix.definition_1: To combine (items from two or more sources normally kept separate).
mix.definition_2: To form by mingling; to produce by the stirring together of ingredients; to concoct from different parts.

hurry.definition_2: An incidence of a defensive player forcing the quarterback to act faster than the quarterback was prepared to, resulting in a failed offensive play.

bray.definition_0: The cry of an animal, now chiefly that of animals related to the ass or donkey, or the camel.
bray.definition_1: (by extension) Any discordant, grating, or harsh sound.

ruin.definition_0: (sometimes in the plural) The remains of a destroyed or dilapidated construction, such as a house or castle.
ruin.definition_1: The state of being a ruin, destroyed or decayed.
ruin.definition_2: Something that leads to serious trouble or destruction.

mole.definition_0: A pigmented spot on the skin, a naevus, slightly raised, and sometimes hairy.

chest.definition_0: A box, now usually a large strong box with a secure convex lid.
chest.definition_2: The place in which public money is kept; a treasury.

mule.definition_0: The generally sterile male or female hybrid offspring of a male donkey and a female horse.
mule.definition_1: The generally sterile hybrid offspring of any two species of animals.

force.definition_0: Strength or energy of body or mind; active power; vigour; might; capacity of exercising an influence or producing an effect.
force.definition_1: Power exerted against will or consent; compulsory power; violence; coercion.
force.definition_2: Anything that is able to make a substantial change in a person or thing.

taunt.definition_0: A scornful or mocking remark; a jeer or mockery

gill.definition_0: (animal anatomy) a breathing organ of fish and other aquatic animals
gill.definition_1: (of a fish) a gill slit or gill cover
gill.definition_2: One of the radial folds on the underside of the cap of a mushroom, on the surface of which the spore-producing organs are borne

shade.definition_0: Darkness where light, particularly sunlight, is blocked.
shade.definition_1: Something that blocks light, particularly in a window.
shade.definition_2: A variety of a colour/color, in particular one obtained by adding black (compare tint).

sneer.definition_0: A facial expression where one slightly raises one corner of the upper lip, generally indicating scorn.

crawl.definition_0: The act of moving slowly on hands and knees etc, or with frequent stops.
crawl.definition_1: A rapid swimming stroke with alternate overarm strokes and a fluttering kick.

toil.definition_0: Labour, work, especially of a grueling nature.
toil.definition_2: (usually in plural) A net or snare; any thread, web, or string spread for taking prey.

plow.definition_0: The notional area of land able to be farmed in a year by a team of 8 oxen pulling a carruca plow, usually reckoned at 120 acres.

tribe.definition_0: A socially, ethnically, or politically cohesive group of people.
tribe.definition_1: A society larger than a band but smaller than a state.
tribe.definition_2: A group of apes who live and work together.

mend.definition_0: A place, as in clothing, which has been repaired by mending.

maw.definition_0: The stomach, especially of an animal.
maw.definition_1: The upper digestive tract (where food enters the body), especially the mouth and jaws of a fearsome and ravenous creature.
maw.definition_2: Any large, insatiable or perilous opening.

mock.definition_0: An imitation, usually of lesser quality.
mock.definition_2: A practice exam set by an educating institution to prepare students for an important exam.

rip.definition_1: A type of tide or current.
rip.definition_2: A comical, embarrassing, or hypocritical event or action.

busk.definition_0: A strip of metal, whalebone, wood, or other material, worn in the front of a corset to stiffen it.

slash.definition_0: A slashing action or motion, particularly:
slash.definition_1: A mark made by a slashing motion, particularly:
slash.definition_2: Something resembling such a mark, particularly:

abbot.definition_0: The superior or head of an abbey or monastery.
abbot.definition_1: The pastor and/or administrator of an order, including minor and major orders starting with the minor order of porter.
abbot.definition_2: A layman who received the abbey's revenues, after the closing of the monasteries.

label.definition_0: A small ticket or sign giving information about something to which it is attached or intended to be attached.
label.definition_1: A name given to something or someone to categorise them as part of a particular social group.

abhor.definition_0: To regard with horror or detestation; to shrink back with shuddering from; to feel excessive repugnance toward; to detest to extremity; to loathe.
abhor.definition_1: To fill with horror or disgust.
abhor.definition_2: To turn aside or avoid; to keep away from; to reject.

acute.definition_0: A person who has the acute form of a disorder, such as schizophrenia.
acute.definition_1: An accent or tone higher than others.

sour.definition_0: The sensation of a sour taste.
sour.definition_1: A drink made with whiskey, lemon or lime juice and sugar.
sour.definition_2: (by extension) Any cocktail containing lemon or lime juice.

keep.definition_0: The main tower of a castle or fortress, located within the castle walls.
keep.definition_1: The food or money required to keep someone alive and healthy; one's support, maintenance.
keep.definition_2: The act or office of keeping; custody; guard; care; heed; charge; notice.

acrid.definition_0: Sharp and harsh, or bitter and not to the taste.

faith.definition_0: A trust or confidence in the intentions or abilities of a person, object, or ideal from prior empirical evidence.
faith.definition_1: The process of forming or understanding abstractions, ideas, or beliefs, without empirical evidence, experience or observation.
faith.definition_2: A religious or spiritual belief system.

creed.definition_0: That which is believed; accepted doctrine, especially religious doctrine; a particular set of beliefs; any summary of principles or opinions professed or adhered to.
creed.definition_1: (specifically) A reading or statement of belief that summarizes the faith it represents; a confession of faith for public use, especially one which is brief and comprehensive.
creed.definition_2: The fact of believing; belief, faith.

acid.definition_1: Any of several classes of compound having the following properties:

paper.definition_0: A sheet material used for writing on or printing on (or as a non-waterproof container), usually made by draining cellulose fibres from a suspension in water.
paper.definition_1: A newspaper or anything used as such (such as a newsletter or listing magazine).

album.definition_0: A book specially designed to keep photographs, stamps, or autographs.
album.definition_1: A collection, especially of literary items
album.definition_2: A phonograph record that is composed of several tracks

work.definition_2: Sustained effort to achieve a goal or result, especially overcoming obstacles.

title.definition_0: A prefix (honorific) or suffix (post-nominal) added to a person's name to signify either veneration, official position or a professional or academic qualification. See also
title.definition_1: Legal right to ownership of a property; a deed or other certificate proving this.
title.definition_2: In canon law, that by which a beneficiary holds a benefice.

dire.definition_0: Warning of bad consequences: ill-boding; portentous.
dire.definition_1: Requiring action to prevent bad consequences: urgent, pressing.

abide.definition_0: To endure without yielding; to withstand; await defiantly; to encounter; to persevere.
abide.definition_1: To bear patiently; to tolerate; to put up with; stand.
abide.definition_2: To pay for; to stand the consequences of; to answer for; to suffer for; to atone for.

abeam.definition_0: Alongside or abreast; opposite the center of the side of the ship or aircraft.

dust.definition_1: The act of cleaning by dusting.
dust.definition_2: The earth, as the resting place of the dead.

tart.definition_0: Sharp to the taste; acid; sour.
tart.definition_1: (of wine) high or too high in acidity.

cliff.definition_0: A vertical (or nearly vertical) rock face.
cliff.definition_1: A point where something abruptly fails or decreases in value etc.

axis.definition_0: An imaginary line around which an object spins (an axis of rotation) or is symmetrically arranged (an axis of symmetry).
axis.definition_1: A fixed one-dimensional figure, such as a line or arc, with an origin and orientation and such that its points are in one-to-one correspondence with a set of numbers; an axis forms part of the basis of a space or is used to position and locate data in a graph (a coordinate axis)
axis.definition_2: The second cervical vertebra of the spine

doom.definition_1: An undesirable fate; an impending severe occurrence or danger that seems inevitable.
doom.definition_2: A feeling of danger, impending danger, darkness or despair.

duke.definition_0: The male ruler of a duchy (female equivalent: duchess).
duke.definition_1: The sovereign of a small state.
duke.definition_2: A high title of nobility; the male holder of a dukedom.

down.definition_2: An act of swallowing an entire drink at once.

dance.definition_0: A sequence of rhythmic steps or movements usually performed to music, for pleasure or as a form of social interaction.
dance.definition_1: A social gathering where dancing is the main activity.
dance.definition_2: A normally horizontal stripe called a fess that has been modified to zig-zag across the center of a coat of arms from dexter to sinister.

fear.definition_0: A strong, uncontrollable, unpleasant emotion or feeling caused by actual or perceived danger or threat.
fear.definition_1: A phobia, a sense of fear induced by something or someone.
fear.definition_2: Terrified veneration or reverence, particularly towards God, gods, or sovereigns.

panic.definition_0: Overpowering fright, often affecting groups of people or animals.
panic.definition_1: Rapid reduction in asset prices due to broad efforts to raise cash in anticipation of continuing decline in asset prices.
panic.definition_2: A kernel panic or system crash.

flow.definition_0: A movement in people or things with a particular way in large numbers or amounts
flow.definition_1: The movement of a real or figurative fluid.
flow.definition_2: A formalization of the idea of the motion of particles in a fluid, as a group action of the real numbers on a set.

goose.definition_0: Any of various grazing waterfowl of the family Anatidae, which have feathers and webbed feet and are capable of flying, swimming, and walking on land, and which are bigger than ducks.
goose.definition_2: The flesh of the goose used as food.

baby.definition_0: A very young human, particularly from birth to a couple of years old or until walking is fully mastered.
baby.definition_1: Any very young animal, especially a vertebrate; many species have specific names for their babies, such as kittens for the babies of cats, puppies for the babies of dogs, and chickens for the babies of birds. See for more.

uncle.definition_0: The brother or brother-in-law of one’s parent.
uncle.definition_1: The male cousin of one’s parent.
uncle.definition_2: A companion to one's (usually unmarried) mother.

plump.definition_0: To grow plump; to swell out.
plump.definition_1: To make plump; to fill (out) or support; often with up.
plump.definition_2: To cast or let drop all at once, suddenly and heavily.

affix.definition_0: That which is affixed; an appendage.
affix.definition_1: A bound morpheme added to the word’s stem's end.
affix.definition_2: (broadly) A bound morpheme added to a word’s stem; a prefix, suffix etc.

arise.definition_0: To come up from a lower to a higher position.
arise.definition_1: To come up from one's bed or place of repose; to get up.
arise.definition_2: To spring up; to come into action, being, or notice; to become operative, sensible, or visible; to begin to act a part; to present itself.

camel.definition_0: A beast of burden, much used in desert areas, of the genus Camelus.
camel.definition_1: A light brownish color, like that of a camel (also called camel brown).
camel.definition_2: Loaded vessels lashed tightly, one on each side of another vessel, and then emptied to reduce the draught of the ship in the middle.

yacht.definition_0: A slick and light ship for making pleasure trips or racing on water, having sails but often motor-powered. At times used as a residence offshore on a dock.
yacht.definition_1: Any vessel used for private, noncommercial purposes.

jelly.definition_0: An explosive mixture of nitroglycerine and nitrate absorbed onto a base of wood pulp.

panda.definition_0: The red panda (Ailurus fulgens), a small raccoon-like animal of northeast Asia with reddish fur and a long, ringed tail.

tiger.definition_0: Panthera tigris, a large predatory mammal of the cat family, indigenous to Asia.
tiger.definition_1: A representation of a large mythological cat, used on a coat of arms.
tiger.definition_2: A servant in livery, who rides with his master or mistress.

zebra.definition_0: Any of three species of genus Equus: E. grevyi, E. quagga, or E. zebra, all with black and white stripes and native to Africa.
zebra.definition_2: An unlikely diagnosis, especially for symptoms probably caused by a common ailment. (Originates in the advice often given to medical students: "when you hear hoofbeats, think of horses, not zebras".)

stout.definition_0: A dark and strong malt brew made with toasted grain.

mango.definition_0: A tropical Asian fruit tree, Mangifera indica.
mango.definition_1: The fruit of the mango tree.
mango.definition_2: A pickled vegetable or fruit with a spicy stuffing; a vegetable or fruit which has been mangoed.

bloom.definition_0: A blossom; the flower of a plant; an expanded bud.
bloom.definition_2: The opening of flowers in general; the state of blossoming or of having the flowers open.

knife.definition_0: A utensil or a tool designed for cutting, consisting of a flat piece of hard material, usually steel or other metal (the blade), usually sharpened on one edge, attached to a handle. The blade may be pointed for piercing.
knife.definition_1: A weapon designed with the aforementioned specifications intended for slashing and/or stabbing and too short to be called a sword. A dagger.
knife.definition_2: Any blade-like part in a tool or a machine designed for cutting, such as that of a chipper.

elbow.definition_0: The joint between the upper arm and the forearm.
elbow.definition_1: (by extension) Any turn or bend like that of the elbow, in a wall, building, coastline, etc.; an angular or jointed part of any structure, such as the raised arm of a chair or sofa, or a short pipe fitting, turning at an angle or bent.

alone.definition_1: Apart from, or exclusive of, others.

fence.definition_0: A thin artificial barrier that separates two pieces of land or a house perimeter.
fence.definition_1: Someone who hides or buys and sells stolen goods, a criminal middleman for transactions of stolen goods.

leash.definition_0: A strap, cord or rope with which to restrain an animal, often a dog.
leash.definition_1: A brace and a half; a tierce.
leash.definition_2: A set of three; three creatures of any kind, especially greyhounds, foxes, bucks, and hares; hence, the number three in general.

night.definition_0: The period between sunset and sunrise, when a location faces far away from the sun, thus when the sky is dark.
night.definition_1: (Astronomy) The period of darkness beginning at the end of evening astronomical twilight when the sun is 18 degrees below the horizon, and ending at the beginning of morning astronomical twilight.
night.definition_2: (Legal) Often defined in the legal system as beginning 30 minutes after sunset, and ending 30 minutes before sunrise.

motor.definition_0: A machine or device that converts other energy forms into mechanical energy, or imparts motion.
motor.definition_2: A source of power for something; an inspiration; a driving force.

drain.definition_0: A conduit allowing liquid to flow out of an otherwise contained volume; a plughole (UK)
drain.definition_1: An access point or conduit for rainwater that drains directly downstream in a (drainage) basin without going through sewers or water treatment in order to prevent or belay floods.
drain.definition_2: Something consuming resources and providing nothing in return.

occur.definition_2: To come or be presented to the mind; to suggest itself.

shake.definition_0: The act of shaking or being shaken; tremulous or back-and-forth motion.
shake.definition_2: A beverage made by adding ice cream to a (usually carbonated) drink; a float.

fable.definition_0: A fictitious narrative intended to enforce some useful truth or precept, usually with animals, etc. as characters; an apologue. Prototypically, Aesop's Fables.
fable.definition_1: Any story told to excite wonder; common talk; the theme of talk.

radar.definition_0: A method of detecting distant objects and determining their position, velocity, or other characteristics by analysis of sent radio waves (usually microwaves) reflected from their surfaces
radar.definition_1: A type of system using such method, differentiated by platform, configuration, frequency, power, and other technical attributes.
radar.definition_2: An installation of such a system or of the transmitting and receiving apparatus.

ghost.definition_0: The spirit; the soul of man.
ghost.definition_1: The disembodied soul; the soul or spirit of a deceased person; a spirit appearing after death
ghost.definition_2: Any faint shadowy semblance; an unsubstantial image

heap.definition_0: A crowd; a throng; a multitude or great number of people.
heap.definition_1: A pile or mass; a collection of things laid in a body, or thrown together so as to form an elevation.
heap.definition_2: A great number or large quantity of things.

lever.definition_0: (except in generalized senses below) A crowbar.
lever.definition_1: A rigid piece which is capable of turning about one point, or axis (the fulcrum), and in which are two or more other points where forces are applied; — used for transmitting and modifying force and motion.
lever.definition_2: A small such piece to trigger or control a mechanical device (like a button).

video.definition_1: A short film clip, with or without audio (as in a music video, or one of the plethora of user-generated short movies on sites such as YouTube).
video.definition_2: Motion picture stored on VHS or some other format.

queen.definition_0: A female monarch. Example: Queen Victoria.
queen.definition_1: The wife or widow of a king.
queen.definition_2: The most powerful piece, able to move any number of spaces horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.

wheel.definition_0: A circular device capable of rotating on its axis, facilitating movement or transportation or performing labour in machines.
wheel.definition_1: The breaking wheel, an old instrument of torture.
wheel.definition_2: A person with a great deal of power or influence; a big wheel.

extra.definition_0: Something additional, such as an item above and beyond the ordinary school curriculum, or added to the usual charge on a bill.
extra.definition_1: An extra edition of a newspaper, which is printed outside of the normal printing cycle.
extra.definition_2: A run scored without the ball having hit the striker's bat - a wide, bye, leg bye or no ball.

vowel.definition_0: A sound produced by the vocal cords with relatively little restriction of the oral cavity, forming the prominent sound of a syllable.
vowel.definition_1: A letter representing the sound of vowel; in English, the vowels are a, e, i, o, u, and sometimes y.

knoll.definition_0: A small mound or rounded hill.

jump.definition_0: The act of jumping; a leap; a spring; a bound.
jump.definition_1: An effort; an attempt; a venture.
jump.definition_2: A dislocation in a stratum; a fault.

mound.definition_0: An artificial hill or elevation of earth; a raised bank; an embankment thrown up for defense
mound.definition_1: A natural elevation appearing as if thrown up artificially; a regular and isolated hill, hillock, or knoll.
mound.definition_2: Elevated area of dirt upon which the pitcher stands to pitch.

ugly.definition_2: A shade for the face, projecting from a bonnet.

twin.definition_0: Either of two people (or, less commonly, animals) who shared the same uterus at the same time; one who was born at the same birth as a sibling.
twin.definition_1: Either of two similar or closely related objects, entities etc.
twin.definition_2: A room in a hotel, guesthouse, etc. with two beds; a twin room.

sweat.definition_0: Fluid that exits the body through pores in the skin usually due to physical stress and/or high temperature for the purpose of regulating body temperature and removing certain compounds from the circulation.
sweat.definition_1: The state of one who sweats; diaphoresis.
sweat.definition_2: (especially WWI) A soldier (especially one who is old or experienced).

xenon.definition_0: The chemical element (symbol Xe) with an atomic number of 54. It is a colorless, odorless, unreactive noble gas, used notably in camera flash technology.

drink.definition_0: To consume (a liquid) through the mouth.
drink.definition_1: (metonymic) To consume the liquid contained within (a bottle, glass, etc.).

jumbo.definition_0: An especially large or powerful person, animal, or thing.
jumbo.definition_1: A platform-mounted machine for drilling rock.

wagon.definition_0: A four-wheeled cart for hauling loads.
wagon.definition_1: A four-wheeled child's riding toy, pulled or steered by a long handle attached to the front.
wagon.definition_2: An enclosed vehicle for carrying goods or people; (by extension) a lorry, a truck.

frown.definition_0: A facial expression in which the eyebrows are brought together, and the forehead is wrinkled, usually indicating displeasure, sadness or worry, or less often confusion or concentration.
frown.definition_1: A facial expression in which the corners of the mouth are pointed down.

knock.definition_0: Sudden fatigue as a result of glycogen depletion from not having taken in enough nutrition.

world.definition_0: (with "the") Human collective existence; existence in general.

woman.definition_2: A female person, usually an adult; a (generally adult) female sentient being, whether human, supernatural, elf, alien, etc.

beach.definition_0: The shore of a body of water, especially when sandy or pebbly.
beach.definition_1: A horizontal strip of land, usually sandy, adjoining water.
beach.definition_2: The loose pebbles of the seashore, especially worn by waves; shingle.

river.definition_0: A large and often winding stream which drains a land mass, carrying water down from higher areas to a lower point, oftentimes ending in another body of water, such as an ocean or in an inland sea.
river.definition_1: Any large flow of a liquid in a single body.
river.definition_2: The last card dealt in a hand.

table.definition_0: Furniture with a top surface to accommodate a variety of uses.
table.definition_2: The top of a stringed instrument, particularly a member of the violin family: the side of the instrument against which the strings vibrate.

add.definition_0: An act or instance of adding.
add.definition_1: An additional enemy that joins a fight after the primary target.

ace.definition_0: A single point or spot on a playing card or die.
ace.definition_1: A card or die face so marked.
ace.definition_2: The ball marked with the number 1 in pool and related games.

shirt.definition_0: An article of clothing that is worn on the upper part of the body, and often has sleeves, either long or short, that cover the arms.
shirt.definition_1: An interior lining in a blast furnace.
shirt.definition_2: A member of the shirt-wearing team in a shirts and skins game.

aid.definition_2: Something which helps; a material source of help.

while.definition_0: An uncertain duration of time, a period of time.

act.definition_2: Something done once and for all, as distinguished from a work.

tone.definition_1: (in the diatonic scale) An interval of a major second.
tone.definition_2: (in a Gregorian chant) A recitational melody.

phone.definition_0: A device for transmitting conversations and other sounds in real time across distances, now often a small portable unit also capable of running software etc.

watch.definition_1: The act of guarding and observing someone or something.
watch.definition_2: A particular time period when guarding is kept.

tame.definition_0: To make (an animal) tame; to domesticate.

rake.definition_0: A garden tool with a row of pointed teeth fixed to a long handle, used for collecting debris, grass, etc., for flattening the ground, or for loosening soil; also, a similar wheel-mounted tool drawn by a horse or a tractor.
rake.definition_1: (by extension) A similarly shaped tool used for other purposes.

take.definition_0: The or an act of taking.
take.definition_1: Something that is taken; a haul.
take.definition_2: An interpretation or view, opinion or assessment; perspective.

air.definition_0: The substance constituting earth's atmosphere, particularly:
air.definition_1: (usually with the) The apparently open space above the ground which this substance fills, formerly thought to be limited by the firmament but now considered to be surrounded by the near vacuum of outer space.

hand.definition_0: The part of the forelimb below the forearm or wrist in a human, and the corresponding part in many other animals.
hand.definition_1: That which resembles, or to some extent performs the office of, a human hand.

ant.definition_0: Any of various insects in the family Formicidae in the order Hymenoptera, typically living in large colonies composed almost entirely of flightless females.

any.definition_0: To even the slightest extent, at all.

awe.definition_0: A feeling of fear and reverence.

are.definition_0: An accepted (but deprecated and rarely used) SI unit of area equal to 100 square metres, or a former unit of approximately the same extent. Symbol: a.

awl.definition_0: A pointed instrument for piercing small holes, as in leather or wood; used by shoemakers, saddlers, cabinetmakers, etc. The blade is differently shaped and pointed for different uses, as in the brad awl, saddler's awl, shoemaker's awl, etc.

mom.definition_1: An adult female owner of a pet.

eel.definition_0: Any freshwater or marine fish of the order Anguilliformes, which are elongated and resemble snakes.

fad.definition_0: A phenomenon that becomes popular for a very short time.

arc.definition_0: That part of a circle which a heavenly body appears to pass through as it moves above and below the horizon.
