arc.definition_1: A continuous part of the circumference of a circle (circular arc) or of another curve.

bar.definition_0: A solid, more or less rigid object of metal or wood with a uniform cross-section smaller than its length.
bar.definition_1: A solid metal object with uniform (round, square, hexagonal, octagonal or rectangular) cross-section; in the US its smallest dimension is 1/4 inch or greater, a piece of thinner material being called a strip.
bar.definition_2: A cuboid piece of any solid commodity.

ape.definition_0: A primate of the clade Hominoidea, generally larger than monkeys and distinguished from them by having no tail.
ape.definition_1: Any such primate other than a human.

ban.definition_1: A public proclamation or edict; a summons by public proclamation. Chiefly, in early use, a summons to arms.
ban.definition_2: The gathering of the (French) king's vassals for war; the whole body of vassals so assembled, or liable to be summoned; originally, the same as arrière-ban: in the 16th c., French usage created a distinction between ban and arrière-ban, for which see the latter word.

beg.definition_0: The act of begging; an imploring request.

razor.definition_0: A keen-edged knife of peculiar shape, used in shaving the hair from the face or other parts of the body.
razor.definition_1: Any tool or instrument designed for shaving.
razor.definition_2: The sharp tusk of a wild boar.

bay.definition_1: Laurus nobilis, a tree or shrub of the family Lauraceae, having dark green leaves and berries.
bay.definition_2: Bay leaf, the leaf of this or certain other species of tree or shrub, used as a herb.

bat.definition_0: Any of the flying mammals of the order Chiroptera, usually small and nocturnal, insectivorous or frugivorous.

cap.definition_0: A close-fitting hat, either brimless or peaked.
cap.definition_1: A special hat to indicate rank, occupation, etc.

ark.definition_0: A large box with a flat lid.
ark.definition_1: Noah's Ark: the ship built by Noah to save his family and a collection of animals from the deluge.
ark.definition_2: Something affording protection; safety, shelter, refuge

bun.definition_0: A small bread roll, often sweetened or spiced.
bun.definition_1: A tight roll of hair worn at the back of the head.

cup.definition_0: A concave vessel for drinking from, usually made of opaque material (as opposed to a glass) and with a handle.
cup.definition_1: The contents of said vessel; a cupful.

bin.definition_0: A box, frame, crib, or enclosed place, used as a storage container.
bin.definition_1: A container for rubbish or waste.
bin.definition_2: Any of the discrete intervals in a histogram, etc

bad.definition_1: An item (or kind of item) of merchandise with negative value; an unwanted good.

bid.definition_0: To issue a command; to tell.
bid.definition_2: To utter a greeting or salutation.

dad.definition_2: Used to address an older adult male

bag.definition_0: A flexible container made of cloth, paper, plastic, etc.

cut.definition_2: An opening resulting from cutting; an incision or wound.

cry.definition_0: A shedding of tears; the act of crying.

owl.definition_0: Any of various birds of prey of the order Strigiformes that are primarily nocturnal and have forward-looking, binocular vision, limited eye movement, and good hearing.
owl.definition_1: (by extension) A person seen as having owl-like characteristics, especially appearing wise or serious, or being nocturnally active.

haunt.definition_0: A place at which one is regularly found; a habitation or hangout.

bow.definition_0: A weapon made of a curved piece of wood or other flexible material whose ends are connected by a string, used for shooting arrows.
bow.definition_1: A curved bend in a rod or planar surface, or in a linear formation such as a river (see oxbow).
bow.definition_2: A rod with horsehair (or an artificial substitute) stretched between the ends, used for playing various stringed musical instruments.

dew.definition_0: Any moisture from the atmosphere condensed by cool bodies upon their surfaces.
dew.definition_1: Moisture in the air that settles on plants, etc in the morning, resulting in drops.
dew.definition_2: (but see usage notes) An instance of such moisture settling on plants, etc.

bug.definition_0: An insect of the order Hemiptera (the “true bugs”).
bug.definition_1: Any of various species of marine or freshwater crustaceans; e.g. a Morton Bay bug, mudbug.
bug.definition_2: Any insect, arachnid, or other terrestrial arthropod that is a pest.

den.definition_0: A small cavern or hollow place in the side of a hill, or among rocks; especially, a cave used by a wild animal for shelter or concealment.
den.definition_1: A squalid or wretched place; a haunt.
den.definition_2: A comfortable room not used for formal entertaining.

day.definition_1: A period from midnight to the following midnight.
day.definition_2: Rotational period of a planet (especially Earth).

bus.definition_0: A motor vehicle for transporting large numbers of people along roads.
bus.definition_1: An electrical conductor or interface serving as a common connection for two or more circuits or components.

ash.definition_0: The solid remains of a fire.
ash.definition_1: The nonaqueous remains of a material subjected to any complete oxidation process.
ash.definition_2: Fine particles from a volcano, volcanic ash.

bed.definition_0: A piece of furniture, usually flat and soft, on which to rest or sleep.
bed.definition_1: A place, or flat surface or layer, on which something else rests or is laid.

big.definition_0: Someone or something that is large in stature
big.definition_1: An important or powerful person; a celebrity; a big name.
big.definition_2: (as plural) The big leagues, big time.

boy.definition_1: (diminutive) A male child: a son of any age.
boy.definition_2: (diminutive) A male of any age, particularly one rather younger than the speaker.

ego.definition_0: The self, especially with a sense of self-importance.
ego.definition_1: (Freudian) The most central part of the mind, which mediates with one's surroundings.

chasm.definition_0: A deep, steep-sided rift, gap or fissure; a gorge or abyss.
chasm.definition_1: (by extension) A large difference of opinion.

fazed.definition_0: To frighten or cause hesitation; to daunt, put off (usually used in the negative); to disconcert, to perturb.

whet.definition_1: That which whets or sharpens; especially, an appetizer.

ale.definition_1: A beer produced by so-called warm fermentation and not pressurized.
ale.definition_2: A festival in English country places, so called from the liquor drunk.

phlox.definition_0: Any flowering plant of the genus Phlox.

bocce.definition_0: A game, similar to bowls or pétanque, played on a long, narrow, dirt-covered court
bocce.definition_1: One of the eight balls that the player throws in a game of bocce.

gulch.definition_0: A ravine-like or deep V-shaped valley, often eroded by flash floods; shallower than a canyon and deeper than a gully.
gulch.definition_1: An act of gulching or gulping.

tweed.definition_0: A coarse woolen fabric used for clothing.

fetid.definition_0: The foul-smelling asafoetida plant, or its extracts.

ogle.definition_0: An impertinent, flirtatious, amorous or covetous stare.

lodge.definition_0: A building for recreational use such as a hunting lodge or a summer cabin.
lodge.definition_1: Short for porter's lodge: a building or room near the entrance of an estate or building, especially as a college mailroom.
lodge.definition_2: A local chapter of some fraternities, such as freemasons.

dig.definition_0: An archeological or paleontological investigation, or the site where such an investigation is taking place.

dip.definition_0: A lower section of a road or geological feature.
dip.definition_1: Inclination downward; direction below a horizontal line; slope; pitch.
dip.definition_2: The action of dipping or plunging for a moment into a liquid.

dot.definition_1: (grammar) A punctuation mark used to indicate the end of a sentence or an abbreviated part of a word; a full stop; a period.
dot.definition_2: A point used as a diacritical mark above or below various letters of the Latin script, as in Ȧ, Ạ, Ḅ, Ḃ, Ċ.

faint.definition_1: The state of one who has fainted; a swoon.

due.definition_2: That which is owed; debt; that which belongs or may be claimed as a right; whatever custom, law, or morality requires to be done, duty.

doe.definition_0: A female deer; also used of similar animals such as antelope, (less commonly goat as nanny is also used).

dark.definition_0: Having an absolute or (more often) relative lack of light.
dark.definition_1: (of colour) Dull or deeper in hue; not bright or light.

point.definition_2: One of the several different parts of the escutcheon.

elf.definition_0: A luminous spirit presiding over nature and fertility and dwelling in the world of Álfheim (Elfland). Compare angel, nymph, fairy.
elf.definition_1: Any from a race of mythical, supernatural beings resembling but seen as distinct from human beings. They are usually delicate-featured and skilled in magic or spellcrafting; sometimes depicted as clashing with dwarves, especially in modern fantasy literature.
elf.definition_2: Any of the magical, typically forest-guarding races bearing some similarities to the Norse álfar (through Tolkien's Eldar).

egg.definition_0: An approximately spherical or ellipsoidal body produced by birds, reptiles, insects and other animals, housing the embryo during its development.
egg.definition_1: The egg of a domestic fowl (especially a hen) or its contents, used as food.
egg.definition_2: The female primary cell, the ovum.

dye.definition_0: A colourant, especially one that has an affinity to the substrate to which it is applied.

fur.definition_0: The hairy coat of various mammal species, especially when fine, soft and thick.
fur.definition_1: The hairy skin of an animal processed into clothing for humans.
fur.definition_2: A pelt used to make, trim or line clothing apparel.

fog.definition_0: A thick cloud that forms near the ground; the obscurity of such a cloud.
fog.definition_1: A mist or film clouding a surface.
fog.definition_2: A state of mind characterized by lethargy and confusion.

fly.definition_0: Any insect of the order Diptera; characterized by having two wings (except for some wingless species), also called true flies.
fly.definition_1: (non-technical) Especially, any of the insects of the family Muscidae, such as the common housefly (other families of Diptera include mosquitoes and midges).
fly.definition_2: Any similar, but unrelated insect such as dragonfly or butterfly.

fig.definition_0: A fruit-bearing tree or shrub of the genus Ficus that is native mainly to the tropics.
fig.definition_1: The fruit of the fig tree, pear-shaped and containing many small seeds.

fit.definition_0: The degree to which something fits.
fit.definition_1: Conformity of elements one to another.
fit.definition_2: The part of an object upon which anything fits tightly.

fee.definition_0: (feudal law) A right to the use of a superior's land, as a stipend for services to be performed; also, the land so held; a fief.
fee.definition_1: An inheritable estate in land held of a feudal lord on condition of the performing of certain services.
fee.definition_2: An estate of inheritance in land, either absolute and without limitation to any particular class of heirs (fee simple) or limited to a particular class of heirs (fee tail).

craze.definition_1: A strong habitual desire or fancy.
craze.definition_2: A temporary passion or infatuation, as for some new amusement, pursuit, or fashion; a fad

eat.definition_0: Something to be eaten; a meal; a food item.

eye.definition_0: An organ through which animals see (perceive surroundings via light).
eye.definition_2: The iris of the eye, being of a specified colour.

fan.definition_0: A hand-held device consisting of concertinaed material, or slats of material, gathered together at one end, that may be opened out into the shape of a sector of a circle and waved back and forth in order to move air towards oneself and cool oneself.
fan.definition_1: An electrical or mechanical device for moving air, used for cooling people, machinery, etc.
fan.definition_2: The action of fanning; agitation of the air.

elk.definition_0: Any of various large species of deer such as the red deer, moose or wapiti (see usage notes).

delay.definition_0: A period of time before an event occurs; the act of delaying; procrastination; lingering inactivity.
delay.definition_1: An audio effects unit that introduces a controlled delay.

ear.definition_0: The organ of hearing, consisting of the pinna, auditory canal, eardrum, malleus, incus, stapes and cochlea.
ear.definition_1: The external part of the organ of hearing, the auricle.

gin.definition_0: A colourless non-aged alcoholic liquor made by distilling fermented grains such as barley, corn, oats or rye with juniper berries; the base for many cocktails.
gin.definition_2: Drawing the best card or combination of cards.

rival.definition_0: A competitor (person, team, company, etc.) with the same goal as another, or striving to attain the same thing. Defeating a rival may be a primary or necessary goal of a competitor.
rival.definition_1: Someone or something with similar claims of quality or distinction as another.
rival.definition_2: One having a common right or privilege with another; a partner.

enemy.definition_0: Someone who is hostile to, feels hatred towards, opposes the interests of, or intends injury to someone else.
enemy.definition_1: A hostile force or nation; a fighting member of such a force or nation.
enemy.definition_2: Something harmful or threatening to another

gap.definition_0: An opening in anything made by breaking or parting.
gap.definition_1: An opening allowing passage or entrance.
gap.definition_2: An opening that implies a breach or defect.

crowd.definition_0: A group of people congregated or collected into a close body without order.
crowd.definition_1: Several things collected or closely pressed together; also, some things adjacent to each other.
crowd.definition_2: (with definite article) The so-called lower orders of people; the populace, vulgar.

pause.definition_0: A button whose functions are pausing and resuming something, such as a DVD player, a video game or a computer.

nest.definition_0: A structure built by a bird as a place to incubate eggs and rear young.
nest.definition_1: A place used by another mammal, fish, amphibian or insect, for depositing eggs and hatching young.
nest.definition_2: A snug, comfortable, or cosy residence or job situation.

basis.definition_1: A starting point, base or foundation for an argument or hypothesis.

enjoy.definition_0: To receive pleasure or satisfaction from something
enjoy.definition_1: To have the use or benefit of something.
enjoy.definition_2: To be satisfied or receive pleasure.

boast.definition_0: A brag; ostentatious positive appraisal of oneself.
boast.definition_2: A shot where the ball is driven off a side wall and then strikes the front wall.

gas.definition_0: Matter in a state intermediate between liquid and plasma that can be contained only if it is fully surrounded by a solid (or in a bubble of liquid) (or held together by gravitational pull); it can condense into a liquid, or can (rarely) become a solid directly.
gas.definition_1: A chemical element or compound in such a state.
gas.definition_2: A flammable gaseous hydrocarbon or hydrocarbon mixture (typically predominantly methane) used as a fuel, e.g. for cooking, heating, electricity generation or as a fuel in internal combustion engines in vehicles.

tooth.definition_0: A hard, calcareous structure present in the mouth of many vertebrate animals, generally used for eating.
tooth.definition_1: A sharp projection on the blade of a saw or similar implement.
tooth.definition_2: A projection on the edge of a gear that meshes with similar projections on adjacent gears, or on the circumference of a cog that engages with a chain.

brand.definition_1: A piece of burning wood or peat, or a glowing cinder.

fry.definition_0: (usually in the plural, fries) A fried strip of potato.
fry.definition_1: A meal of fried sausages, bacon, eggs, etc.

wash.definition_0: The process or an instance of washing or being washed by water or other liquid.
wash.definition_2: A lotion or other liquid with medicinal or hygienic properties.

open.definition_1: Not physically drawn together, closed, folded or contracted; extended
open.definition_2: Actively conducting or prepared to conduct business.

right.definition_1: Of an angle, having a size of 90 degrees, or one quarter of a complete rotation; the angle between two perpendicular lines.
right.definition_2: Of a geometric figure, incorporating a right angle between edges, faces, axes, etc.

punch.definition_0: A hit or strike with one's fist.

bleat.definition_0: The characteristic cry of a sheep or a goat.

brag.definition_0: A boast or boasting; bragging; ostentatious pretence or self-glorification.
brag.definition_1: The thing which is boasted of.
brag.definition_2: (by ellipsis) The card game three card brag.

salon.definition_0: A large room, especially one used to receive and entertain guests.
salon.definition_1: A gathering of people for a social or intellectual meeting.
salon.definition_2: An art gallery or exhibition; especially the Paris salon or autumn salon.

art.definition_0: The conscious production or arrangement of sounds, colours, forms, movements, or other elements in a manner that affects the senses and emotions, usually specifically the production of the beautiful in a graphic or plastic medium.
art.definition_1: The creative and emotional expression of mental imagery, such as visual, auditory, social, etc.
art.definition_2: Skillful creative activity, usually with an aesthetic focus.

clown.definition_0: A slapstick performance artist often associated with a circus and usually characterized by bright, oversized clothing, a red nose, face paint, and a brightly colored wig.
clown.definition_1: A person who acts in a silly fashion.

arm.definition_0: The portion of the upper human appendage, from the shoulder to the wrist and sometimes including the hand.
arm.definition_1: The extended portion of the upper limb, from the shoulder to the elbow.
arm.definition_2: A limb, or locomotive or prehensile organ, of an invertebrate animal.

swarf.definition_0: The waste chips or shavings from an abrasive activity, such as metalworking, a saw cutting wood, or the use of a grindstone or whetstone.
swarf.definition_1: A particular waste chip or shaving.

twirl.definition_0: A movement where a person spins round elegantly; a pirouette.
twirl.definition_2: A little twist of some substance; a swirl.

vain.definition_0: Overly proud of oneself, especially concerning appearance; having a high opinion of one's own accomplishments with slight reason.
vain.definition_1: Having no real substance, value, or importance; empty; void; worthless; unsatisfying.

pulp.definition_0: A soft, moist, shapeless mass or matter.
pulp.definition_1: A magazine or book containing lurid subject matter and characteristically printed on rough, unfinished paper.

all.definition_0: (with a possessive pronoun) Everything that one is capable of.

wound.definition_0: An injury, such as a cut, stab, or tear, to a (usually external) part of the body.
wound.definition_1: A hurt to a person's feelings, reputation, prospects, etc.
wound.definition_2: An injury to a person by which the skin is divided or its continuity broken.

final.definition_0: A final examination; a test or examination given at the end of a term or class; the test that concludes a class.
final.definition_1: The last round, game or match in a contest, after which the winner is determined.
final.definition_2: A contest that narrows a field of contestants (finalists) to ranked positions, usually in numbered places (1st place/prize, 2nd place/prize, etc.) or a winner and numbered runners-up (1st runner-up, etc.).

charm.definition_0: An object, act or words believed to have magic power (usually carries a positive connotation).
charm.definition_1: The ability to persuade, delight or arouse admiration; often constructed in the plural.
charm.definition_2: A small trinket on a bracelet or chain, etc., traditionally supposed to confer luck upon the wearer.

bright.definition_0: An artist's brush used in oil and acrylic painting with a long ferrule and a flat, somewhat tapering bristle head.
bright.definition_2: A person with a naturalistic worldview with no supernatural or mystical elements.

grand.definition_0: (plural "grand") A thousand of some unit of currency, such as dollars or pounds. (Compare G.)

throw.definition_1: To change in state or status

vocal.definition_0: A vocal sound; specifically, a purely vocal element of speech, unmodified except by resonance; a vowel or a diphthong; a tonic element; a tonic; distinguished from a subvocal, and a nonvocal
vocal.definition_1: (Roman Catholic Church) A man who has a right to vote in certain elections.

magic.definition_0: The application of rituals or actions, especially those based on occult knowledge, to subdue or manipulate natural or supernatural beings and forces in order to have some benefit from them
magic.definition_1: A specific ritual or procedure associated with such magic; a spell.
magic.definition_2: The supernatural forces which are drawn on in such a ritual

noble.definition_0: An aristocrat; one of aristocratic blood.
noble.definition_1: A medieval gold coin of England in the 14th and 15th centuries, usually valued at 6s 8d.

badge.definition_0: A distinctive mark, token, sign, emblem or cognizance, worn on one's clothing, as an insignia of some rank, or of the membership of an organization.
badge.definition_1: A small nameplate, identifying the wearer, and often giving additional information.
badge.definition_2: A card, sometimes with a barcode or magnetic strip, granting access to a certain area.

drone.definition_0: A male ant, bee or wasp, which does not work but can fertilize the queen bee.
drone.definition_1: Someone who does not work; a lazy person, an idler.
drone.definition_2: One who performs menial or tedious work.

steam.definition_0: The vapor formed when water changes from liquid phase to gas phase.
steam.definition_1: Pressurized water vapour used for heating, cooking, or to provide mechanical energy.

proud.definition_0: Feeling honoured (by something); feeling happy or satisfied about an event or fact; gratified.
proud.definition_1: Possessed of a due sense of what one deserves or is worth.
proud.definition_2: Having too high an opinion of oneself; arrogant, supercilious.

petit.definition_0: (usually in the plural) A little schoolboy.

blood.definition_0: A member of the Los Angeles gang The Bloods.

nurse.definition_1: A person (usually a woman) who takes care of other people’s young.
nurse.definition_2: A person trained to provide care for the sick.

burly.definition_0: (usually of a man) Large, well-built, and muscular.
burly.definition_1: (East End of London) Great, amazing, unbelievable.
burly.definition_2: (surf culture and/or Southern California) Of large magnitude, either good or bad, and sometimes both.

lymph.definition_1: A colourless, watery bodily fluid, carried by the lymphatic system, that consists mainly of white blood cells.
lymph.definition_2: Discharge from a sore, inflammation etc.

salad.definition_0: A food made primarily of a mixture of raw or cold ingredients, typically vegetables, usually served with a dressing such as vinegar or mayonnaise.
salad.definition_1: A raw vegetable of the kind used in salads.

unzip.definition_0: To open something using a zipper.
unzip.definition_1: To come open by means of a zipper.

elite.definition_0: A special group or social class of people which have a superior intellectual, social or economic status as, the elite of society.
elite.definition_1: Someone who is among the best at a certain task.

vogue.definition_2: A highly stylized modern dance that evolved out of the Harlem ballroom scene in the 1960s.

friar.definition_0: A member of a mendicant Christian order such as the Augustinians, Carmelites (white friars), Franciscans (grey friars) or the Dominicans (black friars).
friar.definition_1: A white or pale patch on a printed page.

quash.definition_1: To crush or dash to pieces.
quash.definition_2: To void or suppress (a subpoena, decision, etc.).

tulip.definition_0: A type of flowering plant, genus Tulipa.

kohl.definition_0: A dark powder (usually powdered antimony) used as eye makeup, especially in Eastern countries; stibnite.

peat.definition_0: Soil formed of dead but not fully decayed plants found in bog areas, often burned as fuel.

movie.definition_0: A recorded sequence of images displayed on a screen at a rate sufficiently fast to create the appearance of motion.

odor.definition_0: Any smell, whether fragrant or offensive.

waive.definition_0: To relinquish (a right etc.); to give up claim to; to forego.

gauze.definition_0: A thin fabric with a loose, open weave.
gauze.definition_1: A similar bleached cotton fabric used as a surgical dressing.
gauze.definition_2: A thin woven metal or plastic mesh.

hair.definition_0: A pigmented filament of keratin which grows from a follicle on the skin of humans and other mammals.
hair.definition_1: The collection or mass of such growths growing from the skin of humans and animals, and forming a covering for a part of the head or for any part or the whole body.
hair.definition_2: A slender outgrowth from the chitinous cuticle of insects, spiders, crustaceans, and other invertebrates. Such hairs are totally unlike those of vertebrates in structure, composition, and mode of growth.

taste.definition_0: One of the sensations produced by the tongue in response to certain chemicals; the quality of giving this sensation.
taste.definition_1: The sense that consists in the perception and interpretation of this sensation.
taste.definition_2: A small sample of food, drink, or recreational drugs.

ocean.definition_0: One of the large bodies of water separating the continents.
ocean.definition_2: An immense expanse; any vast space or quantity without apparent limits.

mount.definition_1: Any of seven fleshy prominences in the palm of the hand, taken to represent the influences of various heavenly bodies.
mount.definition_2: A bulwark for offence or defence; a mound.

wine.definition_0: An alcoholic beverage made by fermenting the juice of grapes.
wine.definition_1: An alcoholic beverage made by fermenting the juice of fruits or vegetables other than grapes, usually preceded by the type of the fruit or vegetable; for example, "dandelion wine".

rebel.definition_0: A person who resists an established authority, often violently
rebel.definition_1: A person from the Confederate States of America

pants.definition_0: (Manchester) An outer garment that covers the body from the waist downwards, covering each leg separately, usually as far as the ankles; trousers.
pants.definition_1: An undergarment that covers the genitals and often the buttocks and the neighbouring parts of the body; underpants.

prior.definition_0: A high-ranking member of a monastery, usually lower in rank than an abbot.
prior.definition_2: (law enforcement) A previous arrest or criminal conviction on someone's record.

nerve.definition_0: A bundle of neurons with their connective tissue sheaths, blood vessels and lymphatics.
nerve.definition_2: A vein in a leaf; a grain in wood

lunge.definition_0: A sudden forward movement, especially with a sword.
lunge.definition_1: A long rope or flat web line, more commonly referred to as a lunge line, approximately 20–30 feet long, attached to the bridle, lungeing cavesson, or halter of a horse and used to control the animal while lungeing.
lunge.definition_2: An exercise performed by stepping forward one leg while kneeling with the other leg, then returning to a standing position.

shoal.definition_0: A sandbank or sandbar creating a shallow.
shoal.definition_1: A shallow in a body of water.

perch.definition_0: Any of the three species of spiny-finned freshwater fish in the genus Perca.
perch.definition_1: Any of the about 200 related species of fish in the taxonomic family Percidae, especially:
perch.definition_2: Several similar species in the order Perciformes, such as the grouper.

axe.definition_0: A tool for felling trees or chopping wood etc. consisting of a heavy head flattened to a blade on one side, and a handle attached to it.
axe.definition_1: An ancient weapon consisting of a head that has one or two blades and a long handle.

fume.definition_0: A gas or vapour/vapor that is strong-smelling or dangerous to inhale.
fume.definition_1: A material that has been vaporized from the solid or liquid state to the gas state and re-coalesced to the solid state.
fume.definition_2: Rage or excitement which deprives the mind of self-control.

speed.definition_0: The state of moving quickly or the capacity for rapid motion; rapidity.
speed.definition_1: The rate of motion or action, specifically / the magnitude of the velocity; the rate distance is traversed in a given time.
speed.definition_2: The sensitivity to light of film, plates or sensor.

moss.definition_0: Any of various small, green, seedless plants growing on the ground or on the surfaces of trees, stones, etc.; now specifically, a plant of the phylum Bryophyta (formerly division Musci).
moss.definition_1: A kind or species of such plants.
moss.definition_2: Any alga, lichen, bryophyte, or other plant of seemingly simple structure.

spill.definition_0: A mess of something that has been dropped.
spill.definition_2: A small stick or piece of paper used to light a candle, cigarette etc by the transfer of a flame from a fire.

stern.definition_0: Having a hardness and severity of nature or manner.

radio.definition_0: The technology that allows for the transmission of sound or other signals by modulation of electromagnetic waves.
radio.definition_1: A device that can capture (receive) the signal sent over radio waves and render the modulated signal as sound.
radio.definition_2: On-board entertainment system in a car, usually including a radio receiver as well as the capability to play audio from recorded media.

pure.definition_0: One who, or that which, is pure.

dive.definition_0: A jump or plunge into water.
dive.definition_1: A headfirst jump toward the ground or into another substance.

skin.definition_0: The outer protective layer of the body of any animal, including of a human.
skin.definition_1: The outer protective layer of the fruit of a plant.
skin.definition_2: The skin and fur of an individual animal used by humans for clothing, upholstery, etc.

spend.definition_0: Amount of money spent (during a period); expenditure.
spend.definition_1: (in the plural) Expenditures; money or pocket money.

budge.definition_2: To yield in one’s opinions or beliefs.

seem.definition_0: To appear; to look outwardly; to be perceived as.

poll.definition_0: A survey of people, usually statistically analyzed to gauge wider public opinion.
poll.definition_2: A polling place (usually as plural, polling places)

hay.definition_0: Grass cut and dried for use as animal fodder.
hay.definition_1: Any mix of green leafy plants used for fodder.

basic.definition_0: A necessary commodity, a staple requirement.
basic.definition_1: An elementary building block, e.g. a fundamental piece of knowledge.

hobby.definition_0: An activity that one enjoys doing in one's spare time.
hobby.definition_1: An extinct breed of horse native to the British Isles, also known as the Irish Hobby

spite.definition_0: Ill will or hatred toward another, accompanied with the desire to irritate, annoy, or thwart; a want to disturb or put out another; mild malice

shout.definition_0: A loud burst of voice or voices; a violent and sudden outcry, especially that of a multitude expressing joy, triumph, exultation, anger, or animated courage.
shout.definition_1: A round of drinks in a pub; the turn to pay the shot or scot; an act of paying for a round of drinks.
shout.definition_2: A call-out for an emergency services team.

toast.definition_1: A proposed salutation (e.g. to say "cheers") while drinking alcohol.
toast.definition_2: A person, group, or notable object to which a salutation with alcohol is made; a person or group held in similar esteem.

camp.definition_0: An outdoor place acting as temporary accommodation in tents or other temporary structures.
camp.definition_1: An organised event, often taking place in tents or temporary accommodation.
camp.definition_2: A base of a military group, not necessarily temporary.

year.definition_0: A solar year, the time it takes the Earth to complete one revolution of the Sun (between 365.24 and 365.26 days depending on the point of reference).
year.definition_1: (by extension) The time it takes for any astronomical object (such as a planet, dwarf planet, small Solar System body, or comet) in direct orbit around a star (such as the Sun) to make one revolution around the star.
year.definition_2: A period between set dates that mark a year, from January 1 to December 31 by the Gregorian calendar, from Tishiri 1 to Elul 29 by the Jewish calendar, and from Muharram 1 to Dhu al-Hijjah 29 or 30 by the Islamic calendar.

nail.definition_0: The thin, horny plate at the ends of fingers and toes on humans and some other animals.
nail.definition_1: The basal thickened portion of the anterior wings of certain hemiptera.
nail.definition_2: The terminal horny plate on the beak of ducks, and other allied birds.

head.definition_0: The part of the body of an animal or human which contains the brain, mouth and main sense organs.
head.definition_1: The topmost, foremost, or leading part.

chain.definition_0: A series of interconnected rings or links usually made of metal.
chain.definition_2: A series of stores or businesses with the same brand name.

word.definition_0: The smallest unit of language that has a particular meaning and can be expressed by itself; the smallest discrete, meaningful unit of language. (contrast morpheme.)
word.definition_1: Something like such a unit of language:
word.definition_2: The fact or act of speaking, as opposed to taking action. .

flour.definition_0: Powder obtained by grinding or milling cereal grains, especially wheat, or other foodstuffs such as soybeans and potatoes, and used to bake bread, cakes, and pastry.
flour.definition_1: The food made by grinding and bolting cleaned wheat (not durum or red durum) until it meets specified levels of fineness, dryness and freedom from bran and germ, also containing any of certain enzymes, ascorbic acid and certain bleaching agents.

page.definition_0: One of the many pieces of paper bound together within a book or similar document.
page.definition_1: One side of a paper leaf on which one has written or printed.
page.definition_2: Any record or writing; a collective memory.

bang.definition_1: A strike upon an object causing such a noise.

pool.definition_0: A small and rather deep collection of (usually) fresh water, as one supplied by a spring, or occurring in the course of a stream; a reservoir for water.
pool.definition_1: A small body of standing or stagnant water; a puddle.

groan.definition_0: A low, mournful sound uttered in pain or grief.
groan.definition_1: A low, guttural sound uttered in frustration, disapproval, or ecstasy.
groan.definition_2: (of an object) A low creaking sound from applied pressure or weight.

evoke.definition_0: To call out; to draw out or bring forth.
evoke.definition_1: To cause the manifestation of something (emotion, picture, etc.) in someone's mind or imagination.

self.definition_0: One individual's personality, character, demeanor, or disposition.
self.definition_1: The subject of one's own experience of phenomena: perception, emotions, thoughts.
self.definition_2: An individual person as the object of his own reflective consciousness (plural selves).

hour.definition_0: A time period of sixty minutes; one twenty-fourth of a day.

debt.definition_0: An action, state of mind, or object one has an obligation to perform for another, adopt toward another, or give to another.
debt.definition_1: The state or condition of owing something to another.
debt.definition_2: Money that one person or entity owes or is required to pay to another, generally as a result of a loan or other financial transaction.

carry.definition_0: A manner of transporting or lifting something; the grip or position in which something is carried.
carry.definition_1: A tract of land over which boats or goods are carried between two bodies of navigable water; a portage.
carry.definition_2: The bit or digit that is carried in an addition operation.

greet.definition_0: To welcome in a friendly manner, either in person or through another means e.g. writing or over the phone/internet
greet.definition_1: To arrive at or reach, or meet (talking of something which brings joy)

reach.definition_0: The act of stretching or extending; extension.
reach.definition_1: The ability to reach or touch with the person, a limb, or something held or thrown.
reach.definition_2: The power of stretching out or extending action, influence, or the like; power of attainment or management; extent of force or capacity.

bulb.definition_0: Any solid object rounded at one end and tapering on the other, possibly attached to a larger object at the tapered end.
bulb.definition_2: The bulb-shaped root portion of a plant such as a tulip, from which the rest of the plant may be regrown.

deny.definition_1: To assert that something is not true.
deny.definition_2: (ditransitive) To refuse to give or grant something to someone.

side.definition_0: A bounding straight edge of a two-dimensional shape.
side.definition_1: A flat surface of a three-dimensional object; a face.
side.definition_2: One half (left or right, top or bottom, front or back, etc.) of something or someone.

pack.definition_0: A bundle made up and prepared to be carried; especially, a bundle to be carried on the back, but also a load for an animal, a bale.
pack.definition_1: A number or quantity equal to the contents of a pack

fall.definition_0: The act of moving to a lower position under the effect of gravity.
fall.definition_1: A reduction in quantity, pitch, etc.
fall.definition_2: The time of the year when the leaves typically fall from the trees; autumn; the season of the year between the autumnal equinox and the winter solstice.

toss.definition_0: A throw, a lob, of a ball etc., with an initial upward direction, particularly with a lack of care.
toss.definition_1: The coin toss before a cricket match in order to decide who bats first, or before a football match in order to decide the direction of play.
toss.definition_2: A haughty throwing up of the head.

last.definition_0: Final, ultimate, coming after all others of its kind.
last.definition_1: Most recent, latest, last so far.
last.definition_2: Farthest of all from a given quality, character, or condition; most unlikely, or least preferable.

abbey.definition_0: The office or dominion of an abbot or abbess.
abbey.definition_1: A monastery or society of people, secluded from the world and devoted to religion and celibacy, which is headed by an abbot or abbess; also, the monastic building or buildings.

quota.definition_0: A proportional part or share; the share or proportion assigned to each in a division.
quota.definition_1: A prescribed number or percentage that may serve as, for example, a maximum, a minimum, or a goal.
quota.definition_2: A restriction on the import of something to a specific quantity.

arch.definition_1: An arch-shaped arrangement of trapezoidal stones, designed to redistribute downward force outward.
arch.definition_2: An architectural element having the shape of an arch

solve.definition_0: (chiefly law enforcement) A solution; an explanation.

soul.definition_0: The spirit or essence of a person usually thought to consist of one's thoughts and personality. Often believed to live on after the person's death.
soul.definition_1: The spirit or essence of anything.

storm.definition_0: Any disturbed state of the atmosphere, especially as affecting the earth's surface, and strongly implying destructive or unpleasant weather.
storm.definition_1: A violent agitation of human society; a civil, political, or domestic commotion; violent outbreak.
storm.definition_2: A wind scale for very strong wind, stronger than a gale, less than a hurricane (10 or higher on the Beaufort scale).

brain.definition_0: The control center of the central nervous system of an animal located in the skull which is responsible for perception, cognition, attention, memory, emotion, and action.

frog.definition_0: A small tailless amphibian of the order Anura that typically hops.
frog.definition_1: The part of a violin bow (or that of other similar string instruments such as the viola, cello and contrabass) located at the end held by the player, to which the horsehair is attached.
frog.definition_2: Road. Shorter, more common form of frog and toad.

view.definition_1: A picture, drawn or painted; a sketch.

hero.definition_0: Somebody who possesses great bravery and carries out extraordinary or noble deeds.
hero.definition_2: The protagonist in a work of fiction.

plead.definition_0: To present (an argument or a plea), especially in a legal case.
plead.definition_2: To offer by way of excuse.

attic.definition_0: The space, often unfinished and with sloped walls, directly below the roof in the uppermost part of a house or other building, generally used for storage or habitation.

agony.definition_1: The sufferings of Jesus Christ in the garden of Gethsemane.

jail.definition_0: A place or institution for the confinement of persons held in lawful custody or detention, especially for minor offenses or with reference to some future judicial proceeding.
jail.definition_2: The condition created by the requirement that a horse claimed in a claiming race not be run at another track for some period of time (usually 30 days).

index.definition_0: An alphabetical listing of items and their location.
index.definition_2: A movable finger on a gauge, scale, etc.

sheep.definition_0: A woolly ruminant of the genus Ovis.
sheep.definition_1: A timid, shy person who is easily led by others.
sheep.definition_2: (chiefly plural) A religious adherent, a member of a congregation or religious community (compare flock).

width.definition_1: The measurement of the extent of something from side to side.
width.definition_2: A piece of material measured along its smaller dimension, especially fabric.

copy.definition_0: The result of copying; an identical duplicate of an original.
copy.definition_1: An imitation, sometimes of inferior quality.
copy.definition_2: The text that is to be typeset.

jaw.definition_0: One of the bones, usually bearing teeth, which form the framework of the mouth.
jaw.definition_1: The part of the face below the mouth.
jaw.definition_2: Anything resembling the jaw of an animal in form or action; especially plural, the mouth or way of entrance.

outer.definition_1: The 4th circle on a target, outside the inner and magpie.
outer.definition_2: A shot which strikes the outer of a target.

joy.definition_0: A feeling of extreme happiness or cheerfulness, especially related to the acquisition or expectation of something good.
joy.definition_1: Anything that causes such a feeling.
joy.definition_2: Luck or success; a positive outcome.

jewel.definition_0: A precious or semi-precious stone; gem, gemstone.
jewel.definition_1: A valuable object used for personal ornamentation, especially one made of precious metals and stones; a piece of jewellery.

tax.definition_0: Money paid to the government other than for transaction-specific goods and services.
tax.definition_2: A task exacted from one who is under control; a contribution or service, the rendering of which is imposed upon a subject.

jury.definition_0: A group of individuals chosen from the general population to hear and decide a case in a court of law.
jury.definition_1: A group of judges in a competition.
jury.definition_2: The audience attending the first night of a performance, whose reaction may determine whether it succeeds or fails.

rugby.definition_0: (usually uncountable) A form of football in which players can hold or kick an ovoid ball. The ball cannot be handled forwards and points are scored by touching the ball to the ground in the area past their opponent’s territory or kicking the ball between goalposts and over a crossbar.
rugby.definition_1: A loose fitting shirt with a collar, as worn by rugby players.

unity.definition_0: Oneness; the state or fact of being one undivided entity.
unity.definition_2: A single undivided thing, seen as complete in itself.

judge.definition_0: A public official whose duty it is to administer the law, especially by presiding over trials and rendering judgments; a justice.
judge.definition_1: A person who decides the fate of someone or something that has been called into question.
judge.definition_2: A person officiating at a sports event or similar.

ivory.definition_0: The hard white form of dentin which forms the tusks of elephants, walruses and other animals.
ivory.definition_1: A creamy white color, the color of ivory.
ivory.definition_2: Something made from or resembling ivory.

entry.definition_2: A doorway that provides a means of entering a building.

duty.definition_0: That which one is morally or legally obligated to do.
duty.definition_1: The state of being at work and responsible for or doing a particular task.
duty.definition_2: A tax placed on imports or exports; a tariff.

rally.definition_0: A public gathering or mass meeting that is not mainly a protest and is organized to inspire enthusiasm for a cause.
rally.definition_1: A protest or demonstration for or against something, but often with speeches and often without marching, especially in North America.
rally.definition_2: A sequence of strokes between serving and scoring a point.

mercy.definition_0: Relenting; forbearance to cause or allow harm to another.
mercy.definition_1: Forgiveness or compassion, especially toward those less fortunate.
mercy.definition_2: A tendency toward forgiveness, pity, or compassion.

jet.definition_0: A collimated stream, spurt or flow of liquid or gas from a pressurized container, an engine, etc.
jet.definition_1: A spout or nozzle for creating a jet of fluid.
jet.definition_2: A type of airplane using jet engines rather than propellers.

irony.definition_0: A statement that, when taken in context, may actually mean something different from, or the opposite of, what is written literally; the use of words expressing something other than their literal intention, often in a humorous context.
irony.definition_1: Dramatic irony: a theatrical effect in which the meaning of a situation, or some incongruity in the plot, is understood by the audience, but not by the characters in the play.
irony.definition_2: Ignorance feigned for the purpose of confounding or provoking an antagonist; Socratic irony.

ally.definition_0: A person, group, or state (etc) which is associated with another for a common cause; one united to another by treaty or common purpose; a confederate.
ally.definition_1: A person, group, concept (etc) which is associated with another as a helper; a supporter; an auxiliary.
ally.definition_2: Anything akin to something else by structure, etc.

fairy.definition_0: The realm of faerie; enchantment, illusion.
fairy.definition_1: A mythical being with magical powers, known in many sizes and descriptions, although often depicted in modern illustrations only as a small sprite with gauze-like wings, and revered in some modern forms of paganism.
fairy.definition_2: An enchantress, or creature of overpowering charm.

navy.definition_0: A country's entire sea force, including ships and personnel.
navy.definition_1: A governmental department in charge of a country's sea force.
navy.definition_2: A dark blue colour, usually called navy blue.

dairy.definition_0: (also dairy products or dairy produce) Products produced from milk.

tasty.definition_0: Having a pleasant or satisfying flavor; delicious.
tasty.definition_1: Having or showing good taste; tasteful.
tasty.definition_2: Appealing; when applied to persons, sexually appealing.

drama.definition_0: A composition, normally in prose, telling a story and intended to be represented by actors impersonating the characters and speaking the dialogue
drama.definition_1: Such a work for television, radio or the cinema (usually one that is not a comedy)

essay.definition_0: (authorship) A written composition of moderate length, exploring a particular issue or subject.

area.definition_0: A measure of the extent of a surface; it is measured in square units.
area.definition_2: Any particular extent of surface, especially an empty or unused extent.

glory.definition_0: Great or overwhelming beauty or splendour.
glory.definition_1: Honour, admiration, or distinction, accorded by common consent to a person or thing; high reputation; renown.
glory.definition_2: That quality in a person or thing which secures general praise or honour.

dirty.definition_1: To stain or tarnish (somebody) with dishonor.
dirty.definition_2: To debase by distorting the real nature of (something).

hide.definition_0: To put (something) in a place where it will be harder to discover or out of sight.
hide.definition_1: To put oneself in a place where one will be harder to find or out of sight.

wire.definition_0: Metal formed into a thin, even thread, now usually by being drawn through a hole in a steel die.
wire.definition_1: A piece of such material; a thread or slender rod of metal, a cable.
wire.definition_2: A metal conductor that carries electricity.

old.definition_0: (with the, invariable plural only) People who are old; old beings; the older generation, taken as a group.
old.definition_1: (in combination) One of a specified age.
old.definition_2: A person older than oneself, especially an adult in relation to a teenager.

beard.definition_0: Facial hair on the chin, cheeks, jaw and neck.
beard.definition_1: The cluster of small feathers at the base of the beak in some birds.
beard.definition_2: The appendages to the jaw in some cetaceans, and to the mouth or jaws of some fishes.

child.definition_0: A person who has not yet reached adulthood, whether natural (puberty), cultural (initiation), or legal (majority)
child.definition_2: (with possessive) One's direct descendant by birth, regardless of age; a son or daughter.

lead.definition_0: A heavy, pliable, inelastic metal element, having a bright, bluish color, but easily tarnished; both malleable and ductile, though with little tenacity. It is easily fusible, forms alloys with other metals, and is an ingredient of solder and type metal. Atomic number 82, symbol Pb (from Latin plumbum).
lead.definition_1: A plummet or mass of lead attached to a line, used in sounding depth at sea or to estimate velocity in knots.
lead.definition_2: A thin strip of type metal, used to separate lines of type in printing.

read.definition_0: A reading or an act of reading, especially an actor's part of a play.
read.definition_1: (in combination) Something to be read; a written work.
read.definition_2: A person's interpretation or impression of something.

bland.definition_0: Having a soothing effect; not irritating or stimulating.
bland.definition_1: Lacking in taste, flavor, or vigor.

board.definition_0: A relatively long, wide and thin piece of any material, usually wood or similar, often for use in construction or furniture-making.
board.definition_1: A device (e.g., switchboard) containing electrical switches and other controls and designed to control lights, sound, telephone connections, etc.
board.definition_2: A flat surface with markings for playing a board game.

red.definition_0: Any of a range of colours having the longest wavelengths, 670 nm, of the visible spectrum; a primary additive colour for transmitted light: the colour obtained by subtracting green and blue from white light using magenta and yellow filters; the colour of blood, ripe strawberries, etc.
red.definition_1: A revolutionary socialist or (most commonly) a Communist; (usually capitalized) a Bolshevik, a supporter of the Bolsheviks in the Russian Civil War.
red.definition_2: One of the 15 red balls used in snooker, distinguished from the colours.

load.definition_0: A burden; a weight to be carried.
load.definition_1: A worry or concern to be endured, especially in the phrase a load off one's mind.
load.definition_2: A certain number of articles or quantity of material that can be transported or processed at one time.

stand.definition_2: A resolute, unwavering position; firm opinion; action for a purpose in the face of opposition.

blind.definition_0: A covering for a window to keep out light. The covering may be made of cloth or of narrow slats that can block light or allow it to pass.
blind.definition_1: A destination sign mounted on a public transport vehicle displaying the route destination, number, name and/or via points, etc.
blind.definition_2: Any device intended to conceal or hide.

flood.definition_0: A (usually disastrous) overflow of water from a lake or other body of water due to excessive rainfall or other input of water.
flood.definition_1: A large number or quantity of anything appearing more rapidly than can easily be dealt with.
flood.definition_2: The flowing in of the tide, opposed to the ebb.

find.definition_0: Anything that is found (usually valuable), as objects on an archeological site or a person with talent.

herd.definition_0: A number of domestic animals assembled together under the watch or ownership of a keeper.
herd.definition_1: Any collection of animals gathered or travelling in a company.
herd.definition_2: (now usually derogatory) A crowd, a mass of people; now usually pejorative: a rabble.

bond.definition_0: Evidence of a long-term debt, by which the bond issuer (the borrower) is obliged to pay interest when due, and repay the principal at maturity, as specified on the face of the bond certificate. The rights of the holder are specified in the bond indenture, which contains the legal terms and conditions under which the bond was issued. Bonds are available in two forms: registered bonds, and bearer bonds.
bond.definition_1: A documentary obligation to pay a sum or to perform a contract; a debenture.
bond.definition_2: A partial payment made to show a provider that the customer is sincere about buying a product or a service. If the product or service is not purchased the customer then forfeits the bond.

herb.definition_0: Any green, leafy plant, or parts thereof, used to flavour or season food.
herb.definition_1: A plant whose roots, leaves or seeds, etc. are used in medicine.

lamb.definition_1: The flesh of a lamb or sheep used as food.
lamb.definition_2: A person who is meek, docile and easily led.

rib.definition_0: Any of a series of long curved bones occurring in 12 pairs in humans and other animals and extending from the spine to or toward the sternum
rib.definition_1: A part or piece, similar to a rib, and serving to shape or support something
rib.definition_2: A cut of meat enclosing one or more rib bones

arena.definition_0: An enclosed area, often outdoor, for the presentation of sporting events (sports arena) or other spectacular events; earthen area, often oval, specifically for rodeos (North America) or circular area for bullfights (especially Hispanic America).
arena.definition_1: The building housing such an area; specifically, a very large, often round building, often topped with a dome, designated for indoor sporting or other major events, such as concerts.
arena.definition_2: The sand-covered centre of an amphitheatre where contests were held in Ancient Rome.

thumb.definition_0: The short thick digit of the hand that for humans has the most mobility and can be made to oppose (moved to touch) all of the other fingers.
thumb.definition_1: The part of a slider that may be moved linearly along the slider.

sofa.definition_0: A raised area of a building's floor, usually covered with carpeting, used for sitting.
sofa.definition_1: (furniture) An upholstered seat with a raised back and one or two raised ends, long enough to comfortably accommodate two or more people.

slab.definition_0: A large, flat piece of solid material; a solid object that is large and flat.
slab.definition_2: A carton containing 24 cans of beer.

snub.definition_1: A sudden checking of a cable or rope.
snub.definition_2: A knot; a protuberance; a snag.

opera.definition_0: A theatrical work, combining drama, music, song and sometimes dance.
opera.definition_1: The score for such a work.
opera.definition_2: A building designed for the performance of such works; an opera house.

climb.definition_1: The act of getting to somewhere more elevated.

idea.definition_0: An abstract archetype of a given thing, compared to which real-life examples are seen as imperfect approximations; pure essence, as opposed to actual examples.
idea.definition_1: The conception of someone or something as representing a perfect example; an ideal.
idea.definition_2: The form or shape of something; a quintessential aspect or characteristic.

hole.definition_0: A hollow place or cavity; an excavation; a pit; an opening in or through a solid body, a fabric, etc.; a perforation; a rent; a fissure.

gene.definition_0: A theoretical unit of heredity of living organisms; a gene may take several values and in principle predetermines a precise trait of an organism's form (phenotype), such as hair color.
gene.definition_1: A segment of DNA or RNA from a cell's or an organism's genome, that may take several forms and thus parameterizes a phenomenon, in general the structure of a protein; locus.

quote.definition_0: A quotation; a statement attributed to a person.
quote.definition_2: A summary of work to be done with a set price.

slide.definition_0: An item of play equipment that children can climb up and then slide down again.
slide.definition_1: A surface of ice, snow, butter, etc. on which someone can slide for amusement or as a practical joke.
slide.definition_2: The falling of large amounts of rubble, earth and stones down the slope of a hill or mountain; avalanche.

shed.definition_1: To part with, separate from, leave off; cast off, let fall, be divested of.

build.definition_0: The physique of a human body; constitution or structure of a human body.
build.definition_1: Any of various versions of a software product as it is being developed for release to users.
build.definition_2: Any structure, such as a building, statue, pool or forest, created by the player.

peace.definition_0: A state of tranquility, quiet, and harmony; absence of violence. For instance, a state free from civil disturbance.
peace.definition_1: A state free of oppressive and unpleasant thoughts and emotions.

abuse.definition_0: Improper treatment or usage; application to a wrong or bad purpose; an unjust, corrupt or wrongful practice or custom.
abuse.definition_2: A delusion; an imposture; misrepresentation; deception.

chase.definition_0: The act of one who chases another; a pursuit.
chase.definition_2: A children's game where one player chases another.

blame.definition_1: Culpability for something negative or undesirable.

fare.definition_0: A going; journey; travel; voyage; course; passage.
fare.definition_1: Money paid for a transport ticket.
fare.definition_2: A paying passenger, especially in a taxi.

graze.definition_0: The act of grazing; a scratching or injuring lightly on passing.
graze.definition_1: A light abrasion; a slight scratch.
graze.definition_2: The act of animals feeding from pasture.

land.definition_0: The part of Earth which is not covered by oceans or other bodies of water.
land.definition_1: Real estate or landed property; a partitioned and measurable area which is owned and on which buildings can be erected.

cycle.definition_0: An interval of space or time in which one set of events or phenomena is completed.
cycle.definition_2: A process that returns to its beginning and then repeats itself in the same sequence.

tape.definition_0: Flexible material in a roll with a sticky surface on one or both sides; adhesive tape.
tape.definition_1: Thin and flat paper, plastic or similar flexible material, usually produced in the form of a roll.
tape.definition_2: Finishing tape, stretched across a track to mark the end of a race.

dome.definition_0: A structural element resembling the hollow upper half of a sphere; a cupola
dome.definition_1: Anything shaped like an upset bowl, often used as a cover

tense.definition_0: (grammar) Any of the forms of a verb which distinguish when an action or state of being occurs or exists.
tense.definition_1: (grammar) An inflected form of a verb that indicates tense.
tense.definition_2: The property of indicating the point in time at which an action or state of being occurs or exists.

skate.definition_0: A light boot, fitted with a blade, used for ice skating.

sense.definition_0: Any of the manners by which living beings perceive the physical world: for humans sight, smell, hearing, touch, taste.
sense.definition_1: Perception through the intellect; apprehension; awareness.

write.definition_0: The act or style of writing.
write.definition_1: The operation of storing data, as in memory or onto disk.

edge.definition_0: The boundary line of a surface.
edge.definition_1: A one-dimensional face of a polytope. In particular, the joining line between two vertices of a polygon; the place where two faces of a polyhedron meet.

close.definition_1: The manner of shutting; the union of parts; junction.

shelf.definition_0: A flat, rigid structure, fixed at right angles to a wall or forming a part of a cabinet, desk etc., and used to support, store or display objects.
shelf.definition_1: The capacity of such an object
shelf.definition_2: A projecting ledge that resembles such an object.

lung.definition_0: A biological organ of vertebrates that controls breathing and oxygenates the blood.
lung.definition_1: (plural) Capacity for exercise or exertion; breath.
lung.definition_2: That which supplies oxygen or fresh air, such as trees, parklands, forest, etc., to a place.

thigh.definition_0: The upper leg of a human, between the hip and the knee.
thigh.definition_1: That part of the leg of vertebrates (or sometimes other animals) which corresponds to the human thigh in position or function; the tibia of a horse, the tarsus of a bird; the third leg-section of an insect.

raise.definition_0: An increase in wages or salary; a rise (UK).
raise.definition_1: A shoulder exercise in which the arms are elevated against resistance.
raise.definition_2: A shot in which the delivered stone bumps another stone forward.

serve.definition_0: An act of putting the ball or shuttlecock in play in various games.
serve.definition_1: A portion of food or drink, a serving.

grief.definition_1: Pain of mind arising from misfortune, significant personal loss, bereavement, misconduct of oneself or others, etc.; sorrow; sadness.
grief.definition_2: Cause or instance of sorrow or pain; that which afflicts or distresses; trial.

wolf.definition_0: The gray wolf, specifically all subspecies of the gray wolf (Canis lupus) that are not dingoes or dogs.
wolf.definition_1: A man who makes amorous advances to many women.
wolf.definition_2: A wolf tone or wolf note.

steak.definition_0: Beefsteak, a slice of beef, broiled or cut for broiling.
steak.definition_1: (by extension) A relatively large, thick slice or slab cut from another animal, a vegetable, etc.
steak.definition_2: (seafood) A slice of meat cut across the grain (perpendicular to the spine) from a fish.

motif.definition_0: A recurring or dominant element; a theme.
motif.definition_1: A short melodic passage that is repeated in several parts of a work.
motif.definition_2: A decorative figure that is repeated in a design or pattern.

fling.definition_0: An act of throwing, often violently.
fling.definition_1: An act of moving the limbs or body with violent movements, especially in a dance.
fling.definition_2: An act or period of unrestrained indulgence.

proof.definition_0: An effort, process, or operation designed to establish or discover a fact or truth; an act of testing; a test; a trial.
proof.definition_1: The degree of evidence which convinces the mind of any truth or fact, and produces belief; a test by facts or arguments which induce, or tend to induce, certainty of the judgment; conclusive evidence; demonstration.
proof.definition_2: The quality or state of having been proved or tried; firmness or hardness which resists impression, or does not yield to force; impenetrability of physical bodies.

golf.definition_0: A ball game played by individuals competing against one another in which the object is to hit a ball into each of a series of (usually 18 or nine) holes in the minimum number of strokes.
golf.definition_1: The letter G in the ICAO spelling alphabet.

leaf.definition_0: The usually green and flat organ that represents the most prominent feature of most vegetative plants.
leaf.definition_1: Anything resembling the leaf of a plant.
leaf.definition_2: A sheet of any substance beaten or rolled until very thin.

ring.definition_0: (physical) A solid object in the shape of a circle.
ring.definition_1: (physical) A group of objects arranged in a circle.
ring.definition_2: A piece of food in the shape of a ring.

wrong.definition_0: Something that is immoral or not good.
wrong.definition_1: An instance of wronging someone (sometimes with possessive to indicate the wrongdoer).
wrong.definition_2: The incorrect or unjust position or opinion.

half.definition_0: One of two usually roughly equal parts into which anything may be divided, or considered as divided.
half.definition_1: Half of a standard measure; frequently used for half a pint of beer or cider.
half.definition_2: (preceded by “a” or a number) The fraction obtained by dividing 1 by 2.

swing.definition_0: The manner in which something is swung.
swing.definition_1: The sweep or compass of a swinging body.
swing.definition_2: A line, cord, or other thing suspended and hanging loose, upon which anything may swing.

plug.definition_0: A pronged connecting device which fits into a mating socket, especially an electrical one.
plug.definition_1: Any piece of wood, metal, or other substance used to stop or fill a hole.
plug.definition_2: A flat oblong cake of pressed tobacco.

mug.definition_0: A large cup for hot liquids, usually having a handle and used without a saucer.

long.definition_2: A note formerly used in music, one half the length of a large, twice that of a breve.

rung.definition_0: A crosspiece forming a step of a ladder; a round.
rung.definition_1: A crosspiece between legs of a chair.

brush.definition_0: An implement consisting of multiple more or less flexible bristles or other filaments attached to a handle, used for any of various purposes including cleaning, painting, and arranging hair.
brush.definition_2: A piece of conductive material, usually carbon, serving to maintain electrical contact between the stationary and rotating parts of a machine.

king.definition_0: A male monarch; a man who heads a monarchy. If it's an absolute monarchy, then he is the supreme ruler of his nation.
king.definition_1: A powerful or majorly influential person.
king.definition_2: Something that has a preeminent position.

high.definition_0: A high point or position, literally or figuratively; an elevated place; a superior region; a height; the sky; heaven.
high.definition_1: A point of success or achievement; a time when things are at their best.
high.definition_2: A period of euphoria, from excitement or from an intake of drugs.

catch.definition_0: The act of seizing or capturing.
catch.definition_1: The act of catching an object in motion, especially a ball.
catch.definition_2: The act of noticing, understanding or hearing.

sting.definition_0: A bump left on the skin after having been stung.
sting.definition_2: A pointed portion of an insect or arachnid used for attack.

flush.definition_0: A group of birds that have suddenly started up from undergrowth, trees etc.

drag.definition_0: Resistance of the air (or some other fluid) to something moving through it.
drag.definition_1: (foundry) The bottom part of a sand casting mold.
drag.definition_2: A device dragged along the bottom of a body of water in search of something, e.g. a dead body, or in fishing.

clash.definition_0: A loud sound, like the crashing together of metal objects.
clash.definition_2: A match; a game between two sides.

north.definition_0: One of the four major compass points, specifically 0°, directed toward the North Pole, and conventionally upwards on a map, abbreviated as N.
north.definition_2: The positive or north pole of a magnet, which seeks the magnetic pole near Earth's geographic North Pole (which, for its magnetic properties, is a south pole).

south.definition_0: One of the four major compass points, specifically 180°, directed toward the South Pole, and conventionally downwards on a map, abbreviated as S.
south.definition_1: The side of a church on the right hand of a person facing the altar.

lunch.definition_0: A light meal usually eaten around midday, notably when not as main meal of the day.
lunch.definition_1: A break in play between the first and second sessions.
lunch.definition_2: (Minnesota) Any small meal, especially one eaten at a social gathering.

march.definition_0: A formal, rhythmic way of walking, used especially by soldiers, bands and in ceremonies.
march.definition_2: Any song in the genre of music written for marching (see Wikipedia's article on this type of music)

sigh.definition_0: A deep, prolonged audible inhale and exhale of breath; as when fatigued, frustrated, grieved, or relieved; the act of sighing.
sigh.definition_1: Figuratively, a manifestation of grief; a lament.

dash.definition_0: Any of the following symbols: ‒ (figure dash), – (en dash), — (em dash), or ― (horizontal bar).
dash.definition_1: (by extension) The longer of the two symbols of Morse code.

fresh.definition_0: A rush of water, along a river or onto the land; a flood.
fresh.definition_1: A stream or spring of fresh water.
fresh.definition_2: The mingling of fresh water with salt in rivers or bays, as by means of a flood of fresh water flowing toward or into the sea.

coach.definition_0: A wheeled vehicle, generally drawn by horse power.
coach.definition_1: A passenger car, either drawn by a locomotive or part of a multiple unit.
coach.definition_2: (originally Oxford University slang) A trainer or instructor.

push.definition_0: A short, directed application of force; an act of pushing.
push.definition_1: An act of tensing the muscles of the abdomen in order to expel its contents.

myth.definition_0: A traditional story which embodies a belief regarding some fact or phenomenon of experience, and in which often the forces of nature and of the soul are personified; a sacred narrative regarding a god, a hero, the origin of the world or of a people, etc.
myth.definition_2: A commonly-held but false belief, a common misconception; a fictitious or imaginary person or thing; a popular conception about a real person or event which exaggerates or idealizes reality.

bench.definition_0: A long seat with or without a back, found for example in parks and schools.
bench.definition_1: The people who decide on the verdict; the judiciary.
bench.definition_2: The place where the judges sit.

forum.definition_1: A gathering for the purpose of discussion.
forum.definition_2: A form of discussion involving a panel of presenters and often participation by members of the audience.

kneel.definition_0: To rest on one's bent knees, sometimes only one; to move to such a position.

kick.definition_0: A hit or strike with the leg, foot or knee.
kick.definition_1: The action of swinging a foot or leg.
kick.definition_2: Something that tickles the fancy; something fun or amusing.

cheek.definition_0: The soft skin on each side of the face, below the eyes; the outer surface of the sides of the oral cavity.
cheek.definition_1: (usually in the plural) The lower part of the buttocks that is often exposed beneath very brief underwear, swimwear, or extremely short shorts.

dough.definition_0: A thick, malleable substance made by mixing flour with other ingredients such as water, eggs, and/or butter, that is made into a particular form and then baked.

torch.definition_0: A stick with a flame on one end, used chiefly as a light source; a similarly shaped implement with a replaceable supply of flammable material.
torch.definition_1: A portable light source powered by electricity; a flashlight.

bank.definition_0: An institution where one can place and borrow money and take care of financial affairs.
bank.definition_1: A branch office of such an institution.
bank.definition_2: An underwriter or controller of a card game; also banque.

thank.definition_0: An expression of appreciation; a thought.

mouth.definition_0: The opening of a creature through which food is ingested.
mouth.definition_1: The end of a river out of which water flows into a sea or other large body of water.

taxi.definition_0: A vehicle that may be hired for single journeys by members of the public, driven by a taxi driver.

match.definition_0: A competitive sporting event such as a boxing meet, a baseball game, or a cricket match.
match.definition_1: Any contest or trial of strength or skill, or to determine superiority.
match.definition_2: Someone with a measure of an attribute equaling or exceeding the object of comparison.

bush.definition_0: A woody plant distinguished from a tree by its multiple stems and lower height, being usually less than six metres tall; a horticultural rather than strictly botanical category.
bush.definition_1: A shrub cut off, or a shrublike branch of a tree.
bush.definition_2: A shrub or branch, properly, a branch of ivy (sacred to Bacchus), hung out at vintners' doors, or as a tavern sign; hence, a tavern sign, and symbolically, the tavern itself.

ranch.definition_0: A large plot of land used for raising cattle, sheep or other livestock.
ranch.definition_1: A small farm that cultivates vegetables and/or livestock, especially one in the Southwestern United States.
ranch.definition_2: A house or property on a plot of ranch land.

tough.definition_0: A person who obtains things by force; a thug or bully.

smash.definition_0: The sound of a violent impact; a violent striking together.
smash.definition_2: Something very successful or popular (as music, food, fashion, etc); a hit.

fork.definition_0: A pronged tool having a long straight handle, used for digging, lifting, throwing etc.
fork.definition_1: A pronged tool for use in the garden; a smaller hand fork for weeding etc., or larger for turning over the soil.

blank.definition_0: A small French coin, originally of silver, afterwards of copper, worth 5 deniers; also a silver coin of Henry V current in the parts of France then held by the English, worth about 8 pence .
blank.definition_2: The white spot in the centre of a target; hence the object to which anything is directed or aimed, the range of such aim .

trunk.definition_2: (heading) A channel for flow of some kind.

check.definition_0: A situation in which the king is directly threatened by an opposing piece.
check.definition_2: A control; a limit or stop.

folk.definition_0: A grouping of smaller peoples or tribes as a nation.
folk.definition_1: The inhabitants of a region, especially the native inhabitants.
folk.definition_2: (plural: folks) One’s relatives, especially one’s parents.

mask.definition_0: A cover, or partial cover, for the face, used for disguise or protection.
mask.definition_1: That which disguises; a pretext or subterfuge.
mask.definition_2: A festive entertainment of dancing or other diversions, where all wear masks; a masquerade

snack.definition_1: An item of food eaten between meals.
snack.definition_2: A very sexy and attractive person.

think.definition_0: An act of thinking; consideration (of something).

rack.definition_0: A series of one or more shelves, stacked one above the other
rack.definition_1: Any of various kinds of frame for holding luggage or other objects on a vehicle or vessel.
rack.definition_2: A device, incorporating a ratchet, used to torture victims by stretching them beyond their natural limits.

park.definition_0: An area of land set aside for environment preservation or recreation.
park.definition_1: A wide, flat-bottomed valley in a mountainous region.
park.definition_2: An area used for specific purposes.

clerk.definition_0: One who occupationally works with records, accounts, letters, etc.; an office worker.
clerk.definition_1: A facilitator of a Quaker meeting for business affairs.
clerk.definition_2: In the Church of England, the layman that assists in the church service, especially in reading the responses (also called parish clerk).

disk.definition_0: A thin, flat, circular plate or similar object.

brick.definition_0: A hardened rectangular block of mud, clay etc., used for building.
brick.definition_1: Such hardened mud, clay, etc. considered collectively, as a building material.

block.definition_0: A substantial, often approximately cuboid, piece of any substance.
block.definition_1: A chopping block; cuboid base for cutting or beheading.
block.definition_2: A group of urban lots of property, several acres in extent, not crossed by public streets.

spoon.definition_0: An implement for eating or serving; a scooped utensil whose long handle is straight, in contrast to a ladle.
spoon.definition_1: An implement for stirring food while being prepared; a wooden spoon.
spoon.definition_2: A measure that will fit into a spoon; a spoonful.

tank.definition_0: A closed container for liquids or gases.
tank.definition_1: An open container or pool for storing water or other liquids.
tank.definition_2: A pond, pool, or small lake, natural or artificial.

pick.definition_0: A tool used for digging; a pickaxe.
pick.definition_1: A tool for unlocking a lock without the original key; a lock pick, picklock.
pick.definition_2: A comb with long widely spaced teeth, for use with tightly curled hair.

shark.definition_0: A scaleless, predatory fish of the superorder Selachimorpha, with a cartilaginous skeleton and 5 to 7 gill slits on each side of its head.

snarl.definition_0: A knot or complication of hair, thread, or the like, difficult to disentangle.
snarl.definition_1: An intricate complication; a problematic difficulty; a knotty or tangled situation.

tick.definition_0: A tiny woodland arachnid of the suborder Ixodida.

veil.definition_0: Something hung up or spread out to hide or protect the face, or hide an object from view; usually of gauze, crepe, or similar diaphanous material.
veil.definition_1: A cover; disguise; a mask; a pretense.

deck.definition_0: Any raised flat surface that can be walked on: a balcony; a porch; a raised patio; a flat rooftop.
deck.definition_1: The floorlike covering of the horizontal sections, or compartments, of a ship. Small vessels have only one deck; larger ships have two or three decks.
deck.definition_2: A main aeroplane surface, especially of a biplane or multiplane.

stall.definition_0: A compartment for a single animal in a stable or cattle shed.
