stall.definition_1: A stable; a place for cattle.
stall.definition_2: A bench or table on which small articles of merchandise are exposed for sale.

tool.definition_0: A mechanical device intended to make a task easier.
tool.definition_1: Equipment used in a profession, e.g., tools of the trade.
tool.definition_2: Something to perform an operation; an instrument; a means.

panel.definition_0: A (usually) rectangular section of a surface, or of a covering or of a wall, fence etc.
panel.definition_1: A group of people gathered to judge, interview, discuss etc. as on a television or radio broadcast for example.
panel.definition_2: An individual frame or drawing in a comic.

drill.definition_0: A tool used to remove material so as to create a hole, typically by plunging a rotating cutting bit into a stationary workpiece.
drill.definition_1: The portion of a drilling tool that drives the bit.
drill.definition_2: An activity done as an exercise or practice (especially a military exercise), particularly in preparation for some possible future event or occurrence.

shock.definition_1: A discontinuity arising in the solution of a partial differential equation.

fuel.definition_0: Substance consumed to provide energy through combustion, or through chemical or nuclear reaction.
fuel.definition_1: Substance that provides nourishment for a living organism; food.
fuel.definition_2: Something that stimulates, encourages or maintains an action.

snail.definition_0: Any of very many animals (either hermaphroditic or nonhermaphroditic), of the class Gastropoda, having a coiled shell.
snail.definition_1: (by extension) A slow person; a sluggard.
snail.definition_2: A spiral cam, or a flat piece of metal of spirally curved outline, used for giving motion to, or changing the position of, another part, as the hammer tail of a striking clock.

palm.definition_0: Any of various evergreen trees from the family Palmae or Arecaceae, which are mainly found in the tropics.
palm.definition_1: A branch or leaf of the palm, anciently borne or worn as a symbol of victory or rejoicing.

room.definition_1: Space for something, or to carry out an activity.

deal.definition_0: A division, a portion, a share.
deal.definition_1: (often followed by of) An indefinite quantity or amount; a lot (now usually qualified by great or good).

goal.definition_0: A result that one is attempting to achieve.
goal.definition_1: In many sports, an area into which the players attempt to put an object.
goal.definition_2: The act of placing the object into the goal.

hall.definition_2: A manor house (originally because a magistrate's court was held in the hall of his mansion).

peel.definition_0: (usually uncountable) The skin or outer layer of a fruit, vegetable, etc.
peel.definition_1: The action of peeling away from a formation.
peel.definition_2: A cosmetic preparation designed to remove dead skin or to exfoliate.

heel.definition_0: The rear part of the foot, where it joins the leg.
heel.definition_1: The part of a shoe's sole which supports the foot's heel.
heel.definition_2: The rear part of a sock or similar covering for the foot.

novel.definition_0: Newly made, formed or evolved; having no precedent; of recent origin; new.
novel.definition_1: Original, especially in an interesting way; new and striking; not of the typical or ordinary type.

tail.definition_0: The caudal appendage of an animal that is attached to its posterior and near the anus.
tail.definition_1: An object or part of an object resembling a tail in shape, such as the thongs on a cat-o'-nine-tails.
tail.definition_2: The back, last, lower, or inferior part of anything.

spell.definition_0: Words or a formula supposed to have magical powers.
spell.definition_1: A magical effect or influence induced by an incantation or formula.

pupil.definition_0: A learner under the supervision of a teacher or professor.
pupil.definition_1: An orphan who is a minor and under the protection of the state.

bowel.definition_0: A part or division of the intestines, usually the large intestine.
bowel.definition_1: (in the plural) The entrails or intestines; the internal organs of the stomach.
bowel.definition_2: (in the plural) The (deep) interior of something.

warn.definition_0: To make (someone) aware of (something impending); especially:
warn.definition_1: To caution or admonish (someone) against unwise or unacceptable behaviour.
warn.definition_2: (chiefly with "off", "away", and similar words) To advise or order to go or stay away.

dream.definition_0: Imaginary events seen in the mind while sleeping.
dream.definition_2: A visionary scheme; a wild conceit; an idle fancy.

stem.definition_0: The stock of a family; a race or generation of progenitors.
stem.definition_2: An advanced or leading position; the lookout.

gown.definition_1: A woman's ordinary outer dress, such as a calico or silk gown.
gown.definition_2: The official robe of certain professional men and scholars, such as university students and officers, barristers, judges, etc.

gloom.definition_1: A melancholic, depressing or despondent atmosphere.
gloom.definition_2: Cloudiness or heaviness of mind; melancholy; aspect of sorrow; low spirits; dullness.

worm.definition_0: A generally tubular invertebrate of the annelid phylum; an earthworm.
worm.definition_1: More loosely, any of various tubular invertebrates resembling annelids but not closely related to them, such as velvet worms, acorn worms, flatworms, or roundworms.
worm.definition_2: A type of wingless "dragon", especially a gigantic sea serpent.

slam.definition_1: The shock and noise produced by violently closing a door or other object.

film.definition_0: A thin layer of some substance; a pellicle; a membranous covering, causing opacity.
film.definition_1: A medium used to capture images in a camera.

widen.definition_2: To let out clothes to a larger size.

disco.definition_0: A genre of dance music that was popular in the 1970s, characterized by elements of soul music with a strong Latin-American beat and often accompanied by pulsating lights.

news.definition_1: Information about current events disseminated via media.

stun.definition_1: That which stuns; a shock; a stupefying blow.

scan.definition_2: The result or output of a scanning process.

term.definition_0: That which limits the extent of anything; limit, extremity, bound, boundary.
term.definition_2: Any of the binding conditions or promises in a legal contract.

warm.definition_0: Having a temperature slightly higher than usual, but still pleasant; mildly hot.
warm.definition_1: Caring and friendly, of relations to another person.
warm.definition_2: Having a color in the red-orange-yellow part of the visible electromagnetic spectrum.

lion.definition_0: A big cat, Panthera leo, native to Africa, India and formerly much of Europe.
lion.definition_1: (by extension) Any of various extant and extinct big cats, especially the mountain lion.

sun.definition_0: A star, especially when seen as the centre of any single solar system.
sun.definition_1: The light and warmth which is received from the sun.
sun.definition_2: Something like the sun in brightness or splendor.

horn.definition_0: A hard growth of keratin that protrudes from the top of the head of certain animals, usually paired.
horn.definition_1: Any similar real or imaginary growth or projection such as the elongated tusk of a narwhal, the eyestalk of a snail, the pointed growth on the nose of a rhinoceros, or the hornlike projection on the head of a demon or similar.

hen.definition_0: A female chicken (Gallus gallus), particularly a sexually mature one kept for its eggs.
hen.definition_1: A female of other bird species, particularly a sexually mature female fowl.
hen.definition_2: A female fish (especially a salmon or trout) or crustacean.

union.definition_0: The act of uniting or joining two or more things into one.
union.definition_1: The state of being united or joined; a state of unity or harmony.
union.definition_2: That which is united, or made one; something formed by a combination or coalition of parts or members; a confederation; a consolidated body; a league.

dozen.definition_1: (as plural only, always followed by of) A large, unspecified number of, comfortably estimated in small multiples of twelve, thus generally implied to be significantly more than ten or twelve, but less than perhaps one or two hundred; many.
dozen.definition_2: An old English measure of ore containing 12 hundredweight.

dawn.definition_0: The morning twilight period immediately before sunrise.
dawn.definition_2: The time when the sun rises.

vein.definition_0: A blood vessel that transports blood from the capillaries back to the heart.
vein.definition_1: (in plural) The entrails of a shrimp.
vein.definition_2: In leaves, a thickened portion of the leaf containing the vascular bundle.

train.definition_1: Connected sequence of people or things.

reign.definition_1: The period during which a monarch rules.
reign.definition_2: The territory or sphere over which a kingdom; empire; realm; dominion, etc. is ruled.

zero.definition_0: The numeric symbol that represents the cardinal number zero.
zero.definition_1: The digit 0 in the decimal, binary, and all other base numbering systems.

brown.definition_0: A colour like that of chocolate or coffee.
brown.definition_1: One of the colour balls used in snooker, with a value of 4 points.

colon.definition_1: The triangular colon (especially in context of not being able to type the actual triangular colon).
colon.definition_2: A rhetorical figure consisting of a clause which is grammatically, but not logically, complete.

van.definition_0: A covered vehicle used for carrying goods or people, usually roughly cuboid in shape, longer and higher than a car but smaller than a truck/lorry.
van.definition_1: An enclosed railway vehicle for transport of goods.
van.definition_2: A light wagon, either covered or open, used by tradesmen and others for the transportation of goods.

nine.definition_1: A playing card with nine pips.

one.definition_1: The neutral element with respect to multiplication in a ring.

crown.definition_0: A royal, imperial or princely headdress; a diadem.
crown.definition_1: A wreath or band for the head, especially one given as reward of victory or a mark of honor.
crown.definition_2: (by extension) Any reward of victory or mark of honor.

three.definition_1: Anything measuring three units, as length.
three.definition_2: A person who is three years old.

eight.definition_1: Any of the four cards in a normal deck with the value eight.
eight.definition_2: A light, narrow rowing boat, especially one used in competitive rowing, steered by a cox, in which eight rowers each have two oars.

ten.definition_0: A set or group with ten elements.
ten.definition_1: A card in a given suit with a value of ten.
ten.definition_2: A denomination of currency, such as a banknote, with a value of ten units. See also tenner.

four.definition_0: The digit or figure 4; an occurrence thereof.
four.definition_1: Anything measuring four units, as length.
four.definition_2: A person who is four years old.

win.definition_1: To reach some destination or object, despite difficulty or toil (now usually intransitive, with preposition or locative adverb).
win.definition_2: To triumph or achieve victory in (a game, a war, etc.).

spin.definition_1: A quantum angular momentum associated with subatomic particles, which also creates a magnetic moment.
spin.definition_2: A favourable comment or interpretation intended to bias opinion on an otherwise unpleasant situation.

six.definition_1: (by ellipsis of six o'clock) Rear, behind (rear side of something).
six.definition_2: An event whereby a batsman hits a ball which does not bounce before passing over a boundary in the air, resulting in an award of 6 runs for the batting team.

five.definition_1: A banknote with a denomination of five units of currency. See also fiver.
five.definition_2: Anything measuring five units, as length.

ratio.definition_0: A number representing a comparison between two named things.
ratio.definition_1: The relative magnitudes of two quantities (usually expressed as a quotient).

loop.definition_0: A length of thread, line or rope that is doubled over to make an opening.
loop.definition_2: A shape produced by a curve that bends around and crosses itself.

piano.definition_0: A percussive keyboard musical instrument, usually ranging over seven octaves, with white and black colored keys, played by pressing these keys, causing hammers to strike strings

seven.definition_0: The digit/figure 7 or an occurrence thereof.

equip.definition_0: To supply with something necessary in order to carry out a specific action or task; to provide with (e.g. weapons, provisions, munitions, rigging)
equip.definition_1: To dress up; to array; to clothe.

pump.definition_0: A device for moving or compressing a liquid or gas.
pump.definition_1: An instance of the action of a pump; one stroke of a pump; any action similar to pumping
pump.definition_2: A device for dispensing liquid or gas to be sold, particularly fuel.

echo.definition_0: A reflected sound that is heard again by its initial observer.
echo.definition_1: An utterance repeating what has just been said.
echo.definition_2: A device in verse in which a line ends with a word which recalls the sound of the last word of the preceding line.

solo.definition_0: A piece of music for one performer.
solo.definition_1: A job or performance done by one person alone.
solo.definition_2: (games) A card game similar to whist in which each player plays against the others in turn without a partner

wrap.definition_0: To enclose (an object) completely in any flexible, thin material such as fabric or paper.
wrap.definition_1: To enclose or coil around an object or organism, as a form of grasping.
wrap.definition_2: To conceal by enveloping or enfolding; to hide.

step.definition_0: An advance or movement made from one foot to the other; a pace.
step.definition_1: A rest, or one of a set of rests, for the foot in ascending or descending, as a stair, or a rung of a ladder.
step.definition_2: A distinct part of a process; stage; phase.

trap.definition_0: A machine or other device designed to catch (and sometimes kill) animals, either by holding them in a container, or by catching hold of part of the body.
trap.definition_1: A trick or arrangement designed to catch someone in a more general sense; a snare.
trap.definition_2: A covering over a hole or opening; a trapdoor.

help.definition_0: Action given to provide assistance; aid.
help.definition_1: (usually uncountable) Something or someone which provides assistance with a task.
help.definition_2: Documentation provided with computer software, etc. and accessed using the computer.

linen.definition_0: Thread or cloth made from flax fiber.
linen.definition_1: Domestic textiles, such as tablecloths, bedding, towels, underclothes, etc., that are made of linen or linen-like fabrics of cotton or other fibers; linens.
linen.definition_2: A light beige colour, like that of linen cloth undyed.

gasp.definition_0: A short, sudden intake of breath.
gasp.definition_1: : A draw or drag on a cigarette (or gasper).

map.definition_0: A visual representation of an area, whether real or imaginary.
map.definition_1: A graphical representation of the relationships between objects, components or themes.

snap.definition_0: A quick breaking or cracking sound or the action of producing such a sound.
snap.definition_2: An attempt to seize, bite, attack, or grab.

strap.definition_0: A long, narrow, pliable strip of leather, cloth, or the like.
strap.definition_1: A strip of thick leather used in flogging.
strap.definition_2: Something made of such a strip, or of a part of one, or a combination of two or more for a particular use.

swop.definition_0: To exchange or give (something) in an exchange (for something else).
swop.definition_2: To beat the air, or ply the wings, with a sweeping motion or noise; to flap.

soup.definition_0: Any of various dishes commonly made by combining liquids, such as water or stock with other ingredients, such as meat and vegetables, that contribute flavor and texture.
soup.definition_1: Any mixture or substance suggestive of soup consistency.

stamp.definition_0: An act of stamping the foot, paw or hoof.
stamp.definition_1: An indentation, imprint, or mark made by stamping.

lamp.definition_0: A device that generates heat, light or other radiation. Especially an electric light bulb.
lamp.definition_1: A device containing oil, burnt through a wick for illumination; an oil lamp.
lamp.definition_2: A piece of furniture holding one or more electric light sockets.

press.definition_0: A device used to apply pressure to an item.
press.definition_2: (collective) The print-based media (both the people and the newspapers).

cross.definition_0: A geometrical figure consisting of two straight lines or bars intersecting each other such that at least one of them is bisected by the other.
cross.definition_1: Any geometric figure having this or a similar shape, such as a cross of Lorraine or a Maltese cross.
cross.definition_2: A wooden post with a perpendicular beam attached and used (especially in the Roman Empire) to execute criminals (by crucifixion).

fuss.definition_0: Excessive activity, worry, bother, or talk about something.
fuss.definition_1: A complaint or noise; a scene.
fuss.definition_2: An exhibition of affection or admiration.

rumor.definition_0: A statement or claim of questionable accuracy, from no known reliable source, usually spread by word of mouth.
rumor.definition_1: Information or misinformation of the kind contained in such claims.

mess.definition_0: A disagreeable mixture or confusion of things; hence, a situation resulting from blundering or from misunderstanding; disorder.

user.definition_0: One who uses or makes use of something, a consumer/client or an express or implied licensee (free user) or a trespasser.
user.definition_1: A person who uses drugs, especially illegal drugs.
user.definition_2: A person who uses a computer or a computing network, especially a person who has received a user account.

tear.definition_0: A hole or break caused by tearing.

guess.definition_0: To reach a partly (or totally) unqualified conclusion.
guess.definition_1: To solve by a correct conjecture; to conjecture rightly.
guess.definition_2: To suppose (introducing a proposition of uncertain plausibility).

bless.definition_0: To make something holy by religious rite, sanctify.
bless.definition_1: To make the sign of the cross upon, so as to sanctify.

color.definition_0: The spectral composition of visible light

amber.definition_0: Ambergris, the waxy product of the sperm whale.
amber.definition_1: A hard, generally yellow to brown translucent fossil resin, used for jewellery. One variety, blue amber, appears blue rather than yellow under direct sunlight.

humor.definition_0: The quality of being amusing, comical, funny.
humor.definition_1: A mood, especially a bad mood; a temporary state of mind or disposition brought upon by an event; an abrupt illogical inclination or whim.
humor.definition_2: Any of the fluids in an animal body, especially the four "cardinal humours" of blood, yellow bile, black bile and phlegm that were believed to control the health and mood of the human body.

anger.definition_0: A strong feeling of displeasure, hostility or antagonism towards someone or something, usually combined with an urge to harm.

wear.definition_1: Damage to the appearance and/or strength of an item caused by use over time

enter.definition_0: The "Enter" key on a computer keyboard.
enter.definition_1: A stroke of the Enter key.

swear.definition_0: To take an oath, to promise.
swear.definition_1: To use offensive, profane, or obscene language.

rider.definition_0: One who rides, often on a horse or a motorcycle.
rider.definition_1: A provision annexed to a bill under the consideration of a legislature, having little connection with the subject matter of the bill.
rider.definition_2: (by extension) Something extra or burdensome that is imposed.

pair.definition_0: Two similar or identical things taken together; often followed by of.
pair.definition_1: Two people in a relationship, partnership or friendship.
pair.definition_2: Used with binary nouns (often in the plural to indicate multiple instances, since such nouns are plural only, except in some technical contexts)

liver.definition_0: A large organ in the body that stores and metabolizes nutrients, destroys toxins and produces bile. It is responsible for thousands of biochemical reactions.
liver.definition_1: This organ, as taken from animals used as food.
liver.definition_2: A dark brown colour, tinted with red and gray, like the colour of liver.

rear.definition_0: To bring up to maturity, as offspring; to educate; to instruct; to foster.
rear.definition_1: (said of people towards animals) To breed and raise.
rear.definition_2: To rise up on the hind legs

major.definition_0: A military rank between captain and lieutenant colonel.

minor.definition_0: A person who is below the age of majority, consent, criminal responsibility or other adult responsibilities and accountabilities.
minor.definition_1: A subject area of secondary concentration of a student at a college or university, or the student who has chosen such a secondary concentration.

stir.definition_0: The act or result of stirring (moving around the particles of a liquid etc.)
stir.definition_1: Agitation; tumult; bustle; noise or various movements.
stir.definition_2: Public disturbance or commotion; tumultuous disorder; seditious uproar.

layer.definition_0: A single thickness of some material covering a surface.
layer.definition_2: One of the items in a hierarchy.

stop.definition_0: A (usually marked) place where buses, trams or trains halt to let passengers get on and off, usually smaller than a station.
stop.definition_1: An action of stopping; interruption of travel.
stop.definition_2: That which stops, impedes, or obstructs; an obstacle; an impediment.

hear.definition_0: (stative) To perceive sounds through the ear.
hear.definition_1: (stative) To perceive (a sound, or something producing a sound) with the ear, to recognize (something) in an auditory way.
hear.definition_2: To exercise this faculty intentionally; to listen to.

skip.definition_0: A leaping, jumping or skipping movement.
skip.definition_1: The act of passing over an interval from one thing to another; an omission of a part.
skip.definition_2: A passage from one sound to another by more than a degree at once.

star.definition_0: Any small luminous dot appearing in the cloudless portion of the night sky, especially with a fixed location relative to other such dots.
star.definition_1: A luminous celestial body, made up of plasma (particularly hydrogen and helium) and having a spherical shape. Depending on context the sun may or may not be included.
star.definition_2: A concave polygon with regular, pointy protrusions and indentations, generally with five or six points.

chaos.definition_0: The unordered state of matter in classical accounts of cosmogony.
chaos.definition_1: Any state of disorder; a confused or amorphous mixture or conglomeration.
chaos.definition_2: A behaviour of iterative non-linear systems in which arbitrarily small variations in initial conditions become magnified over time.

dress.definition_0: An item of clothing (usually worn by a woman or young girl) which both covers the upper part of the body and includes skirts below the waist.
dress.definition_2: The system of furrows on the face of a millstone.

pass.definition_1: To change in state or status

virus.definition_0: A submicroscopic, non-cellular structure consisting of a core of DNA or RNA surrounded by a protein coat, that requires a living host cell to replicate, and often causes disease in the host organism.
virus.definition_1: A disease caused by these organisms.
virus.definition_2: Venom, as produced by a poisonous animal etc.

class.definition_0: A group, collection, category or set sharing characteristics or attributes.
class.definition_1: A social grouping, based on job, wealth, etc. In Britain, society is commonly split into three main classes; upper class, middle class and working class.
class.definition_2: The division of society into classes.

miss.definition_1: A failure to obtain or accomplish.
miss.definition_2: An act of avoidance (used with the verb give).

meet.definition_0: A sports competition, especially for track and field (a track meet) or swimming (a swim meet).
meet.definition_1: A gathering of riders, horses and hounds for foxhunting; a field meet for hunting.
meet.definition_2: A meeting of two trains in opposite directions on a single track, when one is put into a siding to let the other cross.

wrist.definition_0: The complex joint between forearm bones, carpus, and metacarpals where the hand is attached to the arm; the carpus in a narrow sense.
wrist.definition_1: A stud or pin which forms a journal.

menu.definition_0: The details of the food to be served at a banquet; a bill of fare.
menu.definition_1: A list of dishes offered in a restaurant.
menu.definition_2: A list from which the user may select an operation to be performed, often done with a keyboard, mouse, or controller under a graphical user interface

cigar.definition_0: Tobacco rolled and wrapped with an outer covering of tobacco leaves, intended to be smoked.

root.definition_0: The part of a plant, generally underground, that anchors and supports the plant body, absorbs and stores water and nutrients, and in some plants is able to perform vegetative reproduction.
root.definition_2: The part of a tooth extending into the bone holding the tooth in place.

plot.definition_0: (authorship) The course of a story, comprising a series of incidents which are gradually unfolded, sometimes by unexpected means.
plot.definition_1: An area or land used for building on or planting on.
plot.definition_2: A graph or diagram drawn by hand or produced by a mechanical or electronic device.

treat.definition_0: An entertainment, outing, food, drink, or other indulgence provided by someone for the enjoyment of others.
treat.definition_1: An unexpected gift, event etc., which provides great pleasure.
treat.definition_2: A snack food item designed to be given to pets.

loss.definition_0: The result of no longer possessing an object, a function, or a characteristic due to external causes or misplacement.
loss.definition_1: The destruction or ruin of an object.
loss.definition_2: Something that has been destroyed or ruined.

eject.definition_0: To compel (a person or persons) to leave.
eject.definition_1: To throw out or remove forcefully.
eject.definition_2: To compel (a sports player) to leave the field because of inappropriate behaviour.

terms.definition_0: That which limits the extent of anything; limit, extremity, bound, boundary.
terms.definition_2: Any of the binding conditions or promises in a legal contract.

tent.definition_0: A pavilion or portable lodge consisting of skins, canvas, or some strong cloth, stretched and sustained by poles, used for sheltering people from the weather.
tent.definition_1: The representation of a tent used as a bearing.
tent.definition_2: A portable pulpit set up outside to accommodate worshippers who cannot fit into a church.

start.definition_2: The beginning point of a race, a board game, etc.

outdo.definition_0: To excel; go beyond in performance; surpass.

unfed.definition_0: A mosquito that has not had a blood meal.

trawl.definition_0: A net or dragnet used for trawling.
trawl.definition_1: A long fishing line having many short lines bearing hooks attached to it; a setline.

karma.definition_0: The sum total of a person's actions, which determine the person's next incarnation in samsara, the cycle of death and rebirth.
karma.definition_1: A force or law of nature which causes one to reap what one sows; destiny; fate.
karma.definition_2: A distinctive feeling, aura, or atmosphere.

naval.definition_0: Of or relating to a navy.
naval.definition_1: Of or relating to ships in general.

focal.definition_0: Belonging to, concerning, or located at a focus

heath.definition_0: A tract of level uncultivated land with sandy soil and scrubby vegetation; heathland.
heath.definition_1: Any small evergreen shrub of the family Ericaceae.

rebut.definition_0: To drive back or beat back; to repulse.
rebut.definition_1: To deny the truth of something, especially by presenting arguments that disprove it.

adobe.definition_0: An unburnt brick dried in the sun.
adobe.definition_1: The earth from which such bricks are made.
adobe.definition_2: A house made of adobe brick.

crass.definition_0: Coarse; crude; unrefined or insensitive; lacking discrimination

foot.definition_0: A biological structure found in many animals that is used for locomotion and that is frequently a separate organ at the terminal part of the leg.
foot.definition_1: Specifically, a human foot, which is found below the ankle and is used for standing and walking.

asset.definition_0: Something or someone of any value; any portion of one's property or effects so considered.
asset.definition_1: Any component, model, process or framework of value that can be leveraged or reused.

unit.definition_0: A particular, minute unit of mass, defined differently for different substances, but so that varying substances of the same general type have the property that one international unit of the one has the same effect on the human body as one international unit of the other.

east.definition_0: One of the four principal compass points, specifically 90°, conventionally directed to the right on maps; the direction of the rising sun at an equinox. Abbreviated as E.

lost.definition_0: To cause (something) to cease to be in one's possession or capability due to unfortunate or unknown circumstances, events or reasons.
lost.definition_1: To wander from; to miss, so as not to be able to find; to go astray from.
lost.definition_2: To fail to win (a game, competition, trial, etc).

spit.definition_0: A thin metal or wooden rod on which meat is skewered for cooking, often over a fire.
spit.definition_1: A generally low, narrow, pointed, usually sandy peninsula.

merit.definition_0: A claim to commendation or a reward.
merit.definition_1: A mark or token of approbation or to recognize excellence.
merit.definition_2: Something deserving or worthy of positive recognition or reward.

test.definition_1: A cupel or cupelling hearth in which precious metals are melted for trial and refinement.
test.definition_2: (academia) An examination, given often during the academic term.

drift.definition_0: (physical) Movement; that which moves or is moved.
drift.definition_1: The act or motion of drifting; the force which impels or drives; an overpowering influence or impulse.
drift.definition_2: A place (a ford) along a river where the water is shallow enough to permit crossing to the opposite side.

chart.definition_1: A systematic non-narrative presentation of data.

count.definition_0: The act of counting or tallying a quantity.
count.definition_1: The result of a tally that reveals the number of items in a set; a quantity counted.

shift.definition_0: A modifier key whose main function is shifting between two or more functions of any of certain other keys (usually by pressing Shift and the other button simultaneously).

visit.definition_1: A meeting with a doctor at their surgery or the doctor's at one's home.

fleet.definition_0: A group of vessels or vehicles.
fleet.definition_2: A large, coordinated group of people.

hurt.definition_0: An emotional or psychological humiliation or bad experience.
hurt.definition_1: A bodily injury causing pain; a wound or bruise.

west.definition_0: One of the four principal compass points, specifically 270°, conventionally directed to the left on maps; the direction of the setting sun at an equinox, abbreviated as W.

sweet.definition_0: The basic taste sensation induced by sugar.
sweet.definition_1: A confection made from sugar, or high in sugar content; a candy.

draw.definition_0: The result of a contest that neither side has won; a tie.
draw.definition_1: The procedure by which the result of a lottery is determined.
draw.definition_2: Something that attracts e.g. a crowd.

grow.definition_0: To become larger, to increase in magnitude.

glow.definition_0: The state of a glowing object.
glow.definition_1: The condition of being passionate or having warm feelings.
glow.definition_2: The brilliance or warmth of color in an environment or on a person (especially one's face).

allow.definition_0: To grant, give, admit, accord, afford, or yield; to let one have.
allow.definition_1: To acknowledge; to accept as true; to concede; to accede to an opinion.
allow.definition_2: To grant (something) as a deduction or an addition; especially to abate or deduct.

new.definition_2: A naval cadet who has just embarked on training.

law.definition_0: The body of binding rules and regulations, customs and standards established in a community by its legislative and judicial authorities.
law.definition_1: A binding regulation or custom established in a community in this way.

raw.definition_0: (sugar refining, sugar trade) An unprocessed sugar; a batch of such.
raw.definition_1: A galled place; an inveterate sore.
raw.definition_2: (by extension) A point about which a person is particularly sensitive.

row.definition_0: A line of objects, often regularly spaced, such as seats in a theatre, vegetable plants in a garden etc.
row.definition_1: A line of entries in a table, etc., going from left to right, as opposed to a column going from top to bottom.

low.definition_0: Something that is low; a low point.
low.definition_1: The minimum value attained by some quantity within a specified period.

show.definition_0: A play, dance, or other entertainment.

thaw.definition_0: The melting of ice, snow, or other congealed matter; the resolution of ice, or the like, into the state of a fluid; liquefaction by heat of anything congealed by frost
thaw.definition_1: A warmth of weather sufficient to melt that which is frozen

slow.definition_0: Someone who is slow; a sluggard.

snow.definition_0: The frozen, crystalline state of water that falls as precipitation.
snow.definition_1: Any similar frozen form of a gas or liquid.
snow.definition_2: A snowfall; a blanket of frozen, crystalline water.

cluck.definition_0: The sound made by a hen, especially when brooding, or calling her chicks.
cluck.definition_2: A kind of tongue click used to urge on a horse.

booby.definition_1: Any of various large tropical seabirds from the genera Sula and Papasula in the gannet family Sulidae, traditionally considered to be stupid.
booby.definition_2: In the game of croquet, a ball that has not passed through the first wicket.

crate.definition_0: A large open box or basket, used especially to transport fragile goods.
crate.definition_1: (mildly) A vehicle (car, aircraft, spacecraft, etc.) seen as unreliable.
crate.definition_2: In the Rust programming language, a binary or library.

whelp.definition_0: A young offspring of a canid (ursid, felid, pinniped), especially of a dog or a wolf, the young of a bear or similar mammal (lion, tiger, seal); a pup, wolf cub.
whelp.definition_1: An insolent youth; a mere child.

helix.definition_0: A curve on the surface of a cylinder or cone such that its angle to a plane perpendicular to the axis is constant; the three-dimensional curve seen in a screw or a spiral staircase.
helix.definition_1: A small volute under the abacus of a Corinthian capital.
helix.definition_2: The incurved rim of the external ear.

croak.definition_0: A faint, harsh sound made in the throat.
croak.definition_1: The cry of a frog or toad. (see also ribbit)
croak.definition_2: The harsh cry of various birds, such as the raven or corncrake, or other creatures.

marry.definition_0: To enter into the conjugal or connubial state; to take a husband or a wife.
marry.definition_1: (in passive) To be joined to (someone) as spouse according to law or custom.
marry.definition_2: To arrange for the marriage of; to give away as wife or husband.

stool.definition_0: A seat, especially for one person and without armrests.
stool.definition_1: A close-stool; a seat used for urination and defecation: a chamber pot, commode, outhouse seat, or toilet.
stool.definition_2: A plant that has been cut down until its main stem is close to the ground, resembling a stool, to promote new growth.

batty.definition_1: Belonging to, or resembling, a bat (mammal).

abase.definition_0: To lower, as in condition in life, office, rank, etc., so as to cause pain or hurt feelings; to degrade, to depress, to humble, to humiliate.
abase.definition_1: To lower physically; to depress; to cast or throw down; to stoop.
abase.definition_2: To lower in value, in particular by altering the content of alloys in coins; to debase.

floss.definition_0: A thread used to clean the gaps between the teeth.
floss.definition_2: The fibres covering a corncob etc.; the loose downy or silky material inside the husks of certain plants, such as beans.

react.definition_0: An emoji used to express a reaction to a post on social media.

quiet.definition_1: The absence of movement; stillness, tranquility

death.definition_0: The cessation of life and all associated processes; the end of an organism's existence as an entity independent from its environment and its return to an inert, nonliving state.
death.definition_1: (often capitalized) The personification of death as a hooded figure with a scythe; the Grim Reaper. The pronoun he is not the only option, but probably the most traditional one, as it matches with the male grammatical gender of Old English dēaþ, also with cognate German der Tod. The fourth apocalyptic rider (Bible, revelations 6:8) is male θᾰ́νᾰτος (thanatos) in Greek. It has the female name Mors in Latin, but is referred to with male forms qui and eum. The following quotes show this rider on a pale horse is his in the English Bible and she in Peter Gabriel's lyrics.
death.definition_2: (the death) The collapse or end of something.

feign.definition_0: To make a false show or pretence of; to counterfeit or simulate.
feign.definition_1: To imagine; to invent; to pretend.
feign.definition_2: To make an action as if doing one thing, but actually doing another, for example to trick an opponent.

grade.definition_1: The performance of an individual or group on an examination or test, expressed by a number, letter, or other symbol; a score.
grade.definition_2: A degree or level of something; a position within a scale; a degree of quality.

model.definition_0: A person who serves as a subject for artwork or fashion, usually in the medium of photography but also for painting or drawing.
model.definition_1: A person, usually an attractive female, hired to show items or goods to the public, such as items given away as prizes on a TV game show.
model.definition_2: A representation of a physical object, usually in miniature.

blush.definition_0: An act of blushing; a red glow on the face caused by shame, modesty, etc.
blush.definition_1: A glow; a flush of colour, especially pink or red.

sissy.definition_1: A timid, unassertive or cowardly person.
sissy.definition_2: (BDSM) A male crossdresser who adopts feminine behaviours.

dwarf.definition_0: Any member of a race of beings from (especially Scandinavian and other Germanic) folklore, usually depicted as having some sort of supernatural powers and being skilled in crafting and metalworking, often as short with long beards, and sometimes as clashing with elves.
dwarf.definition_1: A person of short stature, often one whose limbs are disproportionately small in relation to the body as compared with normal adults, usually as the result of a genetic condition.
dwarf.definition_2: An animal, plant or other thing much smaller than the usual of its sort.

screw.definition_0: A device that has a helical function.
screw.definition_1: The motion of screwing something; a turn or twist to one side.

straw.definition_0: A dried stalk of a cereal plant.

digit.definition_0: A stage of proficiency or qualification in a course of study, now especially an award bestowed by a university or, in some countries, a college, as a certification of academic achievement. (In the United States, can include secondary schools.)
digit.definition_1: A unit of measurement of angle equal to 1/360 of a circle's circumference.
digit.definition_2: A unit of measurement of temperature on any of several scales, such as Celsius or Fahrenheit.

belly.definition_0: The abdomen, especially a fat one.

crew.definition_0: To make the shrill sound characteristic of a rooster; to make a sound in this manner, either in gaiety, joy, pleasure, or defiance.
crew.definition_1: To shout in exultation or defiance; to brag.
crew.definition_2: To test the reed of a double reed instrument by placing the reed alone in the mouth and blowing it.

forth.definition_0: Forward in time, place or degree.
forth.definition_1: Out into view; from a particular place or position.
forth.definition_2: Beyond a (certain) boundary; away; abroad; out.

maxim.definition_0: A self-evident axiom or premise; a pithy expression of a general principle or rule.
maxim.definition_1: A precept; a succinct statement or observation of a rule of conduct or moral teaching.

mimic.definition_0: A person who practices mimicry, or mime.

print.definition_0: Books and other material created by printing presses, considered collectively or as a medium.
print.definition_1: Clear handwriting, especially, writing without connected letters as in cursive.
print.definition_2: The letters forming the text of a document.

bribe.definition_0: Something (usually money) given in exchange for influence or as an inducement to dishonesty.

pound.definition_0: A unit of mass equal to 16 avoirdupois ounces (= 453.592 37 g). Today this value is the most common meaning of "pound" as a unit of weight.
pound.definition_1: A unit of mass equal to 12 troy ounces (≈ 373.242 g). Today, this is a common unit of weight when measuring precious metals, and is little used elsewhere.

agree.definition_0: To harmonize in opinion, statement, or action; to be in unison or concord; to be or become united or consistent; to concur.
agree.definition_1: To yield assent; to accede;—followed by to.
agree.definition_2: To yield assent to; to approve.

first.definition_0: The person or thing in the first position.
first.definition_1: The first gear of an engine.
first.definition_2: Something that has never happened before; a new occurrence.

offal.definition_0: The internal organs of an animal, used as animal food.
offal.definition_1: A by-product of the grain milling process, which may include bran, husks, etc.

error.definition_0: The state, quality, or condition of being wrong.
error.definition_1: A mistake; an accidental wrong action or a false statement not made deliberately.

argue.definition_0: To show grounds for concluding (that); to indicate, imply.
argue.definition_1: To debate, disagree or discuss opposing or differing viewpoints.
argue.definition_2: To have an argument, a quarrel.

totem.definition_0: Any natural object or living creature that serves as an emblem of a tribe, clan or family.
totem.definition_1: The representation of such object or creature.
totem.definition_2: The clan whose kinship is defined in reference to such an object or creature.

goner.definition_0: Someone (or something) doomed; a hopeless case.

biome.definition_0: Any major regional biological community such as that of forest or desert
biome.definition_1: All the genomes of such a community

golem.definition_0: A humanoid creature made from clay, animated by magic.
golem.definition_1: (by extension) A humanoid creature made from any previously inanimate matter, such as wood or stone, animated by magic.

islet.definition_1: An isolated piece of tissue that has a specific function

lapel.definition_0: Each of the two triangular pieces of cloth on the front of a jacket or coat that are folded back below the throat, leaving a triangular opening between.

civic.definition_0: Of, relating to, or belonging to a city, a citizen, or citizenship; municipal or civil.
civic.definition_1: Of or relating to the citizen, or of good citizenship and its rights and duties.

moult.definition_0: The process of shedding or losing a covering of fur, feathers or skin etc.
moult.definition_1: The skin or feathers cast off during the process of moulting.

bleed.definition_0: An incident of bleeding, as in haemophilia.
bleed.definition_1: A narrow edge around a page layout, to be printed but cut off afterwards (added to allow for slight misalignment, especially with pictures that should run to the edge of the finished sheet).
bleed.definition_2: (sound recording) The situation where sound is picked up by a microphone from a source other than that which is intended.

flick.definition_0: A short, quick movement, especially a brush, sweep, or flip.
flick.definition_1: A motion picture; (in plural, usually preceded by "the") movie theater, cinema.
flick.definition_2: A cut that lands with the point, often involving a whip of the foible of the blade to strike at a concealed target.

guild.definition_0: A group or association mainly of tradespeople made up of merchants, craftspeople, or artisans for mutual aid, particularly in the Middle Ages.
guild.definition_2: A group of diverse species that share common characteristics or habits.

enema.definition_0: An injection of fluid into the large intestine by way of the rectum, usually for medical purposes.
enema.definition_2: A device for administering such an injection.

fjord.definition_0: A long, narrow, deep inlet between cliffs.

steed.definition_0: A stallion, especially in the sense of mount.

erode.definition_0: To wear away by abrasion, corrosion or chemical reaction.
erode.definition_1: To destroy gradually by an ongoing process.

altar.definition_0: A table or similar flat-topped structure used for religious rites.
altar.definition_1: A raised area around an altar in a church; the sanctuary.
altar.definition_2: Anything that is worshipped or sacrificed to.

boozy.definition_1: (of a person) Inclined to consume a significant amount of alcohol.
boozy.definition_2: (of an event) Involving a large consumption of alcohol.

fixer.definition_0: Agent noun of fix; one who, or that which, fixes.
fixer.definition_1: A chemical (sodium thiosulfate) used in photographic development that fixes the image in place, preventing further chemical reactions.
fixer.definition_2: (criminal justice) A person who arranges immunity for defendants by tampering with the justice system via bribery or extortion, especially as a business endeavor for profit.

heron.definition_0: A long-legged, long-necked wading bird of the family Ardeidae.

front.definition_0: The foremost side of something or the end that faces the direction it normally moves.
front.definition_1: The side of a building with the main entrance.

audit.definition_2: An independent review and examination of records and activities to assess the adequacy of system controls, to ensure compliance with established policies and operational procedures, and to recommend necessary changes in controls, policies, or procedures

delta.definition_0: The fourth letter of the modern Greek alphabet Δ, δ.
delta.definition_1: A landform at the mouth of a river where it empties into a body of water.
delta.definition_2: The letter D in the ICAO spelling alphabet, which assigns words to letters of the alphabet.

parry.definition_0: A defensive or deflective action; an act of parrying.
parry.definition_1: A simple defensive action designed to deflect an attack, performed with the forte of the blade.
parry.definition_2: (combat sports and martial arts) A defensive move intended to change the direction of an incoming strike to make it miss its intended target, rather than block and absorb it; and typically performed with an open hand in a downward or sideways slapping motion.

lying.definition_0: To rest in a horizontal position on a surface.
lying.definition_2: To abide; to remain for a longer or shorter time; to be in a certain state or condition.

gamma.definition_0: The third letter of the Greek alphabet (Γ, γ), preceded by beta (Β, β) and followed by delta, (Δ, δ).
gamma.definition_1: The Gamma function, symbolized by Γ.
gamma.definition_2: A constant approximately equal to 0.55721566, symbolized by γ (also known as the Euler–Mascheroni constant).

sonic.definition_1: Having a speed approaching that of the speed of sound in air.

pulpy.definition_1: Having the characteristics of pulp fiction; thus, having a garish focus on sex and violence

exult.definition_0: To rejoice; to be very happy, especially in triumph.

vodka.definition_0: A clear distilled alcoholic liquor made from grain mash.
vodka.definition_1: A serving of the above beverage.
vodka.definition_2: Neutral spirits distilled (or treated after distillation) so as to have no distinctive character, aroma, taste or color.

tilde.definition_1: The character used to represent negation, usually ~ or ¬.

duchy.definition_0: A dominion or region ruled by a duke or duchess. (A grand duchy may be a self-governing state. A simple duchy tends to be a part of a larger kingdom or empire.)

pithy.definition_1: Of, like, or abounding in pith.

unify.definition_0: Cause to become one; make into a unit; consolidate; merge; combine.

agate.definition_0: A semi-pellucid, uncrystallized variety of quartz, presenting various tints in the same specimen, with colors delicately arranged in stripes or bands, or blended in clouds.
agate.definition_1: The size of type between pearl and nonpareil, standardized as 5 1/2-point.

labor.definition_0: Effort expended on a particular task; toil, work.
labor.definition_1: That which requires hard work for its accomplishment; that which demands effort.
labor.definition_2: Workers in general; the working class, the workforce; sometimes specifically the labour movement, organised labour.

corny.definition_2: Producing corn or grain; furnished with grains of corn.

pilot.definition_0: A person who steers a ship, a helmsman.
pilot.definition_1: A person who knows well the depths and currents of a harbor or coastal area, who is hired by a vessel to help navigate the harbor or coast.
pilot.definition_2: A guide book for maritime navigation.

abyss.definition_0: Hell; the bottomless pit; primeval chaos; a confined subterranean ocean.
abyss.definition_1: (frequently figurative) A bottomless or unfathomed depth, gulf, or chasm; hence, any deep, immeasurable; any void space.

spicy.definition_0: Of, pertaining to, or containing spice.
spicy.definition_1: (of flavors) Provoking a burning sensation due to the presence of chilis or similar hot spices
spicy.definition_2: (of flavors or odors) Tangy, zesty, or pungent.

rebus.definition_0: A kind of word puzzle which uses pictures to represent words or parts of words.
rebus.definition_1: A pictorial suggestion on a coat of arms of the name of the person to whom it belongs.

tapir.definition_0: Any one of the species of large odd-toed ungulates of the taxonomic family Tapiridae with a long prehensile upper lip, of which all four surviving species are in genus Tapirus.

aback.definition_0: Towards the back or rear; backwards.
aback.definition_1: In the rear; a distance behind.

gouge.definition_1: A cut or groove, as left by a gouge or something sharp.
gouge.definition_2: (originally United States) An act of gouging.

comet.definition_0: A celestial body consisting mainly of ice, dust and gas in a (usually very eccentric) orbit around the Sun and having a "tail" of matter blown back from it by the solar wind as it approaches the Sun.
comet.definition_1: A celestial phenomenon with the appearance given by the orbiting celestial body.
comet.definition_2: Any of several species of hummingbird found in the Andes.

kebab.definition_0: A dish of pieces of meat, fish, or vegetables roasted on a skewer or spit, especially a doner kebab.
kebab.definition_1: A shish kebab or any other food on a skewer.
kebab.definition_2: The outward growing portions of a shish kebab structure.

coast.definition_0: The edge of the land where it meets an ocean, sea, gulf, bay, or large lake.
coast.definition_1: The side or edge of something.
coast.definition_2: A region of land; a district or country.

growl.definition_0: A deep, rumbling, threatening sound made in the throat by an animal.
growl.definition_1: (by extension) The rumbling sound made by a person's stomach when hungry.

click.definition_0: A brief, sharp, not particularly loud, relatively high-pitched sound produced by the impact of something small and hard against something hard, such as by the operation of a switch, a lock or a latch, or a finger pressed against the thumb and then released to strike the hand.
click.definition_1: An ingressive sound made by coarticulating a velar or uvular closure with another closure.

belch.definition_0: The sound one makes when belching.

briar.definition_0: Any of many plants with thorny stems growing in dense clusters, such as many in the Rosa, Rubus, and Smilax genera.
briar.definition_1: Anything sharp or unpleasant to the feelings.

group.definition_0: A number of things or persons being in some relation to one another.
group.definition_1: A set with an associative binary operation, under which there exists an identity element, and such that each element has an inverse.
group.definition_2: An effective divisor on a curve.

groin.definition_0: The crease or depression of the human body at the junction of the trunk and the thigh, together with the surrounding region.
groin.definition_1: The area adjoining this fold or depression.
groin.definition_2: The projecting solid angle formed by the meeting of two vaults

smart.definition_1: To cause a smart or sting in.
smart.definition_2: To feel a pungent pain of mind; to feel sharp pain or grief; be punished severely; to feel the sting of evil.

chill.definition_0: A moderate, but uncomfortable and penetrating coldness.
chill.definition_1: A sudden penetrating sense of cold, especially one that causes a brief trembling nerve response through the body; the trembling response itself; often associated with illness: fevers and chills, or susceptibility to illness.
chill.definition_2: An uncomfortable and numbing sense of fear, dread, anxiety, or alarm, often one that is sudden and usually accompanied by a trembling nerve response resembling the body's response to biting cold.

gaudy.definition_0: One of the large beads in the rosary at which the paternoster is recited.

triad.definition_2: A branch of a Chinese underground criminal society, mostly based in Hong Kong.

vital.definition_0: Relating to, or characteristic of life.
vital.definition_1: Necessary to the continuation of life; being the seat of life; being that on which life depends.

champ.definition_0: Buddy, sport, mate (as a term of address)

viral.definition_0: A video, image or text spread by "word of mouth" on the internet or by e-mail for humorous, political or marketing purposes.

break.definition_0: An instance of breaking something into two or more pieces.
break.definition_1: A physical space that opens up in something or between two things.
break.definition_2: A rest or pause, usually from work.

using.definition_1: To accustom; to habituate. (Now common only in participial form. Uses the same pronunciation as the noun; see usage notes.)
using.definition_2: (except in past tense) To habitually do; to be wont to do. (Now chiefly in past-tense forms; see used to.)

epoch.definition_0: A particular period of history, especially one considered noteworthy or remarkable.
epoch.definition_1: A notable event which marks the beginning of such a period.
epoch.definition_2: A precise instant of time that is used as a point of reference.

prove.definition_1: To make resistant, especially to water.
prove.definition_2: To allow yeast-containing dough to rise.

grime.definition_0: Dirt, grease, soot, etc. that is ingrained and difficult to remove.
grime.definition_1: A genre of urban music that emerged in London, England, in the early 2000s, primarily a development of UK garage, dancehall, and hip hop.

store.definition_0: A place where items may be accumulated or routinely kept.
store.definition_2: (mainly North American) A place where items may be purchased; a shop.

clock.definition_0: An instrument used to measure or keep track of time; a non-portable timepiece.
clock.definition_1: The odometer of a motor vehicle.
clock.definition_2: An electrical signal that synchronizes timing among digital circuits of semiconductor chips or modules.

finer.definition_2: Behind the batsman and at a small angle to the line between the wickets.

wrote.definition_0: To form letters, words or symbols on a surface in order to communicate.
wrote.definition_1: To be the author of (a book, article, poem, etc.).

rouge.definition_0: Red or pink makeup to add colour to the cheeks; blusher.
rouge.definition_2: A single point awarded when a team kicks the ball out of its opponent's end zone, or when a kicked ball becomes dead within the non-kicking team's end zone. Etymology uncertain; it is thought that in the early years of the sport, a red flag indicated that a single had been scored. (This scoring term is not often used in Canada, with the term single being more commonly used.)

surer.definition_0: Physically secure and certain, non-failing, reliable.
surer.definition_1: Certain in one's knowledge or belief.
surer.definition_2: Certain to act or be a specified way.

rogue.definition_0: A scoundrel, rascal or unprincipled, deceitful, and unreliable person.

usher.definition_0: A person, in a church, cinema etc., who escorts people to their seats.
usher.definition_1: A male escort at a wedding.

trace.definition_1: An enquiry sent out for a missing article, such as a letter or an express package.
trace.definition_2: A mark left as a sign of passage of a person or animal.

boost.definition_0: A push from behind, as to one who is endeavoring to climb.
boost.definition_1: Something that helps, or adds power or effectiveness; assistance.
boost.definition_2: (automotive engineering) A positive intake manifold pressure in cars with turbochargers or superchargers.

truss.definition_0: A bandage and belt used to hold a hernia in place.
truss.definition_1: A structure made up of one or more triangular units made from straight beams of wood or metal, which is used to support a structure as in a roof or bridge.

aside.definition_0: An incidental remark made quietly so as to be heard by the person to whom it is said and not by any others in the vicinity.
aside.definition_1: A brief comment by a character addressing the audience, unheard by other characters.
aside.definition_2: A minor related mention, an afterthought.

troll.definition_0: A supernatural being of varying size, now especially a grotesque humanoid creature living in caves or hills or under bridges.
troll.definition_1: An ugly person of either sex, especially one seeking sexual experiences.
troll.definition_2: Optical ejections from the top of the electrically active core regions of thunderstorms that are red in color that seem to occur after tendrils of vigorous sprites extend downward toward the cloud tops.

weary.definition_0: To make or to become weary.

ferry.definition_0: A ship used to transport people, smaller vehicles and goods from one port to another, usually on a regular schedule.
ferry.definition_1: A place where passengers are transported across water in such a ship.
ferry.definition_2: The legal right or franchise that entitles a corporate body or an individual to operate such a service.

baton.definition_0: A staff or truncheon, used for various purposes
baton.definition_1: The stick of a conductor in musical performances.
baton.definition_2: An object transferred by runners in a relay race.

banal.definition_0: Common in a boring way, to the point of being predictable; containing nothing new or fresh.
banal.definition_1: (history) Relating to a type of feudal jurisdiction or service.

siege.definition_2: A place with a toilet seat: an outhouse; a lavatory.

crank.definition_0: A bent piece of an axle or shaft, or an attached arm perpendicular, or nearly so, to the end of a shaft or wheel, used to impart a rotation to a wheel or other mechanical device; also used to change circular into reciprocating motion, or reciprocating into circular motion.
crank.definition_1: The act of converting power into motion, by turning a crankshaft.
crank.definition_2: Any bend, turn, or winding, as of a passage.

favor.definition_0: A kind or helpful deed; an instance of voluntarily assisting (someone).
favor.definition_2: A small gift; a party favor.

aloft.definition_0: At, to, or in the air or sky.
aloft.definition_1: Above, overhead, in a high place; up.
aloft.definition_2: In the top, at the masthead, or on the higher yards or rigging.

robin.definition_0: Any of various passerine birds (about 100 species) of the families Muscicapidae, Turdidae and Petroicidae (formerly Eopsaltriidae), typically with a red breast.
robin.definition_1: A trimming in front of a dress.

ulcer.definition_0: An open sore of the skin, eyes or mucous membrane, often caused by an initial abrasion and generally maintained by an inflammation and/or an infection.
ulcer.definition_2: Anything that festers and corrupts like an open sore; a vice in character.

tacit.definition_0: Expressed in silence; implied, but not made explicit; silent.
tacit.definition_1: Not derived from formal principles of reasoning; based on induction rather than deduction.

cynic.definition_0: A person who believes that all people are motivated by selfishness.
cynic.definition_1: A person whose outlook is scornfully negative.

rupee.definition_0: The common name for the monetary currencies used in modern India, Mauritius, Nepal, Pakistan, the Seychelles, or Sri Lanka, often abbreviated ₨.
rupee.definition_1: A silver coin circulating in India between the 16th and 20th centuries, weighing one tola (formerly 170–180 troy grains; from 1833, 180 troy grains).

trove.definition_0: A treasure trove; a collection of treasure.

prick.definition_0: A small hole or perforation, caused by piercing.
prick.definition_1: An indentation or small mark made with a pointed object.
prick.definition_2: A dot or other diacritical mark used in writing; a point.

shire.definition_0: Physical area administered by a sheriff.
shire.definition_1: Former administrative area of Britain; a county.
shire.definition_2: The general area in which a person lives or comes from, used in the context of travel within the United Kingdom.

pleat.definition_0: A fold in the fabric of a garment, usually a skirt, as a part of the design of the garment, with the purpose of adding controlled fullness and freedom of movement, or taking up excess fabric. There are many types of pleats, differing in their construction and appearance.
pleat.definition_1: A fold in an organ, usually a longitudinal fold in a long leaf such as that of palmetto, lending it stiffness.

lynch.definition_0: To execute (somebody) without a proper legal trial or procedure, especially by hanging and backed by a mob.

saute.definition_0: To cook (food) using a small amount of fat in an open pan over a relatively high heat, allowing the food to brown and form a crust stopping it from sticking to the pan as it cooks.

epoxy.definition_0: A thermosetting polyepoxide resin used chiefly in strong adhesives, coatings and laminates; epoxy resin.

harry.definition_1: To make repeated attacks on an enemy.

foray.definition_0: A sudden or irregular incursion in border warfare; hence, any irregular incursion for war or spoils; a raid.
foray.definition_1: A brief excursion or attempt, especially outside one's accustomed sphere.

cargo.definition_0: Freight carried by a ship, aircraft, or motor vehicle.

foyer.definition_0: A lobby, corridor, or waiting room, used in a hotel, theater, etc.
foyer.definition_1: The crucible or basin in a furnace which receives the molten metal.
foyer.definition_2: A hostel offering accommodation and work opportunities to homeless young people.

stair.definition_0: A single step in a staircase.
stair.definition_1: A series of steps; a staircase.

askew.definition_0: Turned or twisted to one side.

inert.definition_0: A substance that does not react chemically.

proxy.definition_0: An agent or substitute authorized to act for another person.
proxy.definition_1: The authority to act for another, especially when written.
proxy.definition_2: The written appointment of a proctor in suits in the ecclesiastical courts.

could.definition_0: (auxiliary verb, defective) To know how to; to be able to.
could.definition_1: (modal auxiliary verb, defective) May; to be permitted or enabled to.
could.definition_2: (modal auxiliary verb, defective) To have the potential to; be possible.

robot.definition_0: A machine built to carry out some complex task or group of tasks by physically moving, especially one which can be programmed.
robot.definition_1: An intelligent mechanical being designed to look like a human or other creature, and usually made from metal.
robot.definition_2: A person who does not seem to have any emotions.

solar.definition_0: Of or pertaining to the sun; proceeding from the sun
solar.definition_1: Born under the predominant influence of the sun.
solar.definition_2: Measured by the progress or revolution of the sun in the ecliptic; as, the solar year.

elder.definition_0: An older person or an older member, usually a leader, of some community.
elder.definition_1: One who is older than another.
elder.definition_2: One who lived at an earlier period; a predecessor.

whack.definition_1: Bad (not good), inauthentic, of an inferior quality, contemptible, lacking integrity, lame, or strange.

skill.definition_0: Capacity to do something well; technique, ability. Skills are usually acquired or learned, as opposed to abilities, which are often thought of as innate.

shard.definition_0: A piece of broken glass or pottery, especially one found in an archaeological dig.
shard.definition_1: (by extension) A piece of material, especially rock and similar materials, reminding of a broken piece of glass or pottery.
shard.definition_2: A tough scale, sheath, or shell; especially an elytron of a beetle.

frame.definition_0: The structural elements of a building or other constructed object.
frame.definition_1: Anything composed of parts fitted and united together; a fabric; a structure.
frame.definition_2: The structure of a person's body; the human body.

agora.definition_1: A marketplace, especially in Classical Greece.

query.definition_0: A question, an inquiry (US), an enquiry (UK).
query.definition_2: A set of instructions passed to a database.

wrung.definition_0: To squeeze or twist (something) tightly so that liquid is forced out. See also wring out.
wrung.definition_1: To extract (a liquid) from something wet, especially cloth, by squeezing and twisting it.
wrung.definition_2: To obtain (something from or out of someone or something) by force.

thorn.definition_0: A sharp protective spine of a plant.
thorn.definition_1: Any shrub or small tree that bears thorns, especially a hawthorn.
thorn.definition_2: That which pricks or annoys; anything troublesome.

glyph.definition_2: A visual representation of a letter, character, or symbol, in a specific font and style.

hippy.definition_0: (1950s slang) A teenager who imitated the beatniks.
hippy.definition_1: (1960s slang; still widely used in reference to that era) One who chooses not to conform to prevailing social norms: especially one who subscribes to values or actions such as acceptance or self-practice of recreational drug use, liberal or radical sexual mores, advocacy of communal living, strong pacifism or anti-war sentiment, etc.
hippy.definition_2: (modern slang) A person who keeps an unkempt or sloppy appearance and wearing unusually long hair (for males), and because of it, often stereotyped as a deadbeat.

pooch.definition_1: A dog of mixed breed; a mongrel.

vault.definition_0: An arched masonry structure supporting and forming a ceiling, whether freestanding or forming part of a larger building.
vault.definition_2: Anything resembling such a downward-facing concave structure, particularly the sky and caves.

fanny.definition_1: The buttocks; arguably the most nearly polite of several euphemisms.

quasi.definition_0: Resembling or having a likeness to something

opium.definition_0: A yellow-brown, addictive narcotic drug obtained from the dried juice of unripe pods of the opium poppy, Papaver somniferum, and containing alkaloids such as morphine, codeine, and papaverine.

genre.definition_0: A kind; a stylistic category or sort, especially of literature or other artworks.

avert.definition_1: To ward off, or prevent, the occurrence or effects of.

deter.definition_1: To persuade someone not to do something; to discourage.

undue.definition_0: Excessive; going beyond that what is natural or sufficient.
undue.definition_1: That which ought not to be done; illegal; unjustified.
undue.definition_2: (of a payment etc) Not owing or payable.

gusty.definition_0: (of wind) Blowing in gusts; blustery; tempestuous.
gusty.definition_1: (by extension, metaphoric) Characterized by or occurring in instances of sudden strong expression

guile.definition_0: Astuteness often marked by a certain sense of cunning or artful deception.

udder.definition_0: An organ formed of the mammary glands of female quadruped mammals, particularly ruminants such as cattle, goats, sheep and deer.

covet.definition_0: To wish for with eagerness; to desire possession of, often enviously.
covet.definition_1: To long for inordinately or unlawfully; to hanker after (something forbidden).
covet.definition_2: To yearn; to have or indulge an inordinate desire, especially for another's possession.

inane.definition_0: That which is void or empty.

unite.definition_0: A British gold coin worth 20 shillings, first produced during the reign of King James I, and bearing a legend indicating the king's intention of uniting the kingdoms of England and Scotland.

threw.definition_1: To change in state or status

godly.definition_0: Of or pertaining to a god
godly.definition_1: Devoted to a god or God; devout; righteous.

annul.definition_0: To formally revoke the validity of.
annul.definition_1: To dissolve (a marital union) on the grounds that it is not valid.

prone.definition_1: Having a downward inclination or slope.

arson.definition_0: The crime of deliberately starting a fire with intent to cause damage.

couch.definition_0: Couch grass, a species of persistent grass, Elymus repens, usually considered a weed.

valor.definition_1: Strength of mind in regard to danger; that quality which enables a person to encounter danger with firmness

diode.definition_0: An electronic device that allows current to flow in one direction only; used chiefly as a rectifier.

niece.definition_0: A daughter of one’s sibling, brother-in-law, or sister-in-law; either the daughter of one's brother ("fraternal niece"), or of one's sister ("sororal niece").

filmy.definition_0: Resembling or made of a thin film; gauzy
filmy.definition_1: Covered by (or as if by) a film; hazy

octet.definition_0: A group or set of eight of something.
octet.definition_1: A group of eight musicians performing together.
octet.definition_2: A composition for such a group of musicians.

derby.definition_0: Any of several annual horse races.

mulch.definition_0: Any material used to cover the top layer of soil to protect, insulate, or decorate it, or to discourage weeds or retain moisture.
mulch.definition_1: A material used as mulch, as a decorative redwood bark mulch.

aging.definition_0: To cause to grow old; to impart the characteristics of age to.
aging.definition_1: To postpone an action that would extinguish something, as a debt.

valet.definition_0: A man's personal male attendant, responsible for his clothes and appearance.
valet.definition_1: A hotel employee performing such duties for guests.
valet.definition_2: (professional wrestling) A female performer in professional wrestling, acting as either a manager or personal chaperone; often used to attract and titillate male members of the audience.

daddy.definition_2: An informal term of address for a man.

toxin.definition_0: A toxic or poisonous substance produced by the biological processes of biological organisms.

exalt.definition_0: To honor; to hold in high esteem.
exalt.definition_1: To raise in rank, status etc., to elevate.
exalt.definition_2: To elate, or fill with the joy of success.

lucky.definition_0: (of people) Favoured by luck; fortunate; having good success or good fortune
lucky.definition_1: Producing, or resulting in, good fortune

pushy.definition_0: Aggressively ambitious; overly assertive, bold or determined.

aping.definition_1: To imitate or mimic, particularly to imitate poorly.

mania.definition_0: Violent derangement of mind; madness; insanity.
mania.definition_1: Excessive or unreasonable desire; insane passion affecting one or many people; fanaticism.
mania.definition_2: The state of abnormally elevated or irritable mood, arousal, and/or energy levels.

humid.definition_0: Containing perceptible moisture (usually describing air or atmosphere); damp; moist; somewhat wet or watery.

patio.definition_0: A paved outside area, adjoining a house, used for dining or recreation.
patio.definition_1: An inner courtyard typical of traditional houses in some regions of Spain.

edify.definition_1: To instruct or improve morally or intellectually.

wrest.definition_0: The act of wresting; a wrench or twist; distortion.
wrest.definition_1: A key to tune a stringed instrument.

crave.definition_0: A formal application to a court to make a particular order.

incur.definition_0: To bring upon oneself or expose oneself to, especially something inconvenient, harmful, or onerous; to become liable or subject to
incur.definition_2: To fall within a period or scope; to occur; to run into danger

vomit.definition_0: The regurgitated former contents of a stomach; vomitus.
vomit.definition_2: That which causes vomiting; an emetic.

grave.definition_0: An excavation in the earth as a place of burial
grave.definition_1: Any place of interment; a tomb; a sepulcher.

total.definition_0: An amount obtained by the addition of smaller amounts.

mocha.definition_0: A coffee drink with chocolate syrup added, or a serving thereof; a caffè mocha.
mocha.definition_1: A coffee and chocolate mixed flavour.
mocha.definition_2: A dark brown colour, like that of mocha coffee.

safer.definition_0: Not in danger; out of harm's reach.
safer.definition_2: Providing protection from danger; providing shelter.

rifle.definition_0: A shouldered firearm with a long, rifled barrel to improve range and accuracy.
rifle.definition_2: An artillery piece with a rifled barrel.

plume.definition_0: A feather of a bird, especially a large or showy one used as a decoration.
plume.definition_1: A cluster of feathers worn as an ornament, especially on a helmet; a hackle.
plume.definition_2: A token of honour or prowess; that on which one prides oneself; a prize or reward.

sedan.definition_0: An enclosed windowed chair suitable for a single occupant, carried by at least two porters, in equal numbers in front and behind, using wooden rails that passed through metal brackets on the sides of the chair.
sedan.definition_1: An automobile designed in a configuration with separate compartments for engine space, driver/passenger space and luggage space.

valve.definition_0: A device that controls the flow of a gas or fluid through a pipe.
valve.definition_1: A device that admits fuel and air into the cylinder of an internal combustion engine, or one that allows combustion gases to exit.
valve.definition_2: One or more membranous partitions, flaps, or folds, which permit the passage of the contents of a vessel or cavity in one direction, but stop or control the flow in the opposite direction

study.definition_0: (usually academic) To review materials already learned in order to make sure one does not forget them, usually in preparation for an examination.
study.definition_1: (academic) To take a course or courses on a subject.
study.definition_2: To acquire knowledge on a subject with the intention of applying it in practice.

rivet.definition_0: A cylindrical mechanical fastener that attaches multiple parts together by fitting through a hole and deforming the head(s) at either end.
rivet.definition_1: Any fixed point or certain basis.
rivet.definition_2: A light kind of footman's armour.

pagan.definition_0: A person not adhering to a main world religion; a follower of a pantheistic or nature-worshipping religion.
pagan.definition_1: (by extension) An uncivilized or unsocialized person.
pagan.definition_2: (by extension) An unruly, badly educated child.

stuck.definition_0: To become or remain attached; to adhere.
stuck.definition_2: To tolerate, to endure, to stick with.

stray.definition_0: Any domestic animal that has no enclosure, or its proper place and company, and wanders at large, or is lost; an estray.
stray.definition_1: One who is lost, either literally or metaphorically.
stray.definition_2: The act of wandering or going astray.

lover.definition_0: One who loves and cares for another person in a romantic way; a sweetheart, love, soulmate, boyfriend, girlfriend or spouse.
lover.definition_1: A sexual partner, especially one with whom someone is having an affair.

canoe.definition_0: A small long and narrow boat, propelled by one or more people (depending on the size of canoe), using single-bladed paddles. The paddlers face in the direction of travel, in either a seated position, or kneeling on the bottom of the boat. Canoes are open on top, and pointed at both ends.
canoe.definition_1: An oversize, usually older, luxury car.
canoe.definition_2: Any of the deflectors positioned around a roulette wheel, shaped like upside-down boats.

human.definition_0: A human being, whether man, woman or child.

grind.definition_0: The act of reducing to powder, or of sharpening, by friction.
grind.definition_1: Something that has been reduced to powder, something that has been ground.
grind.definition_2: A specific degree of pulverization of coffee beans.

manga.definition_1: An artistic style heavily used in, and associated with, Japanese comics, and that has also been adopted by a comparatively low number of comics from other countries.
manga.definition_2: A comic in manga style, regardless of the country of origin.

melee.definition_0: A battle fought at close range; hand-to-hand combat; brawling.
melee.definition_1: A noisy, confused or tumultuous fight, argument or scrap.
melee.definition_2: Any any confused, disorganised, disordered or chaotic situation.

slack.definition_0: The part of anything that hangs loose, having no strain upon it.
slack.definition_1: A tidal marsh or shallow that periodically fills and drains.

risen.definition_0: To move, or appear to move, physically upwards relative to the ground.
risen.definition_1: To increase in value or standing.

given.definition_0: (ditransitive) To move, shift, provide something abstract or concrete to someone or something or somewhere.
given.definition_1: (ditransitive) To estimate or predict (a duration or probability) for (something).
